WELL_NAME API12 WAR_START_DT TEXT_REMARK
0 001 608084002100 2010-05-16 05/16/10: Skid BOP to park position. R/D riser handling tools. Begin between well work prior to transit to KC 785. 05/17/10: Continue with O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785. 05/18/10: Continue wwith O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785. 05/19/10: Continue with O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785. Begin transit to KC 785 @ 0130 hrs. Stop @ 1200 hrs to perform black out test and DP testing. Resume transit @ 1600 hrs. 05/20/10: Continue with transit to KC 785. On location KC 785 @ 0430 hrs. Jump ROV and deploy compatts. Position ship and calibrate compatts. Continue with DP acceptance tests. 05/21/10: Complete DP acceptance tests @ 1030 hrs. Hold pre-job safety meeting and R/U 36" casing running tools. Run 4 jts. 36" casing and LPWHH and land in rotary table. R/D casing handling tools. Run 30" jetting assy inside 36". Make up CADA tools. Install 4" ball valves on LPH; left in open position. RIH with 36" casing and jetting assy on 50# DP to 3841'. 05/22/10: Continue RIH w/ 36" casing and tag mud line @ 6686'. Jet in 36" casing to 6997' (includes RKB elevation of 92'). This section drilled w/ 8.6 PPG seawater. Maintain 780K while soaking casing. Fugro surveyed coordinates for Buckskin KC 785 are as follows: Y: 9504321.68 X:1924285.66 Lat: N 26 11 26.3585" Lon: W 092 08 02.6535" (NAD 27 - UTM15)
1 001 608084002100 2010-05-23 05/23/2010: Continue to allow 36¿ casing to soak. Slack off casing; ROV monitor LPWHH for 15 mins. No subsidence observed. Take 20K overpull and release CADA; POOH until bit clear of LPWHH. Move ship 50¿ off location. Wait on approval from MMS to continue drilling. 05/24/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/25/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/26/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/27/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/28/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/29/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.
2 001 608084002100 2010-05-30 05/30/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 05/31/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling. 06/01/2010: Decision made to move drillship to SS362 during Drilling Moratorium. P/U compatts and begin move to SS362.
3 001 608084002100 2011-05-16 5/16/2011: Arrived on location at Buckskin; KC 785 #1 at 02:00 hrs. Deployed compatts and calibrated. Performed seabed survey and inspected 38" LPWH. Ran 26" BHA and drilled 26" hole riserless to 7;072' MD/TVD with seawater. 5/17/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 8;835' MD/TVD. Started displace hole to 10.0 ppg FWPAD mud (fresh water mud - equivalent of dynamic kill fluid) at 7;400' MD/TVD. 5/18/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 10;030' MD/TVD. Increased MW to 10.5 ppg FWPAD mud at 9;000' MD/TVD and to 11.0 ppg at 9;500' MD/TVD. 5/19/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 10;075' MD/TVD. Displaced hole to 12.0 ppg FWPAD mud and spotted 50 bbls of 16.0 ppg FWPAD mud at TD. POOH 26" BHA and ran 22" casing to 7;463' MD/TVD. 5/20/2011: Ran 22" casing to 10;000' MD/TVD (22" shoe depth). Cemented 22" casing with 9;966 cu.ft. of 14.5 ppg foam Lead and 1;044 cu.ft. of foam Tail. Confirmed cement returns with ROV. 5/21/2011: Continued cementing 22" casing with 651 cu.ft. of 16.9 ppg unfoam Tail slurry. Displace cement with seawater. Check float holding. Release MRLD (mechanical rigid lockdown) and displace 22" casing with 12.0 ppg FWPAD mud. POOH with landing string and inner string. R/U riser handling equipment.
4 001 608084002100 2011-05-22 05/22/2011: Re-tested upper; middle and lower VBRs on 4-1/2" drill pipe; 250 psi low; 12000 psi high for 5 min each. Prep BOP to splash; skid BOP under well center. Splash BOP at 23:30 hrs. 05/23/2011: Tested choke and kill lines to 250 psi. Noticed communication issue with high temperature and accumulator sensors on Yellow pod while performing high test on choke and kill lines. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection on Yellow pod; found leak on Blue pod upper shear ram function. Repair SPM valves on Blue pod. At 22:20 hrs.; developed leak on Yellow pod wedge packer. 05/24/2011: Change out shuttle valves and blown packer seals. Test riser connector to 250/7500 psi for 5 min each and choke and kill stabs to 250/11400 psi 5 min each. Function tested upper; middle and lower VBRs and all fail-safe valves on Blue and Yellow pods. Troubleshoot leak on Yellow pod wedge packer and SPM valve. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection stabs. 05/25/2011: Change out Yellow pod wedge packers and adjusted spacing on retainer plate. Test electrical integrity on Yellow pod (MEG). Yellow pod did not MEG correctly. Remove PBOF cable from RTU to Yellow and Blue wet make/break; drained fluid. Found broken wire and repaired same. Install PBOF. Verify accumulator pressure. Function test shear rams and 2 fail safe valves on Yellow and Blue pods. No loss of accumulator pressure observed. 05/26/2011: Splash BOPs @ 00:30 hrs. Halliburton test choke and kill lines to 250 psi low and 10000 psi high for 5 min each. Good low test. On high test; developed leak and switched pumps and repeated test to get a good high test. Noticed small leak while testing valves in line-up to test tool. Realigned test line and repeated test to get good test. Halliburton tested choke and kill lines to 250/10000 psi for 5 min each with fresh water while running BOP on riser at 868'; 1618' and 2818'. 05/27/2011: Run riser to 4093'. Mid-water bullseye (jt #42 & #43) reading was 3/4 at 160 deg. Halliburton tested choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines for 250/10000 psi for 5 min each using freshwater at 4093' and then again at 5369' and 6438'. Pick up termination joint from 6438' to 6513'. Pick up telescopic joint and install drape hoses. 05/28/2011: Landed BOPs with a ship heading of 280°. Set 50k down. Subsea latched the wellhead connector with the Blue pod using SEM A with a gallon count of 9.3. Performed 100k overpull test. Transferred weight to the tensioners. Performed slump test. ROV closed blind shear rams. Time to close 4 minutes 49 seconds. ROV skid pump pressure 1700 psi. ROV skid flow rate 8.1 gpm. Halliburton perform BSR; wellhead connector and casing test. 250 for 5 minutes and 2300 psi for 30 minutes with sea water. Good test. 12 bbls to pressure up; bled back 11-1/4 bbls. ROV removed hot stab. Opened BSR from CCU on Blue pod. 42 seconds to open. 39.5 gallons to open. Performed subsea deadman / autoshear procedure from CCU @ 14:20 hrs. Halliburton pressured up to 1000 psi to confirm shears closed @ 15:40 hrs. Good test. Open BSR from CCU Blue pod 41 seconds; 39.4 gallons. Lay down landing joint. Picked up and installed diverter. Took 10k overpull. Lay down running tool. Run hole with BOP test assembly from surface to 619'. Monitor well on trip tank. Well static.
5 001 608084002100 2011-05-29 05/29/2011: RIH to 2855' with BOP test tool BHA. TIH to 7864'. Performed diverter function test. Performed accumulator test. Tested BOPs with 8.6 ppg SW to 250/9;400 psi for 5 min. Tested annular to 250/7000 psi for 5 min each. Function test BOPs on Yellow pod from OIM's panel. Flow check well for 10 min on trip tank. Well static. POOH 1500' with test assembly. 05/30/2011: POOH 1510'. Functioned casing and BSR. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 9834'. Obtain annular temperatures with LWD. Wash and ream ratty cement to 9900'. Tag firm cement @ 9900'. Drill firm cement to 9920'. Displace from 8.6 ppg seawater to 9.8 ppg Rheliant SBM. C&C mud taking returns back to active pits. Take slow SPR/SCR. 05/31/2011: Closed and located annular. Take gallon counts to open and close annular. Get choke line friction. Applied 520 psi to casing and held choke drill with crew. Drill cement from 9925' to 9995'. Drill shoe @ 10;000'. Cleaned out rathole and drilled from 10;075' to 10;085'. Flow check; CBU to WH + 500' inside riser with 9.8 ppg SBM. C&C mud to 9.8 ppg; flow check; well static. Perform FIT to 583 psi = 10.9 ppg EMW (11.3 ppg EMW on MWD tool). Continue drilling to 10;186'. Open reamer. Drill to 10;700'. 06/01/2011: Continued drilling to 11;126'. Repaired cuttings auger in shaker house. Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" to 11;555'. 06/02/2011: Drill ahead to 11;970'; taking surveys every stand and troubleshoot auger and dryer. Pumped 100 bbls 11.8 ppg sweep. Held pit drill with crew at 10:35 hrs ¿ reaction time 102 seconds; total time to secure well 147 seconds. Monitor well on the trip tank while repairing auger in the shaker house. Continue drilling 12;600'; increase MW to 10.0 ppg at 12;500'. Held pit drill at 19:43 hrs ¿ 108 sec; 153 sec total time. 06/03/2011: Work thru tight spots; troubleshoot mud pumps and TDS. Drill ahead to 13;210'. Weight up to 10.2 ppg. Continue drilling 18-1/8" x 21" hole section to 13;495'. 06/04/2011: Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole to 14;145'. Pump 100 bbls 14 ppg weighted high vis sweep. CBU. Pumped static MW = 10.58 ppg. Weight up active mud system to 10.5 ppg (verbal approval from Mr. David Stanley).
6 001 608084002100 2011-06-05 06/05/2011: Spot 40 bbl 16.4 ppg weighted pill on bottom at 14;145' MD/TVD. POOH to 9;196' MD/TVD and perform 7-day BOP function test from driller¿s panel; blue pod; and diverter function test from OIM panel. POOH to 7;122' MD/TVD and retrieve wear sleeve; continue POOH to surface. Function BSR and CSR from driller¿s panel; blue pod. 06/06/2011: Rig up to run 17-7/8" x 18" casing. Run 1;476' of 17-7/8" 93.5 ppf casing; 2;435' of 17-7/8" 106.3 ppf casing; and 614' of 18" 116 ppf casing. Run 5" inner string and M/U 18" hanger. RIH with casing on landing string to 5;847' MD/TVD; taking mud losses of 15 bbls/stand. Well static on connections. 06/07/2011: Continue TIH with 17-7/8" x 18" casing on 6-5/8" landing string; taking losses of 30-35 bbls/stand; well static on connections. Land casing on 18" supplemental adaptor at 9;501' MD/TVD; with shoe at 14;026' MD/TVD. Break circulation; no returns. Convert surge tools. 06/08/2011: Cement 17-7/8" x 18" casing with 663 cu.ft of 14.5 ppg lead cement and 1;213 cu.ft of 16.4 ppg tail cement. Displaced cement with 10.5 ppg SBM and checked floats. Estimated TOC at 11;430' MD/TVD; 1;718 cu.ft cement in annulus; 165 cu.ft in shoe track. Released running tool and set seal assembly; tested seal assembly to 1900 psi with 10.5 ppg SBM for 5 min - good test. POOH with landing string and inner string. Close BSR and conduct 30 min casing and BSR test to 1900 psi with 10.5 ppg SBM. Note: Hanger running tool hung up on slip joint while POOH causing damage to the tool. 06/09/2011: Mobilize camera to location; close blind shear rams and monitor well on stripping tank. Displaced upper riser to seawater at 200' and RIH with camera to inspect slip joint for damage - no visibility. Displaced seawater to fresh water to improve visibility; with no success. 06/10/2011: Displaced freshwater out of riser and dropped fluid level to 135 ft. Continued to monitor well on stripping tank. RIH with camera and inspected slip joint inner barrel. No damage noted. RIH with 16.5" x 19" drilling BHA to 7;790' MD/TVD. Spaced out on BOP stack; closed test rams and performed BOP test to 250/5500 psi on rams and 250/5000 psi on annular for 5 min each with 10.5 ppg SBM. 06/11/2011: Continued BOP test with choke manifold and floor valves tested to 250/9400 psi for 5 min. Performed diverter function from driller¿s panel and accumulator test from CCU; yellow pod. RIH to 13;623' MD/TVD; spaced out on annular and perform choke drills with crew. RIH to 13;758' MD/TVD and washed and reamed ratty cement to 13;931' MD/TVD. Tagged firm cement at 13;931' MD/TVD and drilled to 13;950' MD/TVD while increasing MW to 10.7 ppg.
7 001 608084002100 2011-06-12 Ongoing MWD/LWD and/or Mudlog Operations 06/12/2011: Continued circulating mud system over 10.7 ppg prior to drilling out 18" casing shoe. Took slow circulating rates and choke line frictions; and conducted choke drills with drill crew. Drilled remaining shoe track from 13;950' MD/TVD to 14;007' MD/TVD. Continued drilling cement from 14;010' to 14;047' MD/TVD and then washed and reamed down to 14;145 MD/TVD. Drilled 10' of new formation to 14;155' MD/TVD and circulated cuttings above BOP for LOT. Conducted LOT to 1823 psi with 10.7 ppg SBM (EMW = 13.2 ppg). Pumped up 13.54 ppg EMW with PWD. Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 14;155' to 14;330' MD/TVD. 06/13/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 14;330' to 15;775' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 11.0 ppg SBM at 14;626' MD/TVD and to 11.3 ppg SBM at 15;500' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 60 ft/hr. 06/14/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 15;775' to 16;975' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight 11.5 ppg at 16;500' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 50 ft/hr. 06/15/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 16;975' to 17;485' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 11.8 ppg SBM at 17;275' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 21 ft/hr. 06/16/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 17;485' to section TD at 17;678' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 12.1 ppg SBM at 17;669' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 21 ft/hr. Circulated and conditioned mud for running casing; flushed choke & kill lines; and spotted 55 bbls of 16.4 ppg SBM in the 16-1/2" rathole. POOH from TD to 13;845' MD/TVD and function tested diverter and BOP stack on Yellow Pod from OIM panel. Continued to POOH from 13;845' to 6;096' MD/TVD and function tested BSR on Yellow Pod from OIM panel. Note: Verbal approval for changing the 16" casing setting depth from 18;400' to +/-17;550' was give by Mr. David LeLeux at 09:35 hrs on 6/16/11. 06/17/2011: Continued to POOH from 6;096' MD/TVD to surface and racked back BHA. Circulated riser through the boost line at 805 gpm to shear mud and remove slugs. Picked up and RIH with Nominal Bore Protector (NBP) running tool and set NBP in wellhead in preparation for wireline VSP run; POOH with the NBP running tool. Rigged up wireline unit and ran in the hole with VSP tools to 2100' MD/TVD. Note: Modification of Permit to Drill for the alteration of the 16" casing point to 17;521' TVD/MD was approved by Mr. Marty Rinaudo at 12:24 hrs on 6/17/11. 06/18/2011: Continued to RIH with VSP wireline log from 2100' to 17;600' MD/TVD; taking down-going checkshots at 8;000'; 12;000' and 16;000' MD/TVD. Begin POOH while acquiring up-going data with 104-level; 50' spaced ZVSP from 17;600' to 12;450' MD/TVD. Continue POOH with up-going checkshots at 500' spacing from 12;500' to 7;000' MD/TVD. Pulled wireline tools to surface and rigged down equipment. Picked up NBP retrieval tool and RIH to retrieve NBP.
8 001 608084002100 2011-06-19 06/19/2011: Rigged up to run 16" casing. Held a pre-task safety meeting with crews on picking up and running 16" casing. Begin to run shoe track and 16" casing. At shoe depth of 5;464'; the hole filling the pipe at 17 spm at 180 psi; saw a 50 psi increase in stand pipe pressure. Lined up on boost choke and kill lines. Started boosting riser with 85 spm at 225 psi with 12.1 ppg SBM. 06/20/2011: Circulate 1 riser volume down choke and kill lines with 12.1 ppg mud at 452 gpm w/ 220 psi to improve auto fill flow in the csg. Broke circulation down 16" casing and circulated staging up pumps from 42-84 gpm @ 245 psi. Continued RIH with 16" 97# HPQ-125 SLSF casing from 5;464' to 6;745' and 16.040" 109.61 HPQ-125 SLSF from 6;745' to 10;609'. Rig down Frank's flow back tool and casing elevators. Rig up Frank's drill pipe elevators. Clean rig floor. 06/21/2011: P/U and M/U Dril-Quip 16" casing hanger joint. RIH with 16" casing on 6-5/8" 47# DP from 10;652' to 13;912'. Continued RIH with 16" casing string on 50# drill pipe from 13;913' to 17;456'. Picked up and RIH with 2 singles of 50# drill pipe. Observed decrease in weight as hanger landed out in 16" SA at 6;901'. Continued slacking off and observed hanger pins shear out. Made up Blackhawk cement head and continued slacking off to 342 klbs. Circulate down cement head with rig pumps. Test cement lines; pump 150 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer. Mixed and pumped 5 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; dropped bottom dart; continue to pump 110 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; consisting of yield of 1.42 cubic feet. Mixed and pumped 191 bbls of 16.6 ppg tail cement at 5 bpm. Yield 1.05 cubic feet per sack. Dropped top dart and pump 20 bbls of tail cement follow by 20 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer. Displace cement with rig pumps. 06/22/2011: Continued pumping and bumped the plug with 1250 psi; 2384 bbls pumped. Increased pressure to 2000 psi and held for 10 mins. Bled back 8 bbls and observed no reduction in flow back. Floats did not hold. Bullheaded back 8 bbls; locked in 1800 psi on 16" casing string and commenced waiting on cement for 12 hours. Bled back 11 bbls. Set seal assembly. Test seal assembly to 5000 psi for 10 minutes. Circulate down the landing cement. Rig down cement head. Trip running tool and landing string out of the hole. 06/23/2011: Continue to pull out of the hole with CHSART and landing string. Functioned blind/casing shear rams on Blue pod from the Driller's panel. Slip and cut drill line. Closed the blind shear rams on the Yellow pod from the OIM's panel and pressure tested the 16" casing to 230 psi low; 3300 psi high for 30 minutes and the blind shear rams to 230 psi low 5 mins; 3300 psi high 5 mins. HES pumped 26.3 bbls and bled back 26.3 bbls of 12.1 ppg SBM during the pressure test. Pick up 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" rotary steerable BHA and trip into the hole. Land out wear sleeve. Held a well control drill while tripping 70 second reaction time. Function tested diverter and BOP stack on Yellow pod from Driller's panel. Continued trip in the hole. 06/24/2011: Continued to trip in the hole with up 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" rotary steerable BHA while testing choke manifold to 250/3600 psi for 5 minutes with 12.1 ppg SBM. At 16;940'; perform Accumulator test. Perform Annular pressure test of 250/5100 and BOP pressure test 250/5500 psi with a 12.1 ppg SBM on the Blue pod from the OIM panel. Perform choke surface manifold equipment test 250/9500 psi. Rotate and wash down; tag firm cement at 17;296'. Take SPR and CLF. 06/25/2011: Performed Well Control choke drills with TOI crews. Displace mud from 12.1 ppg to 12.3 ppg while drilling firm cement in shoe track from 17;296' to 17;513'. Drill the top and bottom float collar and shoe. Washed and ream the rathole. Drilled 10' feet of new formation to 17.678'. Circulated cuttings above the stack. Perform a LOT with 12.3 ppg SBM. After pumping 11.5 bbls; the pressure broke over at 1119 psi (EMW 13.52 ppg). Bled back 8.5 bbls. Lost 3 bbls to the formation. Opened annular and circulated up max downhole pressure of 13.82 ppg. Continue drilling ahead from 17;688' to 17;800'.
9 001 608084002100 2011-06-26 06/26/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole with rotary steerable assembly from 17;800' to 18;007' 06/27/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole with rotary steerable assembly from 18;007' to 18;104'. 06/28/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;104' to 18;194'. 06/29/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;194' to 18;304'. 06/30/2011: Drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;304' to 18;324'. Took final survey with MWD at 18;320'. Flow checked well at 18;324'. Gained 0.7 bbls in 12 minutes; last 3 minutes static. Pipe slugging creating flow back to trip tank. Took SCR's at 18;324' with 12.3 ppg SBM. POOH from 18;324' to 17;651' and check the UR's arms close. POOH from 17;651' to 17;523'. Flow checked and confirmed well static. Pumped slug and POOH from 17;523' to 9;051'. Held well control drill while tripping for 1 minute 54 seconds to secure the well; total drill time 2 minutes 54 seconds. POOH from 9051' to 993'. Function the diverter from the Driller's panel. POOH with BHA from 993' to surface; R/B same. 07/01/2011: Performed function test on Blind and Casing Shear Rams from OIM's panel on Blue pod. Functioned tested Upper and Lower shear rams from OIM's panel on Blue pod. Upper shear rams: 37 sec/43.2 gal to close; 35 sec/39.7 gal to open. Lower shear rams: 39 sec/42.8 gal to close; 38 sec/39.9 gal to open. Held well control drill while tripping: 126 seconds reaction time; 231 seconds total. Performed diverter function test from OIM's panel. TIH with new 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling BHA. Spaced-out and closed the annular with 41.6 gal to locate 6-5/8" tool joint. Open annular with 36.7 gal and function tested the pipe rams and fail safes on the Blue pod from the OIM's panel. Continued to RIH with drilling assembly to bottom. 10 001 608084002100 2011-07-03 07/03/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 18;492' to 18;619'. Entered salt formation at 18;585'. Pulled back to 18;580' and flow checked. Well static. Reversed out landing string from 13.0ppg CaBr to 8.6ppg seawater @ 10 bbl/min w 1000 psi. Opened Upper Annular; flow check well on trip tank. Unlatched SSTT. POOH racking back land out assembly from 6;714' to 3;800'. Thurs - 10/18/18 - Continued to POOH with landing string and SSTT to RKB. Unlatched BOPs . PU and cleared wellhead. Moved rig 46M to West to safe zone. ROV recovered bore protector from THD. Prepped THD for EVDT installation. Landed EVDT; ROV verified the indicator was in the fully landed out position. Latched EVDT. Applied 13;500 psi via ROV; and performed pressure test on the VX gasket @ 15min visual on ROV gauge. Moved vessel to well center. Landed and latched BOP. Performed push pull test 100k Down/Up. ROV close PSV & ASV on the EVDT. Tested connector to 1;000 psi / 5 mins. Good test. Tested lower BSR's against closed PSV & ASV on the EVDT to 13;500 psi / 5 mins. Tested the THD connector in conjunction. Functioned diverter from primary control station. PU SSTT and RIH to 2;400'. Fri - 10/19/18 - Continued to RIH with SSTT. Landed SSTT in top of tree @ 6;705'. Displaced choke and kill lines from seawater to 13.0 ppg CaBr2. Performed VX gasket test via IWOCS; apply 13;500 psi down TST line and charted for 15mins. Performed Tree Gallery test via ROV to 13;500 psi and charted for 5min. Tested surface equipment to 10;700 psi for 5 min on chart. Aligned surface tree and manifolds for opening SCSSV. Pressured up 3;800 psi and opened SCSSV. Opened Upper IWS; pressured up on landing string to 3500 psi ( 18;960 psi DH) and closed upper IWS. Equalize pressure across Lower IWS sleeve; opened same. Pressured up on tubing to shear X-RFV; observed 25;476 psi on Lower IWS & 19;450 psi on Upper IWS when AFV shifted. Handed over well to Cetco @ 02:30 hrs. Began flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. Initial UW4 Sand Reading @ 0300 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 18;873 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 220°F; Annulus PSI 6;370; Choke Pressure 3;488 PSI on 14/64 Choke; Gas Rate 0 MMscfd; Oil Rate 0 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day. Sat - 10/20/18 - Continued flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. Reading @ 0500 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 17;221 psi; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;704; Choke Pressure 7;295.48 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .467 MMscfd; Oil Rate 6;971 bbl/day; Water Rate 116.7 bbl/day.
189 SS003 608084006101 2018-10-21 Sun - 10/21/18 - Continued well flow operations. Shut in lower zone on Cetco choke @ 06:30 hrs. Final Reading for UW4 sand @ 0600 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 17;202 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;727; Choke Pressure 7;312.92 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .459 MMscfd; Oil Rate 7;014.4 bbl/day; Water Rate 58.2 bbl/day. Equalized pressure in tubing; shifted upper IWS sleeve. Closed KWV; bled pressure to 0 psi. Shifted upper sleeve. Turned well over to Cetco; flowed upper zone as per LLOG procedure. Initial Reading for upper sands @ 1000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 18;666 psi; Down Hole Temperature 223°F; Annulus psi 7;126; Choke Pressure 8;232.67 psi on 12/64 Choke; Gas Rate .19 MMscfd; Oil Rate 3;074.50 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day. Mon - 10/22/18 - Continued well flow operations by flowingd upper zone as per LLOG procedure. Shut well in @ 00:20 hrs @ Cetco Choke. Closed upper IWS sleeve. Final Reading for upper sands @ 0000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 19;091 psi; Down Hole Temperature 226°F; Annulus psi 7;537; Choke Pressure 9;030.26 psi on 22/64 Choke; Gas Rate .803 MMscfd; Oil Rate 9;322.1 bbl/day; Water Rate 504.9 bbl/day. Equalized pressure between Common DHPT and Lower DHPT; Closed PMV and SCSSV. Spotted 10 bbls MEG + 25 bbls of 10.6 CaCl2 plus 100 bbls of Soap in kill line. Tues - 10/23/18 - Spotted 75 bbls MEG in landing string and bullheaded across tree and SSCSV. Shifted lower IWS closed. Closed KWV; bled off. Bled 1;000 psi off landing string to 8;000 psi. Performed negative test on SCSSV for 30 minutes on chart (Good Test). Closed PMV; bled pressure on landing string to 0 psi. Closed Cetco choke; opened KWV. Applied 100 psi down landing string against PMV. Closed KWV; bled off pressure. Performed negative test on PMV for 15 minutes; recorded on chart (Good Test). IWOCS applied 12;700 psi as recorded @ PTU through CIT1. Tested PSV; PMV; PWV for 15 minutes. Recorded tests via IWOCS @ PTU. Cetco chart PSV (Good Test). Unlatched SSTT; verified unlatch. Sweep stack under UAP with seawater. Spotted 50 bbls soap pill down kill line taking returns up landing string through Cetco choke. Continued sweeping landing string with 50 bbls soap pill. Boosted riser with seawater. POOH with SSTT to RKB; LD same. Wed - 10/24/18 - Unlatch BOP "B". Moved vessel SW to safe zone. ROV installed TA cap on EVDT. Pulled riser to 1070'. Thurs - 10/25/18 - Pull riser to 145' . RD moon pool. Put BOP on Beams @ 10:20 hrs. RD riser running tool. Jetted BOP 3x passes through BOP. Cleared rig floor of riser running equipment. Vessel under way from KC 829 safe zone to location MC 257 safe zone @ 13:00 hours. FINAL REPORT.

05/16/10: Skid BOP to park position. R/D riser handling tools. Begin between well work prior to transit to KC 785.

05/17/10:  Continue with O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785.

05/18/10:  Continue wwith O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785.

05/19/10:  Continue with O/L of work boats with Buckskin equipment. Continue with rig work in preparation for transit to KC 785. Begin transit to KC 785 @ 0130 hrs. Stop @ 1200 hrs to perform black out test and DP testing. Resume transit @ 1600 hrs.

05/20/10: Continue with transit to KC 785. On location KC 785 @ 0430 hrs. Jump ROV and deploy compatts. Position ship and calibrate compatts. Continue with DP acceptance tests.

05/21/10:  Complete DP acceptance tests @ 1030 hrs. Hold pre-job safety meeting and R/U 36" casing running tools. Run 4 jts. 36" casing and LPWHH and land in rotary table. R/D casing handling tools. Run 30" jetting assy inside 36". Make up CADA tools. Install 4" ball valves on LPH; left in open position. RIH with 36" casing and jetting assy on 50# DP to 3841'. 

05/22/10:  Continue RIH w/ 36" casing and tag mud line @ 6686'.  Jet in 36" casing to 6997' (includes RKB elevation of 92').  This section drilled w/ 8.6 PPG seawater.  Maintain 780K while soaking casing.  

Fugro surveyed coordinates for Buckskin KC 785 are as follows:
     Y: 9504321.68   X:1924285.66
     Lat: N 26 11 26.3585"  Lon: W 092 08 02.6535" (NAD 27 - UTM15)

05/23/2010: Continue to allow 36¿ casing to soak. Slack off casing; ROV monitor LPWHH for 15 mins. No subsidence observed. Take 20K overpull and release CADA; POOH until bit clear of LPWHH. Move ship 50¿ off location. Wait on approval from MMS to continue drilling.  

05/24/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.  

05/25/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.  

05/26/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.  

05/27/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.  

05/28/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.  

05/29/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.

05/30/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.

05/31/2010: Continue to wait on approval f/ MMS to continue drilling.

06/01/2010: Decision made to move drillship to SS362 during Drilling Moratorium. P/U compatts and begin move to SS362.

5/16/2011: Arrived on location at Buckskin; KC 785 #1 at 02:00 hrs. Deployed compatts and calibrated. Performed seabed survey and inspected 38" LPWH. Ran 26" BHA and drilled 26" hole riserless to 7;072' MD/TVD with seawater.

5/17/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 8;835' MD/TVD. Started displace hole to 10.0 ppg FWPAD mud (fresh water mud - equivalent of dynamic kill fluid) at 7;400' MD/TVD.

5/18/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 10;030' MD/TVD. Increased MW to 10.5 ppg FWPAD mud at 9;000' MD/TVD and to 11.0 ppg at 9;500' MD/TVD.

5/19/2011: Drilled 26" hole to 10;075' MD/TVD. Displaced hole to 12.0 ppg FWPAD mud and spotted 50 bbls of 16.0 ppg FWPAD mud at TD. POOH 26" BHA and ran 22" casing to 7;463' MD/TVD.

5/20/2011: Ran 22" casing to 10;000' MD/TVD (22" shoe depth). Cemented 22" casing with 9;966 cu.ft. of 14.5 ppg foam Lead and 1;044 cu.ft. of foam Tail. Confirmed cement returns with ROV.

5/21/2011: Continued cementing 22" casing with 651 cu.ft. of 16.9 ppg unfoam Tail slurry. Displace cement with seawater. Check float holding. Release MRLD (mechanical rigid lockdown) and displace 22" casing with 12.0 ppg FWPAD mud. POOH with landing string and inner string. R/U riser handling equipment.

05/22/2011: Re-tested upper; middle and lower VBRs on 4-1/2" drill pipe; 250 psi low; 12000 psi high for 5 min each. Prep BOP to splash; skid BOP under well center. Splash BOP at 23:30 hrs.

05/23/2011: Tested choke and kill lines to 250 psi. Noticed communication issue with high temperature and accumulator sensors on Yellow pod while performing high test on choke and kill lines. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection on Yellow pod; found leak on Blue pod upper shear ram function. Repair SPM valves on Blue pod. At 22:20 hrs.; developed leak on Yellow pod wedge packer.

05/24/2011: Change out shuttle valves and blown packer seals. Test riser connector to 250/7500 psi for 5 min each and choke and kill stabs to 250/11400 psi 5 min each. Function tested upper; middle and lower VBRs and all fail-safe valves on Blue and Yellow pods. Troubleshoot leak on Yellow pod wedge packer and SPM valve. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection stabs. 

05/25/2011: Change out Yellow pod wedge packers and adjusted spacing on retainer plate. Test electrical integrity on Yellow pod (MEG). Yellow pod did not MEG correctly. Remove PBOF cable from RTU to Yellow and Blue wet make/break; drained fluid. Found broken wire and repaired same. Install PBOF. Verify accumulator pressure. Function test shear rams and 2 fail safe valves on Yellow and Blue pods. No loss of accumulator pressure observed.

05/26/2011: Splash BOPs @ 00:30 hrs. Halliburton test choke and kill lines to 250 psi low and 10000 psi high for 5 min each. Good low test. On high test; developed leak and switched pumps and repeated test to get a good high test. Noticed small leak while testing valves in line-up to test tool. Realigned test line and repeated test to get good test. Halliburton tested choke and kill lines to 250/10000 psi for 5 min each with fresh water while running BOP on riser at 868'; 1618' and 2818'.

05/27/2011: Run riser to 4093'. Mid-water bullseye (jt #42 & #43) reading was 3/4 at 160 deg. Halliburton tested choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines for 250/10000 psi for 5 min each using freshwater at 4093' and then again at 5369' and 6438'.  Pick up termination joint from 6438' to 6513'. Pick up telescopic joint and install drape hoses.

05/28/2011: Landed BOPs with a ship heading of 280°. Set 50k down. Subsea latched the wellhead connector with the Blue pod using SEM A with a gallon count of 9.3. Performed 100k overpull test. Transferred weight to the tensioners. Performed slump test. ROV closed blind shear rams. Time to close 4 minutes 49 seconds. ROV skid pump pressure 1700 psi. ROV skid flow rate 8.1 gpm. Halliburton perform BSR; wellhead connector and casing test. 250 for 5 minutes and 2300 psi for 30 minutes with sea water. Good test. 12 bbls to pressure up; bled back 11-1/4 bbls. ROV removed hot stab. Opened BSR from CCU on Blue pod. 42 seconds to open. 39.5 gallons to open. Performed subsea deadman / autoshear procedure from CCU @ 14:20 hrs. Halliburton pressured up to 1000 psi to confirm shears closed @ 15:40 hrs. Good test. Open BSR from CCU Blue pod 41 seconds; 39.4 gallons. Lay down landing joint. Picked up and installed diverter. Took 10k overpull. Lay down running tool. Run hole with BOP test assembly from surface to 619'. Monitor well on trip tank. Well static.

05/29/2011: RIH to 2855' with BOP test tool BHA. TIH to 7864'. Performed diverter function test. Performed accumulator test. Tested BOPs with 8.6 ppg SW to 250/9;400 psi for 5 min. Tested annular to 250/7000 psi for 5 min each. Function test BOPs on Yellow pod from OIM's panel. Flow check well for 10 min on trip tank. Well static. POOH 1500' with test assembly.

05/30/2011: POOH 1510'. Functioned casing and BSR. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 9834'. Obtain annular temperatures with LWD. Wash and ream ratty cement to 9900'. Tag firm cement @ 9900'. Drill firm cement to 9920'. Displace from 8.6 ppg seawater to 9.8 ppg Rheliant SBM. C&C mud taking returns back to active pits. Take slow SPR/SCR.

05/31/2011: Closed and located annular. Take gallon counts to open and close annular. Get choke line friction. Applied 520 psi to casing and held choke drill with crew. Drill cement from 9925' to 9995'. Drill shoe @ 10;000'. Cleaned out rathole and drilled from 10;075' to 10;085'. Flow check; CBU to WH + 500' inside riser with 9.8 ppg SBM. C&C mud to 9.8 ppg; flow check; well static. Perform FIT to 583 psi = 10.9 ppg EMW (11.3 ppg EMW on MWD tool). Continue drilling to 10;186'. Open reamer. Drill to 10;700'. 

06/01/2011: Continued drilling to 11;126'. Repaired cuttings auger in shaker house. Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" to 11;555'.

06/02/2011:  Drill ahead to 11;970'; taking surveys every stand and troubleshoot auger and dryer. Pumped 100 bbls 11.8 ppg sweep. Held pit drill with crew at 10:35 hrs ¿ reaction time 102 seconds; total time to secure well 147 seconds. Monitor well on the trip tank while repairing auger in the shaker house. Continue drilling 12;600'; increase MW to 10.0 ppg at 12;500'. Held pit drill at 19:43 hrs ¿ 108 sec; 153 sec total time.

06/03/2011: Work thru tight spots; troubleshoot mud pumps and TDS. Drill ahead to 13;210'. Weight up to 10.2 ppg. Continue drilling 18-1/8" x 21" hole section to 13;495'.

06/04/2011: Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole to 14;145'. Pump 100 bbls 14 ppg weighted high vis sweep. CBU. Pumped static MW = 10.58 ppg. Weight up active mud system to 10.5 ppg (verbal approval from Mr. David Stanley).

06/05/2011: Spot 40 bbl 16.4 ppg weighted pill on bottom at 14;145' MD/TVD. POOH to 9;196' MD/TVD and perform 7-day BOP function test from driller¿s panel; blue pod; and diverter function test from OIM panel. POOH to 7;122' MD/TVD and retrieve wear sleeve; continue POOH to surface. Function BSR and CSR from driller¿s panel; blue pod. 

06/06/2011: Rig up to run 17-7/8" x 18" casing. Run 1;476' of 17-7/8" 93.5 ppf casing; 2;435' of 17-7/8" 106.3 ppf casing; and 614' of 18" 116 ppf casing. Run 5" inner string and M/U 18" hanger. RIH with casing on landing string to 5;847' MD/TVD; taking mud losses of 15 bbls/stand. Well static on connections. 

06/07/2011: Continue TIH with 17-7/8" x 18" casing on 6-5/8" landing string; taking losses of 30-35 bbls/stand; well static on connections. Land casing on 18" supplemental adaptor at 9;501' MD/TVD; with shoe at 14;026' MD/TVD. Break circulation; no returns. Convert surge tools. 

06/08/2011: Cement 17-7/8" x 18" casing with 663 cu.ft of 14.5 ppg lead cement and 1;213 cu.ft of 16.4 ppg tail cement. Displaced cement with 10.5 ppg SBM and checked floats. Estimated TOC at 11;430' MD/TVD; 1;718 cu.ft cement in annulus; 165 cu.ft in shoe track. Released running tool and set seal assembly; tested seal assembly to 1900 psi with 10.5 ppg SBM for 5 min - good test. POOH with landing string and inner string. Close BSR and conduct 30 min casing and BSR test to 1900 psi with 10.5 ppg SBM. Note: Hanger running tool hung up on slip joint while POOH causing damage to the tool. 

06/09/2011: Mobilize camera to location; close blind shear rams and monitor well on stripping tank. Displaced upper riser to seawater at 200' and RIH with camera to inspect slip joint for damage - no visibility. Displaced seawater to fresh water to improve visibility; with no success. 

06/10/2011: Displaced freshwater out of riser and dropped fluid level to 135 ft. Continued to monitor well on stripping tank. RIH with camera and inspected slip joint inner barrel. No damage noted. RIH with 16.5" x 19" drilling BHA to 7;790' MD/TVD. Spaced out on BOP stack; closed test rams and performed BOP test to 250/5500 psi on rams and 250/5000 psi on annular for 5 min each with 10.5 ppg SBM.
    
06/11/2011: Continued BOP test with choke manifold and floor valves tested to 250/9400 psi for 5 min. Performed diverter function from driller¿s panel and accumulator test from CCU; yellow pod. RIH to 13;623' MD/TVD; spaced out on annular and perform choke drills with crew. RIH to 13;758' MD/TVD and washed and reamed ratty cement to 13;931' MD/TVD. Tagged firm cement at 13;931' MD/TVD and drilled to 13;950' MD/TVD while increasing MW to 10.7 ppg.

Ongoing MWD/LWD and/or Mudlog Operations 06/12/2011: Continued circulating mud system over 10.7 ppg prior to drilling out 18" casing shoe. Took slow circulating rates and choke line frictions; and conducted choke drills with drill crew. Drilled remaining shoe track from 13;950' MD/TVD to 14;007' MD/TVD. Continued drilling cement from 14;010' to 14;047' MD/TVD and then washed and reamed down to 14;145 MD/TVD. Drilled 10' of new formation to 14;155' MD/TVD and circulated cuttings above BOP for LOT. Conducted LOT to 1823 psi with 10.7 ppg SBM (EMW = 13.2 ppg). Pumped up 13.54 ppg EMW with PWD. Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 14;155' to 14;330' MD/TVD.

06/13/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 14;330' to 15;775' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 11.0 ppg SBM at 14;626' MD/TVD and to 11.3 ppg SBM at 15;500' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 60 ft/hr. 

06/14/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 15;775' to 16;975' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight 11.5 ppg at 16;500' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 50 ft/hr.

06/15/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 16;975' to 17;485' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 11.8 ppg SBM at 17;275' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 21 ft/hr.
   
06/16/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 17;485' to section TD at 17;678' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 12.1 ppg SBM at 17;669' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 21 ft/hr. Circulated and conditioned mud for running casing; flushed choke & kill lines; and spotted 55 bbls of 16.4 ppg SBM in the 16-1/2" rathole. POOH from TD to 13;845' MD/TVD and function tested diverter and BOP stack on Yellow Pod from OIM panel. Continued to POOH from 13;845' to 6;096' MD/TVD and function tested BSR on Yellow Pod from OIM panel.
Note: Verbal approval for changing the 16" casing setting depth from 18;400' to +/-17;550' was give by Mr. David LeLeux at 09:35 hrs on 6/16/11.

06/17/2011: Continued to POOH from 6;096' MD/TVD to surface and racked back BHA. Circulated riser through the boost line at 805 gpm to shear mud and remove slugs. Picked up and RIH with Nominal Bore Protector (NBP) running tool and set NBP in wellhead in preparation for wireline VSP run; POOH with the NBP running tool. Rigged up wireline unit and ran in the hole with VSP tools to 2100' MD/TVD.
Note: Modification of Permit to Drill for the alteration of the 16" casing point to 17;521' TVD/MD was approved by Mr. Marty Rinaudo at 12:24 hrs on 6/17/11.
  
06/18/2011: Continued to RIH with VSP wireline log from 2100' to 17;600' MD/TVD; taking down-going checkshots at 8;000'; 12;000' and 16;000' MD/TVD. Begin POOH while acquiring up-going data with 104-level; 50' spaced ZVSP from 17;600' to 12;450' MD/TVD. Continue POOH with up-going checkshots at 500' spacing from 12;500' to 7;000' MD/TVD. Pulled wireline tools to surface and rigged down equipment. Picked up NBP retrieval tool and RIH to retrieve NBP.

06/19/2011: Rigged up to run 16" casing. Held a pre-task safety meeting with crews on picking up and running 16" casing. Begin to run shoe track and 16" casing. At shoe depth of 5;464'; the hole filling the pipe at 17 spm at 180 psi; saw a 50 psi increase in stand pipe pressure. Lined up on boost choke and kill lines. Started boosting riser with 85 spm at 225 psi with 12.1 ppg SBM.

06/20/2011: Circulate 1 riser volume down choke and kill lines with 12.1 ppg mud at 452 gpm w/ 220 psi to improve auto fill flow in the csg. Broke circulation down 16" casing and circulated staging up pumps from 42-84 gpm @ 245 psi. Continued RIH with 16" 97# HPQ-125 SLSF casing from 5;464' to 6;745' and 16.040" 109.61 HPQ-125 SLSF from 6;745' to 10;609'. Rig down Frank's flow back tool and casing elevators. Rig up Frank's drill pipe elevators. Clean rig floor.

06/21/2011: P/U and M/U Dril-Quip 16" casing hanger joint. RIH with 16" casing on 6-5/8" 47# DP from 10;652' to 13;912'. Continued RIH with 16" casing string on 50# drill pipe from 13;913' to 17;456'. Picked up and RIH with 2 singles of 50# drill pipe. Observed decrease in weight as hanger landed out in 16" SA at 6;901'. Continued slacking off and observed hanger pins shear out. Made up Blackhawk cement head and continued slacking off to 342 klbs. Circulate down cement head with rig pumps. Test cement lines; pump 150 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer. Mixed and pumped 5 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; dropped bottom dart; continue to pump 110 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; consisting of yield of 1.42 cubic feet. Mixed and pumped 191 bbls of 16.6 ppg tail cement at 5 bpm. Yield 1.05 cubic feet per sack. Dropped top dart and pump 20 bbls of tail cement follow by 20 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer.  Displace cement with rig pumps.

06/22/2011: Continued pumping and bumped the plug with 1250 psi; 2384 bbls pumped. Increased pressure to 2000 psi and held for 10 mins. Bled back 8 bbls and observed no reduction in flow back. Floats did not hold. Bullheaded back 8 bbls; locked in 1800 psi on 16" casing string and commenced waiting on cement for 12 hours. Bled back 11 bbls. Set seal assembly. Test seal assembly to 5000 psi for 10 minutes. Circulate down the landing cement. Rig down cement head. Trip running tool and landing string out of the hole.

06/23/2011: Continue to pull out of the hole with CHSART and landing string.  Functioned blind/casing shear rams on Blue pod from the Driller's panel. Slip and cut drill line. Closed the blind shear rams on the Yellow pod from the OIM's panel and pressure tested the 16" casing to 230 psi low; 3300 psi high for 30 minutes and the blind shear rams to 230 psi low 5 mins; 3300 psi high 5 mins. ROV close PSV & ASV on the EVDT.  Tested connector to 1;000 psi / 5 mins.  Good test. Tested lower BSR's against closed PSV & ASV on the EVDT to 13;500 psi / 5 mins.  Tested the THD connector in conjunction.  Functioned diverter from primary control station. PU SSTT and RIH to 2;400'.  

Fri - 10/19/18 - Continued to RIH with SSTT. Landed SSTT in top of tree @ 6;705'. 
Displaced choke and kill lines from seawater to 13.0 ppg CaBr2.  Performed VX 
gasket test via IWOCS; apply 13;500 psi down TST line and charted for 15mins.  
Performed Tree Gallery test via ROV to 13;500 psi and charted for 5min.  Tested surface equipment to 10;700 psi for 5 min on chart. Aligned surface tree and manifolds for opening SCSSV. Pressured up 3;800 psi and opened SCSSV.   Opened Upper IWS; pressured up on landing string to 3500 psi ( 18;960 psi DH) and closed upper IWS.
Equalize pressure across Lower IWS sleeve; opened same. Pressured up on tubing to shear X-RFV; observed 25;476 psi on Lower IWS & 19;450 psi on Upper IWS when AFV shifted.  Handed over well to Cetco @ 02:30 hrs. Began flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. Initial UW4 Sand Reading @ 0300 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 18;873 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 220°F; Annulus PSI 6;370; Choke Pressure 3;488 PSI on 14/64 Choke; Gas Rate 0 MMscfd; Oil Rate 0 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day.
 
Sat - 10/20/18 - Continued flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. 
Reading @ 0500 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 17;221 psi; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;704; Choke Pressure 7;295.48 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .467 MMscfd; Oil Rate 6;971 bbl/day; Water Rate 116.7 bbl/day.

Sun - 10/21/18 - Continued well flow operations.  Shut in lower zone on Cetco choke @ 06:30 hrs.  Final Reading for UW4 sand @ 0600 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 17;202 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;727; Choke Pressure 7;312.92 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .459 MMscfd; Oil Rate 7;014.4 bbl/day; Water Rate 58.2 bbl/day.  Equalized pressure in tubing; shifted upper IWS sleeve. Closed KWV; bled pressure to 0 psi. Shifted upper sleeve.  Turned well over to Cetco; flowed upper zone as per LLOG procedure. Initial Reading for upper sands @ 1000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 18;666 psi; Down Hole Temperature 223°F; Annulus psi 7;126; Choke Pressure 8;232.67 psi on 12/64 Choke; Gas Rate .19 MMscfd; Oil Rate 3;074.50 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day.

Mon - 10/22/18 - Continued well flow operations by flowingd upper zone as per LLOG procedure.  Shut well in @ 00:20 hrs @ Cetco Choke.  Closed upper IWS sleeve. Final Reading for upper sands @ 0000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 19;091 psi; Down Hole Temperature 226°F; Annulus psi 7;537; Choke Pressure 9;030.26 psi on 22/64 Choke; Gas Rate .803 MMscfd; Oil Rate 9;322.1 bbl/day; Water Rate 504.9 bbl/day. Equalized pressure between Common DHPT and Lower DHPT; Closed PMV and SCSSV. Spotted 10 bbls MEG + 25 bbls of 10.6 CaCl2 plus 100 bbls of Soap in kill line.  

Tues - 10/23/18 - Spotted 75 bbls MEG in landing string and bullheaded across tree and SSCSV.  Shifted lower IWS closed.  Closed KWV; bled off. Bled 1;000 psi off landing string to 8;000 psi. Performed negative test on SCSSV for 30 minutes on chart (Good Test). Closed PMV; bled pressure on landing string to 0 psi. Closed Cetco choke; opened KWV. Applied 100 psi down landing string against PMV. Closed KWV; bled off 
pressure. Performed negative test on PMV for 15 minutes; recorded on chart (Good Test).  IWOCS applied 12;700 psi as recorded @ PTU through CIT1. Tested PSV; PMV; PWV for 15 minutes. Recorded tests via IWOCS @ PTU. Cetco chart PSV (Good Test).  Unlatched SSTT; verified unlatch. Sweep stack under UAP with seawater. Spotted 50 bbls soap pill down kill line taking returns up landing string through Cetco choke. Continued sweeping landing string with 50 bbls soap pill.   Boosted riser with seawater.  POOH with SSTT to RKB; LD same. 

Wed - 10/24/18 - Unlatch BOP "B".  Moved vessel SW to safe zone. ROV installed TA cap on EVDT.  Pulled riser to 1070'.  

Thurs - 10/25/18 - Pull riser to 145' . RD moon pool. Put BOP on Beams @ 10:20 hrs.
RD riser running tool.  Jetted BOP 3x passes through BOP. Cleared rig floor of riser running equipment. Vessel under way from KC 829 safe zone to location MC 257 safe zone @ 13:00 hours.  FINAL REPORT.

Wed - 5-22-19 - Bullheaded methanol to balance pressure across the lower sleeve.  Opened lower sliding sleeve.

Thurs - 5-23-19 - Displaced chemical lines.

Fri - 5-24-19 - Displaced chemical lines. Downhole commingling approval received (attached).

"},{"   ":3,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-05-16","TEXT_REMARK":"5/16/2011: Arrived on location at Buckskin; KC 785 #1 at 02:00 hrs. Deployed compatts and calibrated. 5/20/2011: Ran 22" casing to 10;000' MD/TVD (22" shoe depth). Cemented 22" casing with 9;966 cu.ft. of 14.5 ppg foam Lead and 1;044 cu.ft. of foam Tail. Confirmed cement returns with ROV.

5/21/2011: Continued cementing 22" casing with 651 cu.ft. of 16.9 ppg unfoam Tail slurry. Displace cement with seawater. Check float holding. Release MRLD (mechanical rigid lockdown) and displace 22" casing with 12.0 ppg FWPAD mud. POOH with landing string and inner string. R/U riser handling equipment.
"},{"   ":4,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-05-22","TEXT_REMARK":"05/22/2011: Re-tested upper; middle and lower VBRs on 4-1/2" drill pipe; 250 psi low; 12000 psi high for 5 min each. Prep BOP to splash; skid BOP under well center. Splash BOP at 23:30 hrs.

05/23/2011: Tested choke and kill lines to 250 psi. Noticed communication issue with high temperature and accumulator sensors on Yellow pod while performing high test on choke and kill lines. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection on Yellow pod; found leak on Blue pod upper shear ram function. Repair SPM valves on Blue pod. At 22:20 hrs.; developed leak on Yellow pod wedge packer.

05/24/2011: Change out shuttle valves and blown packer seals. Test riser connector to 250/7500 psi for 5 min each and choke and kill stabs to 250/11400 psi 5 min each. Function tested upper; middle and lower VBRs and all fail-safe valves on Blue and Yellow pods. Troubleshoot leak on Yellow pod wedge packer and SPM valve. Troubleshoot wet-mate connection stabs. 

05/25/2011: Change out Yellow pod wedge packers and adjusted spacing on retainer plate. Test electrical integrity on Yellow pod (MEG). Yellow pod did not MEG correctly. Remove PBOF cable from RTU to Yellow and Blue wet make/break; drained fluid. Found broken wire and repaired same. Install PBOF. Verify accumulator pressure. Function test shear rams and 2 fail safe valves on Yellow and Blue pods. No loss of accumulator pressure observed.

05/26/2011: Splash BOPs @ 00:30 hrs. Halliburton test choke and kill lines to 250 psi low and 10000 psi high for 5 min each. Good low test. On high test; developed leak and switched pumps and repeated test to get a good high test. Noticed small leak while testing valves in line-up to test tool. Realigned test line and repeated test to get good test. Halliburton tested choke and kill lines to 250/10000 psi for 5 min each with fresh water while running BOP on riser at 868'; 1618' and 2818'.

05/27/2011: Run riser to 4093'. Mid-water bullseye (jt #42 & #43) reading was 3/4 at 160 deg. Halliburton tested choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines for 250/10000 psi for 5 min each using freshwater at 4093' and then again at 5369' and 6438'.  Pick up termination joint from 6438' to 6513'. Pick up telescopic joint and install drape hoses.

05/28/2011: Landed BOPs with a ship heading of 280°. Set 50k down. Subsea latched the wellhead connector with the Blue pod using SEM A with a gallon count of 9.3. Performed 100k overpull test. Transferred weight to the tensioners. Performed slump test. ROV closed blind shear rams. Time to close 4 minutes 49 seconds. ROV skid pump pressure 1700 psi. ROV skid flow rate 8.1 gpm. Halliburton perform BSR; wellhead connector and casing test. 250 for 5 minutes and 2300 psi for 30 minutes with sea water. Good test. 12 bbls to pressure up; bled back 11-1/4 bbls. ROV removed hot stab. Opened BSR from CCU on Blue pod. 42 seconds to open. 39.5 gallons to open. Performed subsea deadman / autoshear procedure from CCU @ 14:20 hrs. Halliburton pressured up to 1000 psi to confirm shears closed @ 15:40 hrs. Good test. Open BSR from CCU Blue pod 41 seconds; 39.4 gallons. Lay down landing joint. Picked up and installed diverter. Took 10k overpull. Lay down running tool. Run hole with BOP test assembly from surface to 619'. Monitor well on trip tank. Well static.
"},{"   ":5,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-05-29","TEXT_REMARK":"05/29/2011: RIH to 2855' with BOP test tool BHA. TIH to 7864'. Performed diverter function test. Performed accumulator test. Tested BOPs with 8.6 ppg SW to 250/9;400 psi for 5 min. Tested annular to 250/7000 psi for 5 min each. Function test BOPs on Yellow pod from OIM's panel. Flow check well for 10 min on trip tank. Well static. POOH 1500' with test assembly.

05/30/2011: POOH 1510'. Functioned casing and BSR. TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 9834'. Obtain annular temperatures with LWD. Wash and ream ratty cement to 9900'. Tag firm cement @ 9900'. Drill firm cement to 9920'. Displace from 8.6 ppg seawater to 9.8 ppg Rheliant SBM. C&C mud taking returns back to active pits. Take slow SPR/SCR.

05/31/2011: Closed and located annular. Take gallon counts to open and close annular. Get choke line friction. Applied 520 psi to casing and held choke drill with crew. Drill cement from 9925' to 9995'. Drill shoe @ 10;000'. Cleaned out rathole and drilled from 10;075' to 10;085'. Flow check; CBU to WH + 500' inside riser with 9.8 ppg SBM. C&C mud to 9.8 ppg; flow check; well static. Perform FIT to 583 psi = 10.9 ppg EMW (11.3 ppg EMW on MWD tool). Continue drilling to 10;186'. Open reamer. Drill to 10;700'. 

06/01/2011: Continued drilling to 11;126'. Repaired cuttings auger in shaker house. Drilled 18-1/8" x 21" to 11;555'.

06/02/2011:  Drill ahead to 11;970'; taking surveys every stand and troubleshoot auger and dryer. Pumped 100 bbls 11.8 ppg sweep. Held pit drill with crew at 10:35 hrs ¿ reaction time 102 seconds; total time to secure well 147 seconds. Monitor well on the trip tank while repairing auger in the shaker house. Continue drilling 12;600'; increase MW to 10.0 ppg at 12;500'. Held pit drill at 19:43 hrs ¿ 108 sec; 153 sec total time.

06/03/2011: Work thru tight spots; troubleshoot mud pumps and TDS. Drill ahead to 13;210'. Weight up to 10.2 ppg. Continue drilling 18-1/8" x 21" hole section to 13;495'.

06/04/2011: Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole to 14;145'. Pump 100 bbls 14 ppg weighted high vis sweep. CBU. Pumped static MW = 10.58 ppg. Weight up active mud system to 10.5 ppg (verbal approval from Mr. David Stanley).
"},{"   ":6,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-06-05","TEXT_REMARK":"06/05/2011: Spot 40 bbl 16.4 ppg weighted pill on bottom at 14;145' MD/TVD. POOH to 9;196' MD/TVD and perform 7-day BOP function test from driller¿s panel; blue pod; and diverter function test from OIM panel. POOH to 7;122' MD/TVD and retrieve wear sleeve; continue POOH to surface. Function BSR and CSR from driller¿s panel; blue pod. 

06/06/2011: Rig up to run 17-7/8" x 18" casing. Run 1;476' of 17-7/8" 93.5 ppf casing; 2;435' of 17-7/8" 106.3 ppf casing; and 614' of 18" 116 ppf casing. Run 5" inner string and M/U 18" hanger. 06/08/2011: Cement 17-7/8" x 18" casing with 663 cu.ft of 14.5 ppg lead cement and 1;213 cu.ft of 16.4 ppg tail cement. Displaced cement with 10.5 ppg SBM and checked floats. Close BSR and conduct 30 min casing and BSR test to 1900 psi with 10.5 ppg SBM. Note: Hanger running tool hung up on slip joint while POOH causing damage to the tool. 

06/09/2011: Mobilize camera to location; close blind shear rams and monitor well on stripping tank. Displaced upper riser to seawater at 200' and RIH with camera to inspect slip joint for damage - no visibility. Displaced seawater to fresh water to improve visibility; with no success.

06/11/2011: Continued BOP test with choke manifold and floor valves tested to 250/9400 psi for 5 min. Performed diverter function from driller¿s panel and accumulator test from CCU; yellow pod. RIH to 13;623' MD/TVD; spaced out on annular and perform choke drills with crew. RIH to 13;758' MD/TVD and washed and reamed ratty cement to 13;931' MD/TVD. Tagged firm cement at 13;931' MD/TVD and drilled to 13;950' MD/TVD while increasing MW to 10.7 ppg.
"},{"   ":7,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-06-12","TEXT_REMARK":"Ongoing MWD/LWD and/or Mudlog Operations 06/12/2011: Continued circulating mud system over 10.7 ppg prior to drilling out 18" casing shoe. 06/14/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 15;775' to 16;975' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight 11.5 ppg at 16;500' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 50 ft/hr.

06/15/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 16;975' to 17;485' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Increased mud weight to 11.8 ppg SBM at 17;275' MD/TVD. Average ROP = 21 ft/hr.
   
06/16/2011: Drilled ahead with 16-1/2" x 19" BHA from 17;485' to section TD at 17;678' MD/TVD; taking surveys every stand and pumping weighted sweeps every third stand. Circulated and conditioned mud for running casing; flushed choke & kill lines; and spotted 55 bbls of 16.4 ppg SBM in the 16-1/2" rathole. POOH from TD to 13;845' MD/TVD and function tested diverter and BOP stack on Yellow Pod from OIM panel. Note: Verbal approval for changing the 16" casing setting depth from 18;400' to +/-17;550' was give by Mr. David LeLeux at 09:35 hrs on 6/16/11.

Note: Modification of Permit to Drill for the alteration of the 16" casing point to 17;521' TVD/MD was approved by Mr. Marty Rinaudo at 12:24 hrs on 6/17/11.

Begin POOH while acquiring up-going data with 104-level; 50' spaced ZVSP from 17;600' to 12;450' MD/TVD. Continue POOH with up-going checkshots at 500' spacing from 12;500' to 7;000' MD/TVD. Pulled wireline tools to surface and rigged down equipment. Picked up NBP retrieval tool and RIH to retrieve NBP.
"},{"   ":8,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-06-19","TEXT_REMARK":"06/19/2011: Rigged up to run 16" casing. Held a pre-task safety meeting with crews on picking up and running 16" casing. Begin to run shoe track and 16" casing. Started boosting riser with 85 spm at 225 psi with 12.1 ppg SBM.

06/20/2011: Circulate 1 riser volume down choke and kill lines with 12.1 ppg mud at 452 gpm w/ 220 psi to improve auto fill flow in the csg. Broke circulation down 16" casing and circulated staging up pumps from 42-84 gpm @ 245 psi. Continued RIH with 16" 97# HPQ-125 SLSF casing from 5;464' to 6;745' and 16.040" 109.61 HPQ-125 SLSF from 6;745' to 10;609'. Rig down Frank's flow back tool and casing elevators. Rig up Frank's drill pipe elevators. Clean rig floor.

06/21/2011: P/U and M/U Dril-Quip 16" casing hanger joint. RIH with 16" casing on 6-5/8" 47# DP from 10;652' to 13;912'. Continued RIH with 16" casing string on 50# drill pipe from 13;913' to 17;456'. Picked up and RIH with 2 singles of 50# drill pipe. Observed decrease in weight as hanger landed out in 16" SA at 6;901'. Continued slacking off and observed hanger pins shear out. Made up Blackhawk cement head and continued slacking off to 342 klbs. Circulate down cement head with rig pumps. Test cement lines; pump 150 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer. Mixed and pumped 5 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; dropped bottom dart; continue to pump 110 bbls of 14.5 ppg lead cement; consisting of yield of 1.42 cubic feet. Mixed and pumped 191 bbls of 16.6 ppg tail cement at 5 bpm. Yield 1.05 cubic feet per sack. Dropped top dart and pump 20 bbls of tail cement follow by 20 bbls of 13.5 ppg tuned spacer.  Displace cement with rig pumps.

06/22/2011: Continued pumping and bumped the plug with 1250 psi; 2384 bbls pumped. Increased pressure to 2000 psi and held for 10 mins. Bled back 8 bbls and observed no reduction in flow back. Floats did not hold. Bullheaded back 8 bbls; locked in 1800 psi on 16" casing string and commenced waiting on cement for 12 hours. Bled back 11 bbls. Set seal assembly. Test seal assembly to 5000 psi for 10 minutes. Circulate down the landing cement. Rig down cement head. Trip running tool and landing string out of the hole.

06/23/2011: Continue to pull out of the hole with CHSART and landing string.  Functioned blind/casing shear rams on Blue pod from the Driller's panel. Slip and cut drill line. Closed the blind shear rams on the Yellow pod from the OIM's panel and pressure tested the 16" casing to 230 psi low; 3300 psi high for 30 minutes and the blind shear rams to 230 psi low 5 mins; 3300 psi high 5 mins. HES pumped 26.3 bbls and bled back 26.3 bbls of 12.1 ppg SBM during the pressure test. Pick up 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" rotary steerable BHA and trip into the hole. Land out wear sleeve. Held a well control drill while tripping 70 second reaction time. Function tested diverter and BOP stack on Yellow pod from Driller's panel. Continued trip in the hole.
    
06/24/2011: Continued to trip in the hole with up 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" rotary steerable BHA while testing choke manifold to 250/3600 psi for 5 minutes with 12.1 ppg SBM. At 16;940'; perform Accumulator test. Perform Annular pressure test of 250/5100 and BOP pressure test 250/5500 psi with a 12.1 ppg SBM on the Blue pod from the OIM panel. Perform choke surface manifold equipment test 250/9500 psi. Rotate and wash down; tag firm cement at 17;296'. Take SPR and CLF. 

06/25/2011: Performed Well Control choke drills with TOI crews. Displace mud from 12.1 ppg to 12.3 ppg while drilling firm cement in shoe track from 17;296' to 17;513'. Drill the top and bottom float collar and shoe. Washed and ream the rathole. Drilled 10' feet of new formation to 17.678'. Circulated cuttings above the stack.  Perform a LOT with 12.3 ppg SBM. After pumping 11.5 bbls; the pressure broke over at 1119 psi (EMW 13.52 ppg). Bled back 8.5 bbls. Lost 3 bbls to the formation. Opened annular and circulated up max downhole pressure of 13.82 ppg. Continue drilling ahead from 17;688' to 17;800'.
"},{"   ":9,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-06-26","TEXT_REMARK":"06/26/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole with rotary steerable assembly from 17;800' to 18;007'

06/27/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole with rotary steerable assembly from 18;007' to 18;104'.  

06/28/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;104' to 18;194'.

06/29/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;194' to 18;304'.

06/30/2011: Drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 18;304' to 18;324'. Took final survey with MWD at 18;320'. Flow checked well at 18;324'. Gained 0.7 bbls in 12 minutes; last 3 minutes static. Flow checked and confirmed well static. Pumped slug and POOH from 17;523' to 9;051'. POOH with BHA from 993' to surface; R/B same.  

07/01/2011: Performed function test on Blind and Casing Shear Rams from OIM's panel on Blue pod. Functioned tested Upper and Lower shear rams from OIM's panel on Blue pod. Upper shear rams: 37 sec/43.2 gal to close; 35 sec/39.7 gal to open. Lower shear rams: 39 sec/42.8 gal to close; 38 sec/39.9 gal to open.
