"},{"   ":10,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-07-03","TEXT_REMARK":"07/03/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 18;492' to 18;619'. Entered salt formation at 18;585'. Pulled back to 18;580' and flow checked. Well static. Worked pipe through TOS at 18;585' to 18;619' with no drag or filled observed. Simulated making a connection at 18;600' (well static). Continued to drill from 18;619' to 18;873'. Pumped weighted sweep and flushed choke and kill lines with 12.5 ppg SBM. 

07/04/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 18;873' to 19;074'. Weighted up active system to 12.8 ppg SBM; while rotating and reciprocating pipe. Boost riser. Flushed choke and kill lines with 12.8 ppg SBM. Worked pipe to check hole conditions without pumps and rotary. Simulated connection for 10 minutes while flow checking. Well static. Worked pipe to check hole conditions and took SCRs at 19;074' with 12.8 ppg SBM. Cycled pumps to turn on and confirm MWD and complete connection. Continue to drill 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 19;074' to 19;522'. 

07/05/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 19;522' to 19;705'. Encountered tight spots and worked string while raising mud weight from 12.8 ppg to 12.9 ppg. Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 19;705' to 20;212'. Encountered tight hole and had to work and jar string free. Increased mud weight from 12.9 ppg to 13.1 ppg and worked string free. Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole from 20;212' to 20;260'. NOTE: Received a verbal approval to increase MW to 13.1 ppg to continue to drill.

07/06/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 20;260' to 20;325'. Observed change in drilling parameters at 20;313'. Commenced salt exit strategy. Continued to drill ahead in 15' increments down to 20;415'. Picked back up into the salt to flow check after each 15'. Pumped 80 bbls 15.1 ppg 125 Vis sweep at 20;415'. Drilled ahead while circulating out 15.1 ppg sweep to 20;433'. Static flow check for 10 mins at 20;433'. Drilled ahead 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" section to 21;011'.

07/07/2011: Drilled 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 21;011' to 21'400'. Circulated 15.1 ppg sweep around at TD. Static flow check and then pulled out of hole to 20;085'. Hole not taking correct displacement. Wash back to bottom; and monitor well on connections.

07/08/2011: Pumped out of hole from 21;400' to 21;227' with 800 gpm. Shut well in when bottoms up was 1;000' below the wellhead; circulated out on the choke. Ran back in hole to bottom; 21;400'; and increased mud weight from 13.1 ppg to 13.2 ppg. Spotting 16.4 ppg pill on bottom and pumped out of hole from 21;400' to 19;967' with 700 gpm and 2;500 psi standpipe pressure. NOTE: Received a verbal approval for a 24 hr. extension on BOP test.

07/09/2011: Continued to pump out of hole from 19;967' to 19;335'. Performed static flow check. Pulled out of hole from 19;335' to 17;376'. Static flow check back inside the 16" casing shoe. Continued to POOH to 7;025' while testing BOP's equipment. Opened the PBL sub and washed the 14" hanger; wellhead and stack. Circulated a sweep around via the boost line. POOH to surface and handled BHA. RIH with BOP test tool.
"},{"   ":11,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-07-10","TEXT_REMARK":"07/10/2011:  Continue RIH with BOP test tool to 8;337'. Landed test tool in the wellhead and set 70k down to shear pin. Tested BOP from Driller's panel on Yellow Pod with 13.2 ppg SBM on 6-5/8" 47# drill pipe. Tested annular and inner bleed 250/5000 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested annular and outer bleed 250/5000 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested UVBRs; UIK; and LIK 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested UVBRs; UOK and LOK 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested LVBRs 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested from Driller's panel on Yellow Pod with 13.2 ppg SBM on 47# drill pipe. Test MVBRs and LIC to 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Test MVBRs and LOC to 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Test MVBRs and bottom of CMV #5 to 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Test annular and UIC to 250/5000 psi for 5 minutes each. Test annular and UOC to 250/5000 psi for 5 minutes each. Test UVBRs and bottom of CMV #1 to 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Test Upper IBOP to 250/9500 psi for 5 minutes each. Test Lower IBOP to 250/9500 psi for 5 minutes each. Test Kelly hose; swivel packing and #2 stand pipe crown valve to 250/7000 psi for 5 minutes each. Function test BOPs from OIM's panel on Blue Pod. Function test diverter from OIM's panel.

07/11/2011: Rigged down cement lines; chick sans; unseated test plug. Flow check well for 5 minutes on trip tank. The well is static. Pulled out of the hole from 8;387' to surface. Monitored well on trip tank while changing bushings. Functioned the upper and lower blind shear rams from the Driller's panel using the Blue Pod. Slip and cut drilling line. Boosted 1 riser volume at 750 GPMs with 2700 psi; then start running casing to 4;914'. 

07/12/2011: Continue picking up and go in the hole with 13-3/4"; 98.58#; HP Q-125; SLSF casing from 4;914' to 7;176'. Pick up crossover joint (13-3/4" x 13-5/8"). Picked up and went in the hole with 13-5/8"; 88.20#; HP Q-125; SLSF casing from 7;176' to 11;600'.

07/13/2011: Continue to run in the hole with 13-5/8" and 14" casing to 14;533'. M/U 13-5/8" hanger stand and run in the hole from 14;533' to 14;788' with 6-5/8" 50# landing string. Rabbit each stand with 3" drift then continued running in the hole with casing to 19;185'.

07/14/2011: Continue tripping in the hole from 19;185' to 21;222' and land 13-5/8" casing hanger. Pumped at 8 bpm to convert floats with no returns. Circulated at 4 bpm while holding pre-job safety meeting for cement job. Pumped a total of 190 bbls; broke circulation. Pumped 5 bbls of 15.0 ppg Tuned Spacer III and tested lines to 5000 psi. Pumped 135 bbls of 15.0 ppg Tuned Spacer III at 5 bpm. HES mix and pumped 201 bbls (1128 cubic feet) of 16.4 cement using 1036 sacks of Class H. Pump 15 bbls of 15.0 ppg Tuned spacer III behind and continue displace cement. Did not bump and float held. Slacked off to 398k/60k down on CHSART; rotate 5-1/2 turns to the right to release running tool from seal assembly. Observed 10" drop in drill string. Test line to 3;500 psi. Close MVBRs (20.3 gal); Halliburton pressure up to 3;500 psi to energize seal assembly and held for 1 minute. Continued staging up test pressure to 10;000 psi and held for 5 minutes. Release running tool. Picked up 5' and circulate @ 1;000 psi for 2 minutes to wash seal assembly. Slack off 70k down on running tool. Close MVBRs and retested seal assembly to 10;000 psi. Pull out of hole with 2 stands from 6;678' to 6;412' with CHSART. Flushed choke and kill lines with 13.2 ppg sbm. Flow check well for 5 min; continue POOH.
	
07/15/2011: Continued pulling out of the hole from 4;514' to 2;616' with CHSART. Removed blown hydraulic service loop from the FWD block. Continue pulling out of hole from 1;352' to surface with CHSART. Close shear rams. Test casing to 250 psi low for 5 minutes and 5;600 psi high for 30 minutes with 13.2 ppg sbm. Test upper shear rams to 250/5;600 psi for 5 minutes each. 

07/16/2011: Subsea function tested the lower shear rams from the Driller's panel using the Yellow Pod. Subsea functioned both shear rams from the OIM's panel using the Blue Pod. Continue going in the hole from 2;100' to 6;966" with wear sleeve assy. Land wear sleeve in wellhead. Set 20k down and closed annular. Pressured up to 2500 psi for 1 minute. Open annular. Took 30k overpull to shear out. Set 20k back down and picked up again with no overpull. Tested the choke manifold to 250/9;500 for 5 minutes each. Tested the Buffer side to 250/3;500 for 5 minutes each. Pull out of the hole from 6;966' to 1;613' with wear sleeve running tool. Tested the choke manifold to 250/9;500 for 5 minutes each. Tested the Buffer side to 250/3;500 for 5 minutes each. All tested with 13.2 ppg sbm. Continued pulling out of the hole from 288 to surface. Tripped in the hole with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly to 20;003'. Subsea perform accumulator draw down test. Tested BOPs. Testing from Driller's panel on Blue Pod with 13.2 ppg SBM on 6-5/8" 34 ppf drill pipe. Tested annular and inner bleed to 250/5;000 psi for 5 minutes each.

"},{"   ":12,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-07-17","TEXT_REMARK":"No Wireline Logs Run 07/17/2011: Continue to assist Subsea and Halliburton with testing the BOPs from the Driller's panel on Blue Pod with 13.2 ppg SBM on 6-5/8"; 34# DP. Tested annular and outer bleed valve 250/5000 for 5 mins each. ROV closed upper variable bore rams with the Hot Stab. Tested upper variable bore rams; upper inner kill; and lower inner kill to 250/5700 for 5 mins each. Tested upper variable bore rams; upper outer kill; lower outer kill to 250/5700 for 5 mins each. Tested upper variable bore rams and bottom of choke manifold valve #1 to 250/5700 for 5 minutes each. Tested lower variable bore rams to 250/5700 for 5 mins each. Tested middle variable bore rams and lower inner choke to 250/5700 for 5 minutes each. Tested middle variable bore rams and lower outer choke to 250/5700 for 5 mins each. Tested middle variable bore rams and choke manifold valve #5 to 250/5700 for 5 mins each. Tested annular and upper inner choke to 250/5000 for 5 mins each. Tested annular and upper outer choke to 250/5000 for 5 mins each. Subsea function tested the BOPs from the OIM's panel on Yellow Pod. Continue assisting Subsea and Halliburton with BOP testing form Driller's panel on Yellow Pod with 13.2 ppg sbm. Test lower IBOP to 250/9500 psi for 5/5 min ea. Test upper IBOP to 250/9500 psi for 5/5 min ea. Test Kelly hose; swivel packing and #2 standpipe valve to 250/7000 psi for 5/5 min ea. Function diverter from Driller's panel. Run in hole with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly from 20;003' to 20;697'. Drilling cement from 20;969' to 20;997'.

07/18/2011: Continue drilling cement; float equipment and 10' new formation from 21;400' to 21;410'. Perform LOT to 1696 psi with 13.2 ppg SBM for EMW 14.7 ppg. Drill ahead to 21;612'.

07/19/2011: Drilling ahead with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section from 21;612' to 22;600'. Raised MW from 13.4 to 13.6 ppg. Continue to drill from 22;600' to 22;707'.

07/20/2011: Drilling ahead with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section from 22;707' T/24;072'. Raised MW from 13.6 to 13.8.  

07/21/2011: Drilling 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section from 24;072' to 24;600'. Weight up mud system to 13.9 ppg @ 24;200'. Continue drilling from 24;600' to 25;219'. Held well control drill while drilling; 141 seconds reaction time; 60 seconds secure time.

07/22/2011: Continue drilling 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole from 25;219' to 25;254' (Section TD). Weighted up active system to 14.2 ppg SBM. Circulated weighted and LCM sweeps out of hole with 14.2 ppg SBM. Flushed choke and kill lines with 14.2 ppg SBM. Flow checked well at 25;220' for 5 min. Well static. Pull out of hole from 25;254' to 25;074'. Flow checked well at 25;074' for 5 min. Well static. Continued pulling out of hole from 25;074' to 15;090'. 

07/23/2011: Continue pulling out of the hole with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly to 9;040'. Function tested the BOP from the Driller's panel on the Blue Pod. Wash the BOP stack. Performed diverter function test from OIM's panel. Continue pulling BHA to surface. Functioned the upper and lower shear rams from the OIM's panel using the Yellow Pod. Slip and cut 119' of drill line. Monitor well on trip tank. Well static. RIH with 11-7/8" (71.8 ppf) casing from surface to 740' (torque to 40k; record same). Monitored torque on every connection for movement on stands 5; 6; and 7 (no movement).
"},{"   ":13,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-07-24","TEXT_REMARK":"07/24/2011: RIH from 1;186' to 4;197' with HPQ-125 casing; torque to 40K. P/U Halliburton Versa-Flex 11-7/8" casing hanger and made up to casing and RIH with same from 4;197' to 4;229'. RIH with 6-5/8" landing string from 4;229' to 19;272'. Drifted drill pipe with 3" rabbit.  

07/25/2011: RIH with landing string from 19;272' to 25;082'. R/U CMT head and control lines. Perform step rate circ test: 1 bpm to 4 bpm. Convert floats. Circulate & Condition mud. Halliburton pressure tested lines to 6500 psi in preparation for cement operation. Mixed and pumped 115 bbls of 15.4 Spacer @ 4 bpm with 900 psi. Halliburton mixed 16.6 ppg Class "H" cement and pumped 144 bbls @ 4 bpm. Displace with 15 bbls of 15.4 ppg Tuned Spacer. Swap over to rig pumps and displace with 14.2 ppg SBM at 4 bpm. Bump plugs @ 17:30 hrs with 2000 psi. Bleed back 7.5 bbls and observe floats holding. Pull Versa-Flex liner running tool out of liner with 65k snap-out. Circulate 1-1/2 times drill string volume.  

07/26/2011: Pull out of hole from 20;540' to 6;888'. Flow check well for 10 mins.; well static. Continue pulling out of hole from 6;888' to surface. P/U and TIH with 10-5/8" drilling assembly to 6;111'. Performed casing pressure test. Tested 11-7/8" casing to 2300 psi for 30 minutes. Tested blind shear rams to 250/2300 for 5 minutes. All tests were made with 14.2 SBM. Tested from the Driller's panel using the Blue Pod. Subsea function tested BSRs from OIM's Panel on Yellow Pod. Continue tripping in the hole from 6;111' to 7;587' running BHA through BOPs. Rig preparing for possible displacement due to development of storm.    

07/27/2011: Waiting on Tropical Disturbance #20. Note: At 16:00 hrs on 07/27/11; Tropical Disturbance #20 became Tropical Storm Don. BOP inspection performed by ROV. RIH from 7;587' to 12;771' with 10-5/8" drilling assembly and EDPHOT tools. Space-out in hang-off position and waited on orders to set Emergency Drill Pipe Hang Off Tool (EDPHOT) tool. Monitor well on trip tank. Well static. Secured rig floor for weather. PM's and housekeeping. TIH from 12;771' to 12;921' (bit depth). Land EDPHOT in wellhead at 6;671'. Pump down the drill pipe and converted the float. Line up on seawater and displace surface equipment with seawater. Displace boost line; kill line and choke line with seawater. Close middle VBRs. Perform pressure test with 8.6 ppg seawater. Pressure up to 1000 psi and held for 5 mins. Disconnected EDHOT. Note: MVBR gallon count = 41.6.

07/28/2011: Closed upper blind shear rams and put upper shear rams in block position. Monitor well for 30 mins on trip tanks and monitor BOP pressures. Well static. BSR -  44.7 gals. Pump spacer down the drill pipe line up on the sea chest and displace riser with seawater. Flow check well on trip tanks and monitored BOP pressures for 30 mins. Well static. POOH with EDPHOT. Rack back the EDPHOT running tool and RIH with BOP Landing Assist Tool (BLAT) and monitored well while conducting maintenance while waiting on weather. 

07/29/2011: ROV inspected BOP/Riser. Monitored well on trip tank while waiting on weather and monitor BOP pressures. POOH and L/D BLAT tool. TIH with EDPHOT to 6631'. Equalized pressure across BOP. Displaced surface equipment.Displaced boost line; kill line; and choke line with 14.2 ppg SBM. Displaced riser from seawater to 14.2 SBM. 

07/30/2011: Made up into the EDPHOT. Open failsafe valve to equalize pressures. Monitored well on trip tank. Well static. Unseated EDHPOT tool. Monitored BOP pressure. Monitor well. Well static. POOH. Well control drill while tripping.  Perform diverter function test from Driller's panel. Replace o'ring seal on open port diverter. Functioned the upper and lower shear rams from the Driller's panel using the Blue Pod. Pressure test upper shear rams and casing from OIM Panel on Yellow Pod with Halliburton using 14.2 SBM. 250 psi low and 2300 psi high. 5 minutes each; Closed upper shear rams (45.6 gal); 44 seconds to close.  Open upper shear rams (42.4 gal); 40 seconds to open. Performed diverter function test. TIH with 10-5/8" drilling assembly. Subsea testing choke manifold. Performed BOP Accumulator test. Conducted BOP function test on 5-7/8" drill pipe on the Yellow Pod from the OIM's panel. Pressure tested annular and upper inner choke to 250/5000 psi 5 minutes each. 
"},{"   ":14,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-07-31","TEXT_REMARK":"07/31/2011: Continued pressure testing BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from OIM panel on the Yellow Pod. All tests conducted with 14.2 SBM to 250/5000 psi on annular and 250/5800 psi on rams. TIH from 15;619' to 15;854' to space out for 6-5/8" drill pipe. Pressure test BOPs on 6-5/8" drill pipe from OIM panel Yellow Pod with 14.2 ppg SBM to 250/5000 psi on the annular and 250/5800 psi on the rams. Tested all surface equipment to 250/9500 psi. Continued to RIH from 15;753' to 18;575' with 10-5/8" drilling assembly.

08/01/2011: Closed annular and performed well control choke drills with crew by circulating up kill line while maintaining 500 psi on the choke gauge. Continued to TIH from 18;575' to 21;669' with 10-5/8' drilling assembly. Washed down from 24;529' to 24;930' with 120 spm at 3100 psi. Flow check well. Well static. Spaced out drill string; closed annular; and performed choke drills with 2nd crew. Washed down from 24;839' to 24;930'; and tagged firm cement. Drilled firm cement in shoe track from 24;930' to shoe at 25;082' with 14.2 ppg SBM. Drilled cement in rathole from 25;082' to 25;096'. Washed and reamed from 25;096' to 25;254' and drilled 10' of new formation to 25;264' for FIT. Circulated cuttings above BOP.

08/02/2011: Pulled back into 11-7/8" shoe and held well control drill while circulating. Spaced out on annular and performed FIT to 15.2 ppg EMW. Ran back in hole to 25;264' and drilled ahead from 25;264' to 25;528'. While making a connection at 25;504'; the well was flow checked and a 10.3 bbl gain was noted. Shut in well and monitored pressures - casing pressure increased 80 psi in 26 minutes and then held static for 30 minutes. Opened choke and bled off to 44 psi and monitored as pressure built up to 58 psi in 12 min then held static for 10 min. Opened choke and bled pressure to zero and monitored for flow on stripping tank - observed 5.1 bbl gain in 21 min (total gain of 15.4 bbl). Closed choke and monitored pressures. Located tool joint on annular and closed MVBRs to be in hangoff position for well-kill operation. Allowed pressures to stabilize and noted 246 psi on DP and 327 psi on casing. Broke circulation up choke and kill lines at 30 spm and staged up to 50 spm to establish ICP with 14.2 ppg while preparing 14.4 ppg KWM; circulated a total of 548 bbls of 14.2 ppg SBM while preparing KWM. Commenced killing well with 14.4 ppg KWM; staging pumps up to 40 spm with an ICP of 813 psi; circulated KWM to bit as per DP pressure schedule. 

08/03/2011: Circulated 14.4 ppg KWM to surface and shut in well to monitor pressures for 25 min. Opened choke and monitored well for flow on stripping tank for 40 min; well static. Displaced riser to 14.4 ppg SBM and performed stack sweep. Opened up BOP stack while monitoring for pressure. With BOP stack open; monitored well on trip tank and observed no flow. Continued drilling ahead with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from 25;528' to 25;672' with 35 ft/hr average ROP.

08/04/2011: Continued drilling ahead with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from 25;672' to 25;854'. Circulated and conditioned mud while waiting on confirmation of coring point. Continued drilling to 25;929'. Pumped 100 bbls of 14.4 ppg HiVis sweep to circulate hole clean; shut down pumps and flow checked well - static. Pumped out of hole at 50 spm from 25;929' to 11-7/8" shoe at 25;062'; shut down pumps and flow checked well for 5 min - static. Continued to pump out of hole at 50 spm to 24;611' and shut down pumps to flow check ¿ well static. Pump out of hole from 24;611' to 23;519' at 50spm. 

08/05/2011: Continued to pump out of the hole with 10-5/8" drilling BHA at 50 spm from 23;519' to 11-7/8" liner top at 20;852'. At 20;852'; shut down pumps and flow checked well - static. Pulled out of hole wet from 20;852' to 20;189' and observed proper hole fill. Pumped 60 bbl slug and pulled out of hole to 1;010'. Function tested diverter at 1;010' from OIM panel and continued pulling out of hole to surface.

08/06/2011: Continued to handle BHA on surface. Slipped and cut 119' of drill line and performed planned maintenance while continuing to boost riser. Made up coring BHA in forward rotary and began tripping in the hole from 252' to 6;327'; filling pipe every 20 stands. Held well control drill while tripping at 3;780' - well secured in 166 sec. 
"},{"   ":15,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-08-07","TEXT_REMARK":"08/07/2011: Continued tripping in the hole with 14.4 ppg SBM and staged pumps up. Function lower and upper shear rams on OIM panel Blue Pod. Continued tripping in the hole. Function tested diverter from Driller's panel. Functioned annular opened and closed from Blue Pod on Driller's panel. Function tested BOPs from Yellow Pod OIM panel. Continued tripping in the hole to 22;292'. Surface indicators suggested potential leak on BOP; ROV dove to investigate. Leak was confirmed in flange on 5k-to-3k regulator on Yellow Pod. Pumped out the hole to top of 11-7/8" liner to monitor well; and prepare to secure. Well static. 

08/08/2011: Continued to pump out of the hole to 20;678'. Pulled out of hole wet with core barrels from 15;032' to 13;555'. Took Slow Pump Rates with one pump at 13;555'. Made up 13-5/8" RTTS packer at 13;555'. Tripped in the hole with 13-5/8" RTTS from 13;555' to 20;572' (bit depth) and prepared to set. Set packer at 7016' in the 13-5/8" casing. BOP pressure read 5113 psi and annular closed. 

08/09/2011: Applied 1000 psi down drill pipe and positive pressure tested RTTS and SSC3 valve for 5 minutes. Bled off pressure and opened annular. Pulled out of the hole from 6;998' to 6;704' and closed annular once again. Located tool joint with 20k overpull and began preparing to perform negative test on RTTS. Held pre-job safety meeting then performed negative test by pumping base oil (6.6 ppg) down the drill pipe simulating the removal of 2100 psi off the RTTS with the test Rams closed. Determined the well was static after monitoring well for 1 hour. Pumped up the stand pipe to balance the 2100 psi back to the hydrostatic column. Prepared rig for riser displacement and held pre-job safety meeting. Flushed choke and kill lines with seawater; then shut and trapped additional 2132 psi under shear rams to simulate 14.4 ppg mud column above in preparation for unlatching the LMRP (Lower Marine Riser Package). Pumped Hi-Vis water based spacer followed by seawater to displace; monitored riser barrel in barrel out. Shut pumps down once seawater was seen at the gumbo box. Pulled out of hole from 6;616' to 2;741' with SSC3 RTTS running tool. 

08/10/2011: Rigged up riser handling equipment and picked up diverter running tool to latch into diverter. Picked up landing joint and then slacked off to scope in the inner barrel. Proceeded to unlatch the LMRP connector with Blue Pod at 13:54 hours and lifted LMRP off BOP at 6;643'. Once off the BOP; the rig was moved 500' off location in a 230 degree direction. Rigged up in moon pool to pull landing joint and riser jewelry while ROV conducted a sea floor survey. Once finished; pulled the Slip joint and began pulling out the hole with riser. 

08/11/2011: Continued POOH with the termination joint; 20' PUP; and then riser from 6;240' to 6;410' and laid them out. Once up and running; pulled another 17 joints of riser out of the hole from 6;015' to 4;740'. Continued to pull another 26 jts to 2;790. 

08/12/2011: Continued pulling riser and LMRP from 2;790' to 1;093'. Held a safety stand down meeting following shutting down operations due to personnel hand injury (held two during the day to brief both tours). Continued pulling riser from 1;093' to surface. Once the riser was on the beams and moved to work maintenance area; the work scope started. 

08/13/2011: Continued work scope; repairs; and tests on the LMRP. 
"},{"   ":16,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-08-14","TEXT_REMARK":"08/14/2011: Resume repairs; pre-launch checks; and testing on LMRP. Functioned annular on Yellow and Blue Pods and conducted soak test on Yellow and Blue Pods. Conducted initial and final EDS testing from the subsea CCU using the Yellow Pod SEM A and Blue Pod SEM A. Installed choke and kill internal packing seals and performed Solenoid Dry Fire test on Yellow Pod. Checked pressures across 4 x 5 and 3 x 5 regulators on both Yellow and Blue Pods. Installed new VGX2 gasket and picked up LMRP and prepare to splash. 

08/15/2011: Resume with LMRP/Riser run. Splashed LMRP and ran riser from surface to 3;868' (49 jts). The boost and rigid conduit lines were tested by Subsea; and Halliburton pressure tested both the choke and kill lines. 

08/16/2011: Continue with running the LMRP/Riser from 3;868' to 6;438'. Continue with testing choke and kill lines; boost and rigid conduit lines. Installed the drape hoses and mux cable saddles in the moon pool. Installed choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit hoses on termination joint. 

08/17/2011: Held pre-job safety meeting on landing and latching LMRP to BOP. Landed the LMRP on the BOP stack applying 50k down. Subsea latched connector on Blue Pod and energized pod stabs; choke and kill stabs on LMRP; and brought the BOP back on-line. Installed diverter in diverter housing and energized locking dogs. Perform full diverter function test from Driller's panel. Tripped in the hole with RTTS overshot assembly from surface to 5;430'. 

08/18/2011: Continued running in the hole with RTTS overshot assembly from 5;340' to 6;975'. Held pre-job safety meeting on displacing riser to SBM. Flow check well - well static. Tested upper shears rams against RTTS from the OIM panel on Blue Pod to 250/2100 psi for 5 minutes each. Monitor well on the trip tank. Well static. Functioned the upper and lower blind shear rams from Driller's panel on Yellow Pod. Performed accumulator test. Pressure tested the BOPs on 5-7/8" DP from the OIM panel on the Blue Pod to 250/5700 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested annular; upper inner choke; upper outer choke; UVBR; MVBR; LVBRs; lower inner choke; lower outer choke; and bottom of CMV #5 for 5 minutes each - surface equipment tested to 250/9400 psi; subsea equipment tested to 250/5700 psi and annular and associated valves tested to 250/5000 psi. Also; performed BOP function test on Yellow Pod from Driller's panel. 

08/19/2011: Continued with procedure to retrieve RTTS. Freed RTTS with 40k overpull. Monitored well on backside and trip tank. Closed off backside and opened annular to monitor well on trip tank. Well static. POOH from 7;009' to 6;372' with RTTS. Circulate and condition mud. Continue testing choke manifold with 14.4 SBM to 250/9400 psi for 5 minutes each. Tested buffer side of choke manifold and continued pulling out of the hole with coring assembly from 18;873' to 13;555'. Laid-out RTTS assembly; and then ran back in the hole with coring assembly from 13;555' to 16;030' to space out and test BOPs. Held well control drill while tripping. 

08/20/2011: Continued with BOP testing on 6-5/8" DP with 14.4 ppg SBM from the OIM's panel on Blue Pod. Diverter function tested from OIM panel. Held Well Control Drill. Continued running in the hole with core barrel assembly from 16;030' to 22;023'. 
"},{"   ":17,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-08-21","TEXT_REMARK":"08/21/2011: Continue tripping in the hole from 22;023' to 25;082' to the 11-7/8" liner shoe. Function test the BOP's from Driller's panel using the Yellow Pod. Function the diverter from the OIM's panel. Continue to trip to 25;684'. Begin washing down to total depth at 25;929'. Circulate bottoms up and condition the mud. 

08/22/2011: Continue circulating bottoms up and conditioning the mud at 25;929'. After circulating the mud; begin coring from 25;929' to 26;169'; filling the 240' core barrel. Circulate cuttings up the hole.  

08/23/2011: Begin pumping out the hole from 26;169' to 20;140' above the top of the 11-7/8" liner. Pump slug and continue trip out of the hole to 6;836'. 

08/24/2011: Continue pulling out of the hole from 6;836' to surface. Function test upper and lower shear rams from OIM's panel on Blue Pod. Rigged up Schlumberger wireline equipment. Pick up Schlumberger USIT wireline tool and run the USIT tool in the hole to perform casing evaluation. 

08/25/2011: Continued running in the hole with the Schlumberger USIT wireline tool. Start logging up from 25;000' to 6;671. Pull out of hole with USIT wireline tool and rig down wireline equipment. Function both sets of shear rams from the OIM's panel on Yellow Pod. Slip and cut drill line. Make up core assembly #2 and run core assembly in the hole to 914'.

08/26/2011: Continued tripping in the hole with coring assembly from 914' to 11;692'. Perform well control drill while tripping. Continue tripping in the hole from 11;692 to 19;744'. Function test BOP on blue pod from OIM panel. Continue tripping in the hole from 19;744' to 26;047'. Break circulation and wash down to 26;160'.

08/27/2011: Establish slow pump rates. Start coring from 26;169' to 26;210'. Break off core and circulate cuttings up the hole. Check flow for 5 minutes. Well was static. Pump out the hole with coring assembly to 22;309'  
"},{"   ":18,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-08-28","TEXT_REMARK":"08/28/2011: Pumped out of the hole with coring assembly from 22;309' to 20;859' and flow checked well at shoe. Pulled out of hole from 20;829' to 675'; performed well control drill while tripping at 20;157'. 

08/29/2011: Continued pulling out of the hole with the coring assembly from 675' to surface. Functioned BSR and CSR. Began running in hole with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from surface to 20;052'; filling pipe every 20 stands. Held well control drill while tripping at 14;676'.   

08/30/2011: Continued to run in hole from 20;052' to 25;749'; filling pipe every 20 stands and breaking circulation. Washed and reamed while logging cored section with LWD from 25;749' to 26;410'. Drilled ahead with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from 26;410' to 26;710'. 

08/31/2011: Continued drilling ahead with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from 26;710' to 27;490'. Held well control pit drill while drilling. 

09/01/2011: Continued drilling ahead with 10-5/8" drilling assembly from 27;490' to 27;517'. Circulated sweep while troubleshooting drawworks encoder malfunction. Pumped out of hole with drilling assembly from 27;326' to 20;725'. Flow checked well at shoe and top of liner and held well control drill while tripping. Continued to pull out of hole from 20;725' to 17;362' and picked up RTTS tool for storm suspension. Began tripping back in the hole with RTTS tool from 17;430' to 18;775'.    

09/02/2011: Continued tripping in hole from 18;775' to 24;370' with RTTS tool for storm suspension. Set tool at 24;370' bit depth / 6;998' tool depth. Tested RTTS and storm valve to 1000 psi for 5 min against annular preventer. Picked up above BOP stack and displaced the choke and kill lines over to seawater. Closed BSR and pressure tested BSR against RTTS to 1000 psi over hydrostatic for 15 min. Displaced riser to seawater and pulled out of the hole to surface with the RTTS running tool.

09/03/2011: Wait on weather and performed planned maintenance on drilling equipment.   
"},{"   ":19,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-09-04","TEXT_REMARK":"09/04/2011: Tripped in the hole with the RTTS Overshot tool and one test stand of 5-7/8" drill pipe on a 6-5/8" drill string. Displaced surface equipment; Boost; Choke; and Kill lines from seawater to 14.4 ppg SBM. Pressure tested BSR; and function tested both BSR and CSR. 

09/05/2011: Performed BOP accumulator test. Tested the BOP annular along with variable pipe ram components on 5-7/8" and 6-5/8" drill pipe. Engaged RTTS SSCIII with Overshot; unlatched; and began pumping out of the hole. Began testing choke manifold and safety valves. 

09/06/2011: Finished pumping out of the hole with RTTS and laid it down along with BOP test stands. Tripped in the hole with 10-5/8" drill ahead assembly to 25;648'. Finished testing the choke manifold. Observed an 8.5 bbl gain on the trip tank and shut the well in. Recorded pressures and monitored well on the choke panel. Held pre-job safety meeting on rig floor and stripped 5 stands through annular to bit depth 26;144 (deeper than estimated deepest logged permeable zone) and began circulating out the influx while keeping constant bottom hole pressure and original mud weight 14.4 ppg.  

09/07/2011: Finished circulating the influx out of well from 26;144' with original mud weight. Swept remaining gas from below annular via u-tubing kill line with base oil. Began circulating riser volume down the boost and choke lines with 14.4 ppg SBM and monitored wellbore.   

09/08/2011: Finished circulating riser after circulating out the influx and sweeping the stack. Flow checked the well and confirmed it static. Pumped out of the hole to remove safety valves from string and tripped back to bottom in with 10-5/8" drilling assembly. Circulated 14.5 ppg mud weight around once on bottom; and reconfirmed static wellbore. Pumped out of the hole to pick up RTTS in preparation for Tropical Storm Nate.  

09/09/2011: Continued to pump out of the hole 5 stands to top of liner. Flow checked and ensured a static well. Pulled out of the hole to pick up RTTS. Decision was made concerning Tropical Storm Nate that well operations would continue. Pulled out of hole above the BOP and performed BSR/CSR function test. Began TIH with 10-5/8" drilling assembly to BOP test stands. 

09/10/2011: Continued to trip in the hole to 9;170' and performed both a diverter function test as well as a BOP function test on both 5-7/8" and 6-5/8" drill pipe. Tripped in the hole to bottom and drilled from 27;517' to 27;553'. Picked up off bottom to investigate and begin troubleshooting upper inner kill fail safe valve function on the Yellow Pod.   
"},{"   ":20,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-09-11","TEXT_REMARK":"09/11/2011: Pumped and circulated LCM sweep out of the hole while troubleshooting and investigating the lower marine riser package upper inner kill failsafe function on Yellow Pod. Flow checked well and pumped out of the hole to 24;762'. Trip to bottom with the drilling assembly. 

09/12/2011: Drill the 10-5/8" section from 27;452' to 27;970'.

09/13/2011: Continued to drill from 27;970' to well total depth 28;000'. Weighted up to a 14.6 ppg SBM mud and circulated over total system volume. Pulled out of the hole to 15;438' and checked for flow prior to performing an accumulator draw down test on the Blue Pod from the central control unit. 

9/14/2011: Pressure tested BOPs on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Driller's panel on Blue Pod. Pressure tested BOPs on 6-5/8" drill pipe with Blue Pod from Driller's panel. Function tested BOPs with Yellow Pod from OIM panel. Function tested diverter from OIM panel. Pulled out of the hole with 10-5/8" drilling assembly to 11;184'. Held well control drill while tripping. 

9/15/2011: Continued pulling out of the hole to 7;504' while subsea finished testing the choke manifold. Flow checked the well and ensured it was static. Continued pulling out of the hole to surface with 10-5/8" drilling assembly. Rigged up wire line and ran in hole to begin first of five logging runs. 

09/16/2011: Pulled out of the hole with wireline run #1. Held a pre-job safety meeting with crew on rigging down and rigging up wireline equipment for next run. Ran in hole with wireline run #2. Pulled out of the hole with run #2 and rigged up and ran in hole with wireline run #3. 

09/17/2011: Held pre-job safety meeting and continued to get on depth for third wireline run. Continued with logging program and began pulling out of the hole to commence taking formation samples. 
"},{"   ":21,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-09-18","TEXT_REMARK":"09/18/2011: Continued with third wireline run; taking fluid samples. 

09/19/2011: Completed taking wireline samples with run #3. Pulled out of hole with wireline. Held a pre-job safety meeting with crew on rigging down; changing wire and rigging up wireline equipment for next run. Changed wire and ran in hole with wireline run #4A; MCST. 

09/20/2011: Completed wireline run #4A taking sidewall cores. Pulled out of hole and held a pre-job safety meeting with crew on laying out and picking up new wireline tools for next run. Ran in hole with wireline run #4B; MCST. Held well control drill while tripping in. Took sidewall cores and began pulling out of hole with wireline run #4B. 

09/21/2011: Continued to pull out of hole with wireline run #4B. Held pre-job safety meeting on laying out wireline tools. Laid out wireline tools and function tested upper and lower shear rams from OIM panel on Yellow Pod. Performed passive acoustic monitoring for marine mammals while making up wireline run #5. Ran in hole with wireline run #5 and performed VSP. Pulled out of hole and rigged down wireline. Held pre-job safety meeting and picked up forward TDS. 

09/22/2011: Held pre-job safety meeting and ran in hole with mule shoe cement assembly to 27;990'. While running in hole; functioned diverter from the Driller's panel. Functioned upper and lower shear rams from Driller's panel on Blue pod. Performed a BOP function test from the Driller's panel on Blue Pod. Circulated bottoms up. 

09/23/2011: Continued to circulate bottoms up. Flushed stack and pulled out of hole from 27;990' to 26;850' and spotted 55 bbls 16.6 ppg weighted hi-vis pill. Pulled out of hole to 26;302'. Held pre-job safety meeting and made up cement stand. Held pre-job safety meeting and spaced out and started cement job. Performed balanced cement job and began displacing cement with rig pumps.

09/24/2011: Rigged down cement stand and pulled out of cement to 24;980'. Pumped to clear drill string prior to pulling out of hole to 24;419'. Circulated 1-1/2 times drill string volume and then pulled out of hole. Held well control drill while tripping. Held pre-job safety meeting and racked back TDS while boosting riser. Held pre-job safety meeting and rigged up wireline to run 11-7/8" EZSV. Began to RIH with 11-7/8" EZSV.
"},{"   ":22,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-09-25","TEXT_REMARK":"09/25/2011: Continued to run in hole with 11-7/8" EZSV on wireline. Observed restriction above planned setting depth; therefore set EZSV above restriction at 24;490' per approval from BOEMRE. Pressure tested EZSV; casing and blind shear rams to 250/2;000 psi for 5/30 minutes with cement unit; and function blind shear rams and casing shear rams on Blue Pod from Driller's panel. Ran in hole with EZSV MST stinger assembly. 

09/26/2011: Continued to run in hole with EZSV MST stinger assembly. Performed well control drill while tripping. Tagged EZSV at 24;496' with 10 klbf down. Spotted balanced cement plug above EZSV from 24;188' ¿ 24;492' with 34 bbls of 16.6 ppg Class H silica-blend cement. Pressure tested EZSV and cement plug to 1;000 psi for 15 minutes with cement unit. 

09/27/2011: POOH with EZSV MST stinger assembly and spotted 55 bbls of 15.6 ppg hi-vis pill at 21;600'. POOH to 21;100' and spotted balanced cement plug from across 11-7/8" liner top from 20;600' to 21;100' with 66 bbls of 16.6 ppg Class H cement silica-blend. 

09/28/2011: POOH to surface with the EZSV MST stinger. Picked up and RIH with 13-3/8" EZSV on drill pipe to 14;100'. Set EZSV at 14;107' and picked up above it to 14;102'. Spotted balanced cement plug above EZSV from 13;602 to 14;102' with 75 bbls of 16.6 ppg Class H silica-blend cement. 

09/29/2011: Pulled out of hole to 7;821' to circulate and condition mud. Pressure tested retainer and cement to 1;000 psi for 15 minutes with cement unit. Spotted 75 bbls 16.6 ppg hi-vis weighted pill; 7;821'. Pulled out of hole from 7;821' to 7;321'. 

09/30/2011: Performed negative test on wellbore to 2;325 psi with base oil. Bled pressure down to 250 psi and monitored for 10 min with no increase in pressure. Bled pressure down to zero and monitored for flow for one hour with no flow observed from wellbore. Displaced choke; kill; boost; and riser from SBM to seawater. Spotted balanced cement plug from 6;825' to 7;325' with 75 bbls of 16.4 ppg Class H cement. 

10/01/2011: POOH to surface with EZSV MST. Picked up and RIH with riser brush and wear-bushing retrieval tool. Circulated riser and pulled out of hole with wear bushing and riser brush assembly. 
"},{"   ":23,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2011-10-02","TEXT_REMARK":"10/02/2011: Rigged up riser handling equipment and began pulling riser jewelry followed by riser joints and BOP from 6671' to 6;269'. 

10/03/2011: Continued pulling riser and BOP from 6;269' to surface. Landed BOPs on beams and split LMRP from BOP. 

10/04/2011: Begin Rig Work Scope: Rig down riser handling equipment; prepare for heavy lift inspection and cleaning the mud module. 

10/05/2011: Rig Work Scope: Continue preparing for heavy lift inspection. Prepare pipe handling equipment for NDT (non-destructive testing) inspection. Clean mud module. 

10/06/2011: Rig Work Scope: Continue heavy lift inspection and cleaning the mud module. 

10/07/2011: Rig Work Scope: Performed clear bottom survey and recovered compatts with the ROV. Continued heavy lift inspections and cleaning mud module. 

10/08/2011: Ship departed from Keathley Canyon 785.  
"},{"   ":24,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-06-27","TEXT_REMARK":"06/27/2017: Continue between well maintenance.

Note; On 06/27/2017 at 12:52 hrs; Mr. Kenley McQueen (Chevron) notified Mr. Tom Basey; Mr. Michael Burdette; and Mr. Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) of the Discoverer Inspiration's intentions to begin transit tomorrow; 06/28/2017; from GC640 to KC785 in preparation for P&A operations at the Buckskin well (KC785 #1) with an anticipated arrival on the evening of 06/28/2017.

Note: On 06/27/2017 at 12:57 hrs; Mr. Kenley McQueen notified Mr. Tom Basey; Mr. Michael Burdette; and Mr. Marty Rinaudo of the Discoverer Inspiration's intentions to commence initial subsea BOP testing in 72 hours on Friday; 06/30/2017; for P&A operations at the KC785 #1 well.

06/28/2017: Perform between well maintenance. Move rig from GC 640 PC001 SHZ to Buckskin #1 (KC 785 #1) SHZ.

06/29/2017: Perform between well maintenance. Prepare to run BOP on riser. 

06/30/2017: Perform between well maintenance. Completed BOP stump testing per Transocean procedure. Prepare to run BOP on riser.

Note: On 06/30/2017 at 12:00 hrs; Mr. Kenley McQueen (Chevron) received written approval from Mr. Michael Burdette (BSEE) to leave the 1502 companion flanges rigged up to the choke manifold outlets during the Buckskin P&A.

07/01/2017: Skid BOP from starboard setback area to well center. Make up riser double and suspend BOP in moonpool. Splash BOP at 03:30 hrs. Run BOP on riser from surface to 6;344'.

"},{"   ":25,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-07-02","TEXT_REMARK":"07/02/2017: Ran BOP on riser from 6;344' to 6;514'. Pressure tested choke and kill lines to 250-350 psi/ 6;600 psi for 5 minutes; good test. Pressure tested boost line to 250-350 psi/ 5;000 psi; good test. Pressure tested rigid conduit to 5;000 psi with Subsea test unit; good test. Landed BOP on Buckskin #1. Performed slump and overpull test. Close UBSR on Primary Panel; Blue Pod; and pressure test connector to 1;000 psi for 5 minutes against surface cement plug; good test. Installed diverter. Performed deadman test; good test. Performed UBSR pressure test to 250-350 psi/ 5;600 psi; good test. Function tested UBSR and CSR from Primary Panel; Blue Pod; and from Secondary Panel; Yellow Pod; good tests.

Note: On 07/02/2017 at 9:01 PM; Kenley McQueen (Chevron) notified Tom Basey (BSEE); Michael Burndette (BSEE); and Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) that Stump Testing on the Inspiration concluded Friday; 06/30/2017; and attached the results.

07/03/2017: Troubleshot leak in diverter flowline seal. Tripped in hole with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from surface to 130' and functioned diverter. Observed BOP fluid in diverter housing. Pulled out of hole with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from 130' to surface. Pulled diverter to surface and changed diverter upper flow line seal. Re-install diverter.

07/04/2017: Tripped in hole with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from surface to 6;801'. Washed down from 6;801' and tag hard cement at 6;918'. Pressure tested BOP using test rams on 6-5/8" drill pipe from Primary Panel; Blue Pod; with 8.6 ppg seawater. Tested annular; rams; and associated valves to 250-350 psi/ 5;600 psi; good tests. Displaced well and riser from 8.6 ppg seawater to 13.0 ppg SBM. Performed choke and diverter drills. Drilled hard cement from 6;918' to 6;979'.

Note: On 07/04/2017 at 3:09 PM; Mr. Kenley McQueen (Chevron) received written approval from Mr. Mark Malbrue (BSEE) to proceed with P&A operations and received recognition of 3rd party BOP compatibility verification.

07/05/2017: Continued to drill hard cement from 6;979' to 7;011'. Pulled out of hole from 7;011' to surface. Tripped in hole from surface to 7;011' with 12-1/4" drilling assembly. Continued to drill hard cement from 7;011' to 7;090'.

07/06/2017: Drilled hard cement from 7;090' to 7;324'. Broke through hard cement and performed flow check; well static. Washed from 7;324' to 7;358' and tagged cement. Drilled hard cement from 7;358' to 7;367'. Broke through hard cement and washed from 7;367' to 7;387'. Performed flow check; well static.

Note: On 07/06/2017 at 1:50 PM; Kenley McQueen (Chevron) notified Tom Basey (BSEE); Michael Burndette (BSEE); and Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) that Initial Latchup Testing on the Inspiration concluded Tuesday; 07/04/2017; and attached the results. 

07/07/2017: Drilled ratty cement from 7;387' to 7;410' and broke through cement. Washed down from 7;410' to 7;476'. Tripped in hole from 7;476' to 9;400'. Displaced wellbore to 13.0 ppg SBM. Pulled out of the hole with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from 9;400' to 6;677'. Washed 14" hanger and BOPs from 6;677' to 6;627'. Performed flow check; well static. Pulled out of the hole with 12-1/4" drilling assembly from 6;585' to surface. Tripped in hole with hydraulic casing cutter from surface to 6;923'.

07/08/2017: Continued tripping in hole with hydraulic casing cutter from 6;923' to 9;344'. Landed out marine swivel on 14" casing hanger. Cut casing at 9;397'. Performed flow checks; well static. Pulled out of hole with hydraulic cutter assembly from 9;405' to surface. Tripped in hole with multi-purpose tool (MPT) assembly from surface to 6;730'. Jetted BOP and wellhead with three passes. Circulated bottoms up. Tripped in hole with MPT assembly from 6;830' to 7;441' and land MPT in seal assembly. Close annular and pull seal assembly. 
"},{"   ":26,"WELL_NAME":"  001","API12":608084002100,"WAR_START_DT":"2017-07-09","TEXT_REMARK":"07/09/2017: Trip out of hole (TOH) with seal assembly from 7;435' to surface. Trip in hole (TIH) with casing spear assembly from surface and engage 14" casing fish at 6;692' with spear (end of fish at 9;398'). TOH with casing from 9;398' to 2;590'. 

07/10/2017: TOH with 14" casing from 2;590' to surface. TIH with cleanout assembly from surface to 9;375' and circulate well clean. TOH with cleanout assembly from 9;375' to surface. Pick up CIBP (Cast Iron Bridge Plug) and TIH from surface to 5;664'. 

07/11/2017: TIH with CIBP from 5;664' to 9;350'. Set CIBP at 9;350' and pressure test from above to 1;000 psi for 5 min; good test. Release from CIBP and spot 400' cement plug from 9;350' to 8;950'. TOH from 9;350' to 8;602'. Pressure test cement plug to 1;000 psi for 15 minutes with 13.0 ppg SBM; good test. TOH from 8;602' to 7;985' and perform negative test o 1;998 psi for 30 minutes. Displace well from 13.0 ppg SBM to 8.6 ppg seawater. 

07/12/2017: Continue displacing well to 8.6 ppg seawater. TOH with CIBP setting tool from 7;985' to surface. TIH with riser cleanout assembly from surface to 6;694 and circulate riser clean with 8.6 ppg seawater. TOH with riser cleanout assembly from 6;694' to 5;545'.

07/13/2017: TOH with riser cleanout assembly from 5;545' to surface. Unlatch BOP and pick up from 6;671' to 6;607'. Transit vessel 548' off location and pull BOP on riser from 6;607' to 6;455'. 

07/14/2017: Pull BOP on riser from 6;455' to surface.

07/15/2017: TIH with cement diverter sub from surface to 6;038'. Transit back to well center and TIH from 6;038' to 7;486'. Spot 400' viscous pill from 7;486' to 7;186'. TOH from 7;486' to 7;186'. Spot 485' cement plug from 7;186' to 6;701'. TOH with cement stinger from 7;186' to 6;573'. Move 50' off location and ROV install TA cap over wellhead. TOH with cement stinger from 6;573' to surface. ROV perform clear bottom survey. End of well.

"},{"   ":27,"WELL_NAME":"  001a","API12":608084001600,"WAR_START_DT":"2008-08-24","TEXT_REMARK":"08/24/08 - Offloaded equipment.

08/25/08 - Began to run 36" DP.

08/26/08 - Began evacuation for Hurricane Gustav.

08/27/08 - Continued TIH from 1275' - 6579'.

08/28/08 - LD 36" DP to surface. Secured rig & continued evacuation of non-essential personnel due to hurricane.

08/29/08 - Finished evacuation for hurricane.

"},{"   ":53,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-03-31","TEXT_REMARK":"03/31/2013: Drill 26" hole from 7;675' to 8;600' with seawater. Drill 26" hole from 8;600' to 9;000' with 10.0 ppg PAD mud. Drill 26" hole from 9;000' to 9;145' with 10.5 ppg PAD mud. 

04/01/2013: Continue drilling 26" hole from 9;146' to 9;915' with 10.5 ppg PAD mud. Drill from 9;915' to 10;448' with 11.0 - 11.5 ppg PAD mud. 

04/02/2013: Continue drilling 26" hole from 10;448' to 10;835' with 11.3 ppg PAD mud. Circulate sweeps. Spot 50 bbls; 16.6 ppg PAD mud on bottom. Displace hole to 12.5 ppg PAD mud. Pulled out of the hole with 26" drilling assembly from 10;835' to 1;061'. 

04/03/2013: Continue pulling out of the hole to surface. Rigged up casing handling equipment. Run 22" casing from surface to 4;075'.
Note: Ms. Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received approval from Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE) to manually control the nitrogen; foamer and stabilizer injection for 22" casing cement job.

04/04/2013: Continue running 22" casing from 4;075' to 4;241'. Make up the high pressure wellhead housing and run inner string. Run 22" casing and high pressure wellhead housing on landing string to 10;166'. Wash down to 10;795' and land the high pressure wellhead in the low pressure housing. Circulate 560 bbls 12.5 ppg PAD mud. Pump 300 bbl; 12.5 ppg lignite caliper with 300 bbl; 12.5 ppg PAD mud. Pump 20 bbls 14.2 ppg unfoamed cement spacer; pump 208 bbls 13.2 ppg foamed spacer. Begin to mix and pump 130 bbls 16.4 ppg (surface); equivalent to 826 cu ft 14.5 ppg (downhole) foamed lead cement for 22" casing.  

04/05/2013: Continue to mix and pump 1;391 bbls 16.4 ppg (surface); equivalent to 8;833 cu ft 14.5 ppg (downhole) foamed lead cement for 22" casing. Total foamed lead cement: 1;521 bbls 16.4 ppg (surface); equivalent to 9;659 cu ft 14.5 ppg (downhole). Mix and pump foamed tail cement: 231 bbls 16.4 ppg (surface); 1;465 cu ft 14.5 ppg (downhole). Mix and pump unfoamed tail cement: 190 bbls 1;067 cu ft; 16.4 ppg. Launched dart and put cement in place with 289 bbls seawater. Check floats; holding.  Pre-load high pressure wellhead housing and release running tool. Pick up running tool from high pressure housing; displace casing to 12.5 ppg treated PAD mud. Pull out of the hole with landing string and inner string to 7;860'; displace casing to seawater; spot 120 bbls; 13.0 ppg viscous pill from 7;860' to 7;560'. Pull up to spot 100' cement plug from 7;560' to 7;460'; mix and pump 40 bbls (225 cu ft) 13.5 ppg cement. Pull stinger above cement plug to 7;410' and displace well to 12.5 ppg treated PAD mud. Pull out of the hole to 3;935'.  

04/06/2013: Continue to pull out of hole with 5-7/8" inner string to surface. ROV installed T/A cap on high pressure wellhead. 
"},{"   ":54,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-04-07","TEXT_REMARK":"04/07/2013: ROV spotted 35 gal preservation fluid in wellhead and performed clear bottom survey. Rig departed field at 12:00 hrs."},{"   ":55,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-07-24","TEXT_REMARK":"07/24/2013: Complete testing wellhead connector on BOP; performed pre-deployment and deployment checks on BOP. Skid BOP onto beams and make up riser double.

07/25/2013: Torqued bolts on double; lowered BOP; install mux clamps and position mux cable sheaves for deployment; splashed BOP; run BOP on marine riser to 5;294'. Held Safety Stand-up and perform rig-wide hazard hunt.

07/26/2013: Continue to run BOP on marine riser to 6;279'. Make up flex/termination and slip joint. Install drape hoses. Hold Safety Stand-up and review well control. Pick up 16' heavy wall pup and landing joint; install storm loops and slacked off and lock SDC ring. Positioned rig 30' from wellhead and performed dummy run. Wellhead is higher than expected. Lay out landing joint; heavy wall pup and 10' riser pup.

07/27/2013: Held Safety Stand-up. Run termination and slip joints; make up drape hoses; pick up 16' heavy wall pup and landing joint; close and lock SDC ring; Position rig over wellhead and land out BOP. Perform overpull and slump tests. Adjust tensioners. Lay down landing joint and install diverter. Rig down riser handling equipment. Pick up one stand of DP and perform diverter flow test from Driller's panel and Toolpusher's panel. Make up and trip in the hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 413'.
"},{"   ":56,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-07-28","TEXT_REMARK":"07/28/2013: Continue tripping in the hole from 413' to 684'; make up BOP test tool and contine tripping in the hole to 6;957'.  erformed Accumulator Drawdown Test. Land BOP test tool in wellhead; pressure test variable bore rams; associated valves and wellhead connector to 250/11;700 psi with seawater. Pressure test Annular Preventer against BOP test tool to 250/5;200 psi with seawater.

07/29/2013: Pressure test blind shear rams against BOP test tool to 250/11;700 psi with seawater. Perform BOP function test. Function test diverter. POOH with BOP test tool assembly from 7;077' to 2;009'. Function test BSR/CSR. POOH with BOP test tool assembly from 2;009' to 413'. Rack back BOP test tool. Make up remainder of 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and TIH from 413' to 5;169'. 

07/30/2013: Continue tripping into the hole from 5;169' to 6;503'. Displace drill pipe to 9.8 ppg WBM. Continue to trip into the hole wash down to tag top of cement at 7;482'. Displace wellbore; riser; Choke/Kill/Boost lines to 9.8 ppg WBM. Circulate and condition mud to 10.2 ppg in/out. Drill out surface cement plug from 7;482' to 7;607'. Continue tripping into the hole from 7;607' to 10;249'. Wash down from 10;249' to 10;413'.

07/31/2013: Circulate bottoms up at 10;407' MD. Wash down; and tag TOC at 10;562' MD. Circulate and condition mud to 10.2 ppg. Test 22" casing to 3;000 psi with 10.2 ppg WBM. Drill out cement from 10;562' to 10;793'. Clean out cement to 10;795'. Circulate and condition mud.

08/01/2013: Wash and ream from 10;793' to 10;845' MD. Drill 18-1/8" hole from 10;845' to 10;855' MD. Backream from 10;855' MD to 10;786' MD. Circulate and condition mud. Perform shoe test to 233 psi with 10.2 ppg WBM; 10.6 ppg equivalent. Spot 78 bbls 16.0 ppg mud on bottom. Pull out of the hole from 10;850' to 784'.

08/02/2013: Continue to pull out of the hole from 784' to surface. Rack back 18-1/8" X 21" BHA. Make up 6-5/8" cement stinger and trip into the hole to 10;855' MD. Circulate and Condition mud to 10.2 ppg in/out. Pump 175 bbls 12.5 ppg spacer; mix & pump 165 bbls 16.4 ppg cement; pump 15 bbls 12.5 ppg spacer and displace. Pull out of the hole to 10;173'. Shut in well on annular and perform hesitation squeeze. Wait on cement.

08/03/2013: Continue to wait on cement. Open annular and flow check; well static. Circulate and condition mud. Trip out of the hole with cement stinger from 10;173' to surface. 
"},{"   ":57,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-08-04","TEXT_REMARK":"08/04/2013: Clean and clear rig floor. Slip & cut drill line. Pick up and trip in hole with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling BHA. Wash and ream from 10;632' to 10692'. Drill cement from 10;692' to 10;770'. Circulate and condition water based mud. 

08/05/2013: Drill out cement from 10;770' MD to 10;858' MD. Function test BOPs. Drill 18-1/8" x 19-7/8" hole from 10;858' MD to 10;865' MD. Circulate & condition mud. POOH to 10;788' MD. Function test diverter. Perform shoe test with 10.2 ppg WBM to 340 psi; 10.8 ppg equivalent.

08/06/2013: Trip out of the hole from 10;788' to 1;029'. Rack back 18-1/8" x 21" BHA fom 1;029' to surface. Clean and clear rig floor. Make up diverter sub and trip in hole to 10;865' MD. Circulated and conditioned mud. Pump 175 bbls of 10.2 ppg spacer for cement squeeze.

08/07/2013: Mix and pump 147 bbls of 16.4 ppg cement; 16 bbls 10.2 ppg spacer; displace with 10.2 ppg WBM. Pull out of the hole to 10;145' and performed hesitation squeeze. Shut in well and wait on cement. Bled pressure off of wellbore; opened annular and flow checked - well static. Circulated bottoms up. Pulled out of hole from 10;145' to 9;146'.

08/08/2013: Continue to pull out of the hole from 9;146' to surface with cement stinger. Pick up 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and trip in the hole from surface 10;253'. Washed down from 10;253' to top of cement at 10;472'. Drilled out cement inside 22" casing from 10;472' to 10;653'.

08/09/2013: Continue drilling out cement from 10;653' to 10;830'. Circulate and condition mud. Pull out of the hole to 10;743'. Performed preliminary FIT at 22" casing shoe with 10.2 ppg WBM to 380 psi; 10.87 ppg equivalent. Pull out of the hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA from 10;830' to surface. Picked up 4-1/2" cement stinger and trip in the hole to 65'.

08/10/2013: Continue to trip in hole from 65' to top of cement at 10;830'. Circulated and conditioned mud. Pump 175 bbls 10.2 ppg spacer; 65 bbls drill water; mix and pump 134 bbls of 16.4 ppg cement; 6 bbls drill water; 16 bbls 10.2 ppg spacer and displace with 10.2 ppg WBM. Rack back cement stand and trip out of the hole to 10;147'. Squeeze cement. Shut in and wait on cement.
"},{"   ":58,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-08-11","TEXT_REMARK":"08/11/2013: Monitor shut-in well while waiting on cement. Wash down from 10;089' to 10;491' with cement diverter. Circulated hole clean and conditioned 10.2 ppg WBM. Pressure test BOPE. Function test BOPs. Function test diverter. Pull out of the hole to 9;287'.

08/12/2013: Continue to trip out of the hole with cement diverter. Function test BSR and CSR. Pick up 18-1/8" x 19-7/8" BHA and trip in hole to 10;263'. Washed down and located top of cement at 10;508'. Drill out cement to 10;545'; circulate and condition mud. Begin 22" casing test.

08/13/2013: Continue to pressure test 22" casing to 3000 psi for 30 minutes with 10.2 ppg WBM. Drill out cement with 18-1/8" x 19-7/8" assembly from 10;545' to 10;830'. Circulate and condition mud. Perform preliminary shoe test with 10.2 ppg WBM to 530 psi; 11.1 ppg equivalent. Drilled cement from 10;830' to 10;865'. Drill new formation from 10;865' to 10;875'. Circulate and condition mud. 
   
08/14/2013: Continue to circulate and condition mud. Perform shoe test with 10.2 ppg WBM to 403 psi; 10.9 ppg equivalent. Trip out of the hole with 18-1/8" x 19-7/8" BHA. Begin to run in the hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA.

08/15/2013: Continue to run in the hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA; with BOP Test/Hangoff Tool. Land hangoff tool in wellhead. Prepare to displace riser to seawater. Decision was made to resume normal operations. Pull out of the hole from 6;910' to 388' with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA; lay out BOP Test/Hangoff Tool. Function test BSR and CSR. Trip in the hole with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA to 10;763'. Begin preparations to displace well to SBM. 

08/16/2013: Displace wellbore and surface equipment from 10.2 ppg WBM to 10.4 ppg SBM. Clean pits.

08/17/2013: Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 10;875' to 11;414' with 10.4 ppg SBM. Lost returns at 11;414'; picked up 75' of bottom and pumped 100 bbl 50 ppb LCM pill. Closed annular due to falling fluid level in riser and shut the well in. Began building more SBM while monitoring the well on the BOP pressure gauge. 
"},{"   ":59,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-08-18","TEXT_REMARK":"08/18/2013: Build mud volume. Establish loss rate. Build mud volume. Open MVBR and attempt to circulate 100 bbl LCM pill out of drill pipe; close MVBR to control losses. Monitor well on BOP pressure gauge and build mud volume. Pump base oil down kill line to simulate 10.2 ppg and 10.0 ppg equivalent mud weight in the well.  Losses manageable with 10.0 ppg. Displace choke; kill and boost lines to 10.0 ppg SBM; begin to displace riser to 10.0 ppg.

08/19/2013: Continue displacing riser from 10.4 ppg to 10.0 ppg SBM. Open MVBR and finish pumping 100 bbl LCM pill out of drill string. Spot 350 bbl LCM pill on bottom. Pick up above loss zone and monitor wellbore; well static. Pull out of the hole from 11;307' to 10;951'; break circulation; monitor well; static. Trip out of the hole from 10;951' to 10;762'. Hole not taking proper fill; monitor well; static. Pump out of the hole from 10;762' to 7;649'. Circulate 10.0 ppg SBM at 7;649'.

08/20/2013: Continue to circulate 10.0 ppg SBM at 7;649'. Observe 5 bbls gain; shut well in on annular (no pressure increase noted). Monitored well on strip tank through kill line; observed a 1/2 bbl gain in 12 minutes. Closed choke and monitored pressure. Pressure increased to 56 psi on casing gauge. Displace riser; choke; kill; boost and drill pipe to 10.1 ppg SBM. Displace wellbore to 10.1 ppg at 7;620'. Flow checked well on trip tank; well static. Pump out of hole from 7;620' to 6;211'.
  
08/21/2013: Trip out of hole from 6;211' to surface. Function BSRs and CSRs. Pick up new BHA; trip in hole with 18-1/8" x 21" Drilling BHA to 7;577'.

08/22/2013: Break circulation. While circulating; a 3 bbl gain was noted in the active system. Flow checked; additional 5 bbl gain in the trip tank. Shut well in on annular and monitored pressures (no pressure increase). Closed MVBRs; monitored well on the stripping tank (well static). Opened MVBR; well static. Wash down from 7;577' to 8;080'; circulate bottoms up. Continue washing down from 8;080' to 9;023'; circulate bottoms up. Wash down from 9;023' to 9;450'; circulate bottoms up. Wash down from 9;450' to 9;849'.

08/23/2013: Continue washing down from 9;849' to 10;094'; circulate bottoms up. Wash down from 10;094' to casing shoe at 10;810'. Logged from 22" casing shoe; to 11;404'. Pick up to 11;340' and circulate bottoms up. Flow check well; well static.

08/24/2013: Pump out of hole from 11;340' to 10;630'. Begin testing BOPE with 10.1 ppg SBM to 250/9;100 psi on 6-5/8" drill pipe. 
"},{"   ":60,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-08-25","TEXT_REMARK":"08/25/2013: Completed testing BOPE with 10.1 ppg SBM to 250/ 9;100 psi on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Wash down from 10;630' to 10;920'. Activate 21" reamer. Wash and ream down from 10;920' to bottom at 11;414'. Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 11;414' to 11;557'.

08/26/2013: Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 11;557' to 11;574'. P/U to 11;560'. Wash and ream from 11;560' to 11;574'; observe 450 psi pressure loss on standpipe; troubleshoot pressure loss. Drill 11;574' to 11;579' at reduced rate with the reamer closed. P/U and ledge test reamer; reamer arms appear to be closed. Pump out of the hole from 11;579' to 6;213'.

08/27/2013: Pump out of the hole from 6;213' to 4;477'. Trip out of the hole from 4;477' to surface. 18-1/8" bit and PowerDrive bias assembly (4.67' total length) left in the hole. Pick up BOP test tool and dual cam assembly. TIH to 7;600'. 

08/28/2013: Test choke manifold valves #1 & #5 to 250 psi with 10.1 ppg SBM. Displace choke and kill lines to 6.6 ppg base oil. Attempt to test choke manifold valves #1 & #5 to 12;200 psi with base oil; no test. Displace choke and kill lines to 10.1 ppg SBM. Land BOP test tool in wellhead; drop dart; release dual cam; pressure test BSRs to 250/ 3;000 psi with 10.1 ppg SBM. Function test BSR and CSR. Pressure test choke manifold valves #1 & #5 to 250/ 9;500 psi with 10.1 ppg.

08/29/2013: Continue pressure testing choke manifold valves #1 & #5 to 250/ 9;500 psi with 10.1 ppg. Boost riser. POOH with BOP test tool and Dual Cam assembly. Perform preventive maintenance and general housekeeping while waiting on fishing tools.

08/30/2013: Perform preventative maintenance on rig floor. Make up fishing BHA. Trip in hole with fishing BHA from surface to 11;470'. Wash down from 11;470' to 11;575'. Tag top of fish; work overshot assembly over top of fish.

08/31/2013: Pump out of the hole from 11;575' to 5;313' with fishing BHA. Pull out of the hole from 5;313' to surface. No fish. Pick up cement diverter and trip in hole from surface with cement stinger to 5;004'.
"},{"   ":61,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-09-01","TEXT_REMARK":"09/01/2013: Function test BSR & CSR. Tripped in the hole from 5;004 to 10;689' with cement stinger assembly. Function tested Diverter & BOP. Troubleshoot slip joint packer. Continued to trip in the hole to locate top of fish at 11;577'. Circulated bottoms up. 

09/02/2013: Mixed; pumped and displaced 244 bbls of 17.0 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #1 from 11;569' to 10;969'. POOH with cement stinger assembly to 10;546'. Attempted to break circulation; no returns. Closed the annular BOP and waited on cement. Washed down to locate top of cement at 11;462'. Circulated bottoms up at 11;462'.

09/03/2013: Continued circulating and condtitioning mud. Mixed; pumped and displaced 107 bbls of 17.0 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #2 from 11;462' to 11;212'. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 10;590'. Closed the annular BOP and waited on cement. Flow check well - static. Washed down to locate top of cement at 11;424'. Staged up pumps and began circulating bottoms up. 

Note: Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) notified Mr. Robert Rainey (BSEE - Lafayette District) on 08/31/2013 at 8:39 PM via e-mail that the Discoverer Clear Leader's fishing attempt to recover the bit and power drive section was unsuccessful and that the forward plan will be to set a kick off plug and bypass the fish. On 09/03/2013; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE - Lafayette District) confirmed that verbal approval was granted to set a bypass plug.

09/04/2013: Continued circulating bottoms up. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 11;419'. Mixed; pumped and displaced 107 bbls of 14.6 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #3 from 11;424' to 11;174'. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 10;578'. Closed the annular BOP and waited on cement. Opened annular and flow check well - static. Washed down to locate top of cement at 11;415'. Staged up pumps and began circulating bottoms up.

Note: Suzanne Murphy received confirmation via email fromm Mr. David LeLeux on 09/04/2013 at 6:10 AM that verbal approval was granted to begin drilling open-hole bypass.

09/05/2013: Continued circulating bottoms up. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 11;395'. Mixed; pumped and displaced 107 bbls of 14.6 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #4 from 11;415' to 11;165'. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 10;544'. Closed the annular BOP and waited on cement. Opened annular and flow checked well - static. Washed down from 10;578' to 10;764'. 

09/06/2013: Continued to wash down to locate top of cement at 11;272'. Circulated the hole clean. Mixed; pumped and displaced 280 bbls of 17.0 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #5 from 11;267' to 10;600'. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 10;042'. Circulated and conditioned 10.1 ppg SBM while waiting on cement. 

09/07/2013: Continued circulating and conditioning 10.1 ppg SBM at 10;042' while waiting on cement. Flow check well - static. Washed down to locate top of cement at 10;930'. Pumped sweep and circulated bottoms up. Mixed; pumped and displaced 180 bbls of 17.0 ppg Class H cement to set balanced cement plug #6 from 10;931' to 10;483'. Picked up cement stinger assembly to 9;550' and circulated drill pipe volume. 
"},{"   ":62,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003100,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-09-08","TEXT_REMARK":"09/08/2013: Tripped out of hole from 9;950' to 3;402' and made up BOP test stands. Tripped in hole to 10;060'. Made up surface equipment and pressure tested BOPs.

09/09/2013: Function tested BOPs. TIH and tagged top of cement (Kick off plug #6). Circulated hole clean. Tripped out of hole with cement diverter. Tested 22" casing to 3;000 psi. Slipped and cut drill line. Made up 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and tripped in hole with same to 2;881'.

09/10/2013: Tripped in hole from 2;881'; tag top of cement at 10;599'. Drilled cement in 22" casing from 10;599' to 10;800'. Continued drill from 10;800' to KOP at 10;848'. Bypass 01 - control drilled from 10;848' to 10;896'. Circulated hole clean.  Performed FIT with 10.1 ppg SBM to 10.8 ppg SBM equivalent. Continued to control drill to 10;930'. Opened 21" reamer.

09/11/2013: Control drilled to 11;387' and observed partial losses; pumped LCM and drilled ahead to 11;407'. Spotted LCM pill; losses subsided while circulating hole clean. Decreased MW from 10.1 to 10.0 ppg SBM. While circulating; observed gain in active; flow checked and observed 5 bbl gain (previously saw losses of 222 bbls). Shut in well and monitored for pressure. No pressure build. Kill line static on mini strip tank. Opened annular; flow check. Well static. Continued displacing to 10.0 ppg SBM.

Note: By email dated 09/11/2013; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE - Lafayette District) granted approval to drill with 0.3 ppg margin in the 16.5" x 19" hole section as requested by Suzanne Murphy of Chevron.

09/12/2013: Completed displacement to 10.0 ppg SBM. Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 11;407' to 11;700'. 

09/13/2013: Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 11;700' to 11;997'; adjusting drilling parameters for max ROP.

Note: On 09/13/2013; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE - Lafayette District) granted verbal approval to Kenley McQueen of Chevron to set the 18" liner deeper than the permitted depth of 12;040 ft TVD by up to 500 ft TVD contingent on sending PE certification to the BSEE after hours phone.

09/14/2013: Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 11;997' to 12;190'; adjusting drilling parameters for max ROP. Incurred pressure loss on drill string. Troubleshoot on surface with no problems identified. Decision made to pull out of hole. Flow checked well; well static. Pulled out of hole wet from 12;190' to 9;692'.
"},{"   ":63,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003101,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-09-08","TEXT_REMARK":"09/08/2013: Tripped out of hole from 9;950' to 3;402' and made up BOP test stands. Tripped in hole to 10;060'. Made up surface equipment and pressure tested BOPs.

09/09/2013: Function tested BOPs. TIH and tagged top of cement (Kick off plug #6). Circulated hole clean. Tripped out of hole with cement diverter. Tested 22" casing to 3;000 psi. Slipped and cut drill line. Made up 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and tripped in hole with same to 2;881'.

09/10/2013: Tripped in hole from 2;881'; tag top of cement at 10;599'. Drilled cement in 22" casing from 10;599' to 10;800'. Continued drill from 10;800' to KOP at 10;848'. Bypass 01 - control drilled from 10;848' to 10;896'. Circulated hole clean.  Performed FIT with 10.1 ppg SBM to 10.8 ppg SBM equivalent. Continued to control drill to 10;930'. Opened 21" reamer.

09/11/2013: Control drilled to 11;387' and observed partial losses; pumped LCM and drilled ahead to 11;407'. Spotted LCM pill; losses subsided while circulating hole clean. Decreased MW from 10.1 to 10.0 ppg SBM. While circulating; observed gain in active; flow checked and observed 5 bbl gain (previously saw losses of 222 bbls). Shut in well and monitored for pressure. No pressure build. Kill line static on mini strip tank. Opened annular; flow check. Well static. Continued displacing to 10.0 ppg SBM.

Note: By email dated 09/11/2013; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE - Lafayette District) granted approval to drill with 0.3 ppg margin in the 16.5" x 19" hole section as requested by Suzanne Murphy of Chevron.

09/12/2013: Completed displacement to 10.0 ppg SBM. Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 11;407' to 11;700'. 

09/13/2013: Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 11;700' to 11;997'; adjusting drilling parameters for max ROP.

Note: On 09/13/2013; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE - Lafayette District) granted verbal approval to Kenley McQueen of Chevron to set the 18" liner deeper than the permitted depth of 12;040 ft TVD by up to 500 ft TVD contingent on sending PE certification to the BSEE after hours phone.

09/14/2013: Control drilled 18-1/8" x 21" hole section from 11;997' to 12;190'; adjusting drilling parameters for max ROP. Incurred pressure loss on drill string. Troubleshoot on surface with no problems identified. Decision made to pull out of hole. Flow checked well; well static. Pulled out of hole wet from 12;190' to 9;692'.
"},{"   ":64,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003101,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-09-15","TEXT_REMARK":"09/15/2013: Pulled out of hole from 9;692' to surface with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling assembly. Discovered wash out in pony drill collar box connection and noted two missing antenna split keys on the MWD. Trip in hole with concave mill assembly to 6;098'. Function tested blind shear rams and casing shear rams. Continue tripping in hole with concave mill assembly to 10;378'.

09/16/2013: Function tested BOPs and diverter. Continue running in hole with concave mill assembly to 12;190' and milled down to 12;191'. Pulled out of hole to surface with 17-1/2" concave mill assembly. Pick up 18-1/8" x 21" drilling assembly and run in hole to 578'.

09/17/2013: Continue running in hole with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling assembly to 12;190'. Shut in after 6 barrel gain in the active system and circulated riser volume to get 10 lb/gal mud in and out. Monitored well and it was static. Drilled down to 12;400' with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling assembly while monitoring gamma ray to locate clean shale interval for casing point.

09/18/2013: Performed static influx test with ESD of 10.18 ppg. Circulated bottoms up. Pull out of hole with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling BHA from 12;400' to surface. Run in hole with 18-1/8" x 21" reaming assembly to 1;697'.

09/19/2013: Continue tripping in hole with 18-1/8" x 21" reaming assembly to 12;296' bit depth. Ream to 12;400' bit depth. Performed static influx test and circulated bottoms up. Pulled out of hole with reaming assembly to 10;378' PBL depth and jetted the 18" supplemental adapter. Continue tripping out of hole with reaming assembly to 7;840' bit depth.
