Note: At 17:21 hrs; Mr. Kenley McQueen (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette District) to proceed with well suspension activities; to troubleshoot kill line leak.

11/26/2013: TOH and R/B the 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" BHA. Slip and cut drill line. Recalibrated drawworks and performed brake test: successful. TIH with 16" RTTS (SSC-3) to 6;421'. Shut down operations due to high winds and seas. Monitor well on trip tank: static. 

11/27/2013: Wait on weather from 00:00 hrs to 07:00 hrs. Continue TIH from 6;421' to 7;882'. Monitor well: static. Circulate and condition. Set RTTS with SSC-3 valve at 7;000' (top of RTTS @ 6;981'). Pressure test to 1;000 psi: successful. Spot Hi-Vis pill. Safety meeting with all personnel on negative test. Perform negative test and chart pressure bleed off. Monitor DP with 200 psi for 15 minutes: static. Monitor DP with 0 psi for 30 min: static. Prepare displacing riser to SW. BSR is incapable of staying in block position. Troubleshot BSR/MPR. Discuss forward plan. 

Note: At 23:51 hrs; Mr. Kenley McQueen received verbal approval from Mr. Mark Malbrue (BSEE Lafayette District) to proceed with isolating the wellbore with two barriers and pull the Subsea BOP/LMRP to troubleshoot kill line leak and blind shear rams not remaining closed when placed in block position.

11/28/2013: Prepare well for pulling BOP/LMRP. Circulate riser with 12.4 ppg SBM. P/U 16" running tool and TIH to 6;981'. Retrieve RTTS #1 and reset at 8;107'. Pressure test to 1;000 psi: successful. TOH and P/U RTTS #2. Set RTTS #2 at 6;913'. Pressure test to 1;000 psi: successful. TOH to 6;821' in preparation to perform negative test. 

11/29/2013: PJSM with all personnel on negative test. Successfully perform negative test with 132 bbls of base oil pumped down drill string and 1;425 psi on standpipe. Monitor 215 psi SPP for 15 minutes: well static. Bleed pressure to 0 psi and monitor for 30 minutes: well static. Displace choke and kill; boost line; and riser. TOOH. Begin R/U of riser handling equipment. PJSM with all personnel on pulling riser. Unlatched from Buckskin Appraisal #2 (BP02) @ 21:19 hrs. Move rig 250' west. Inspect HPWH with ROV: well static.

11/30/2013: Safety Stand-Up with all involved personnel to discuss recent safety alert related to pulling riser. Unlock and service slip joint. Remove drape hoses. PJSM on pulling riser. Pull riser from 6;344' to 1;094' (total 70 of 83 joints).
"},{"   ":76,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003102,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-12-01","TEXT_REMARK":"12/01/2013: Pull riser and BOPs from 1;094' to surface and land BOP on cart in moonpool. Skidded stack from well center to maintenance/testing area and laid out double riser joint. Began troubleshooting and repairing BOPs.

12/02/2013: Continued BOP troubleshooting and repair scope of work.

Note: On 12/2/13 at 3:13 PM; Ms. Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) provided 72 hour notice to Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE) via email that the DCL plans to stump test the BOP beginning 12/5/13. The BSEE After Hours Blackberry acknowledged receipt of the notice at 5:14 PM.

12/03/2013: Continued BOP troubleshooting and repair scope of work.

12/04/2013: Continued BOP troubleshooting and repair scope of work and began BOP pressure testing on surface. Performed surface Autoshear/Deadman test.

Note: On 11/4/13 at 7:37:30 AM; Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette District) granted approval to not retest ROV hot stab functions for stump test before resplashing stack in an email to Ms. Suzanne Murphy (Chevron). 

12/05/2013: Continued with BOP pressure tests on surface.

12/06/2013: Continued with BOP pressure tests on surface.

12/07/2013: Completed BOP pressure tests on surface and made final preparations to run the BOP/LMRP. Skidded BOP/LMRP to well center and made up same to marine riser double. Ran BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 194' to 1;844' (24 of 83 riser joints).
"},{"   ":77,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003102,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-12-08","TEXT_REMARK":"12/08/2013: Run BOP/LMRP on marine riser from 1;844' to 6;269' (total 83 jts.). Made up termination; flex; and telescoping joints to 6;388' and install drape hoses. Pressure tested choke; kill; and boost lines then displaced rigid conduit lines to BOP fluid. Made up landing joints; lowered BOP/LMRP from 6;444' to 6;473'; and installed MUX storm loops.

12/09/2013: Install SDC ring and transferred riser and BOP/LMRP load to tensioners. Landed and latched BOP to wellhead. Laid out landing joint; scope out slip joint; and install diverter. Close bind shear ram with ROV and pressure tested to 1;000 psi. Performed dead man test and pressure test below BSRs. Perform diverter flow test. Run in hole with BOP test tool and land in wellhead. Begin pressure testing BOPs; upper variable bore rams did not test.

Note: On 12/9/13 at 12:44 hrs; Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received verbal approval from Troy Trosclair (BSEE Lafayette) for a nine-day extension on the 30 day casing evaluation requirement. The casing evaluation is now due 16 days after crossing the BOP stack. Based on crossing the stack on 12/9/13; the casing evaluation is due 12/24/13.

Note: On 12/9/13 at 15:24 hrs; Suzanne Murphy received verbal approval from Marty Rinaudo (BSEE Lafayette) to proceed with SSBOP pressure testing."

12/10/2013: Continue troubleshooting pressure test on upper variable bore rams with no success. Trip out of hole with BOP test tool to surface. Rig up to pull LMRP/BOP. Wait on weather.

Note: On 12/10/13 at 15:19 hrs; Suzanne Murphy received verbal approval from David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette) to pull BOP and LMRP.

12/11/2013: Pull and lay out diverter. Unlatched BOPs from wellhead and removed drape hoses. Pulled slip joint and termination joint. Pulled LMRP/BOP on marine riser from 6;269' to 3;119'.

Note: On 12/11/13 at 8:42 hrs; Suzanne Murphy received approved RBP from David LeLeux to return to work after BOP repairs to upgrade the ram locks on 22" operators and repair leak between kill line and riser adapter on LMRP.

12/12/2013: Pull LMRP/BOP from 3;119' to surface. Land BOP on transporter and skid to maintenance area. Begin replacing rubber goods in pipe rams and conducting preventative maintenance.

12/13/2013: Continue replacing rubber goods in pipe rams; continue BOP maintenance. 

12/14/2013: Completed replacing rubber goods in pipe rams. Performed autoshear/deadman and EDS tests. Begin surface function testing of BOPs.
"},{"   ":78,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003102,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-12-15","TEXT_REMARK":"12/15/2013: Complete surface function testing of BOPs. Performed surface pressure test against 4-1/2" DP. Began surface pressure tests against 6-5/8" DP.

NOTE: On 12/15/2013; Russell Robinson (Chevron) provided a 72-hour notice to Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette District) via email of plans to latch up and begin subsea testing of DCL BOP on the afternoon of 12/18/13.

12/16/2013: Completed surface pressure test against 6-5/8" DP. Performed subsea BOP pre-deployment checks.

12/17/2013: Completed subsea BOP deployment checks. Skidded BOPs/LMRP to well center and splashed BOPs. Ran BOPs/LMRP on marine riser from surface to 3;869'.

12/18/2013: Continued running LMRP/BOP on marine riser from 3;869'. Installed drape hoses; riser jewelery. Moved rig into position for BOP latch up on wellhead; landed and latched BOPs on wellhead and verified swallow with ROV. Perform 100 klbs overpull test. Performed slump test. Transferred riser load to tensioners.

12/19/2013: Installed diverter. Performed deadman test and tested BSR to 1;000 psi. Performed ROV function test (closed BSR) and tested BSRs to 1;000 psi. TIH with Multi Purpose Tool (MPT) to retrieve Nominal Bore Protector (NBP) from surface to 6;820' stinger depth. Latch NBP and POOH with NBP to 281'. 

NOTE: On 12/19/13 at 11:46 hrs; Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received approval via email from David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette District) for an extension on the 30 day casing evaluation requirement. The casing evaluation will be due 16 days after crossing the BOP stack with the drilling assembly.

12/20/2013: Continued to POOH with NBP from 281' to surface. TIH with Dual Cam and BOP Test Tool to 6;713'. Performed Accumulator drawdown test. Land BOP Test Tool in wellhead; pressure test BOP with seawater. Release from Dual Cam tool. 

12/21/2013: Pressure tested BSRs. Performed diverter function & flow through test. Engage Dual Cam tool. Function tested BOPs. TOH with Dual Cam and BOPTT from 6;808' to surface. Pick up Nominal Bore Protector (NBP); TIH from surface to 6;810; installed NBP and TOH with running tool. P/U and TIH with RTTS SSCII overshot assembly to 6;698'. Began displacing riser/choke/kill/boost/drill pipe from 8.6 ppg seawater to 12.4 ppg SBM.
"},{"   ":79,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003102,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-12-22","TEXT_REMARK":"12/22/2013: Displaced the riser from 8.6 ppg seawater to 12.4 ppg SBM. TIH with the RTTS Retrieval Tool from 6;698' to 6;896'. Unseated and retrieved RTTS #2 (upper) and TOH from 7;683' to surface. TIH with the RTTS Retrieval Tool from surface to 8;109'. Circulate and conditioned 12.4 ppg mud. Performed 22" casing pressure test to 5;400 psi for 30 min. Unseated RTTS #1 (lower); circulated and conditioned mud at 12.4 ppg.

12/23/2013: Continued circulating bottoms up. TOH with RTTS #1 (lower) from 8;996' to surface. Rebooted Node #1 per OEM procedure with no issues. Function tested BSR & CSR. Made up and TIH with 14.5" x 16.5" drilling BHA from surface to 13;097' (circulate and conditioned mud at 11;068' and 13;097').

12/24/2013: Continued TIH with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 13;097' to 16;029'. TOH from 16;029' to 15;368'. Activated reamer and performed pull test against 16" casing shoe. Continued TIH with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 15;529' to 16;842'. Washed and reamed down with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 16;842' to 17;243'; worked string up/down with intermittent stalling and packing off. Pumped sweep and circulated well clean. Observed cavings on bottoms up. Continued washing and reaming down from 17;243' to 17;779'.

12/25/2013: Continued washing and reaming down with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 17;779' to 18;850'. Pumped sweep; and continued circulating well clean; continue to observe cavings on bottoms up. Decision made to POOH. Backream out from 18;850' to 18;583'. 

12/26/2013: Continue to backream from 18;583' to 15;527'. Pull test reamer against the 16" shoe; closed reamer. TOH with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 15;527' to 15;333'; and observed overpull. Pumped sweep and circulated well clean; observed cavings on bottoms up. Backream from 15;333' to 14;296'.

NOTE: Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. Marty Rinaudo (BSEE Lafayette District) to begin to plug back the 16.5" hole section on 12/26/2013 at 6:50:29 PM CST.

12/27/2013: Continued backreaming with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 14;296' to 12;958'. TOH with 14.5" x 16.5" BHA from 12;958' to surface. Made up and TIH from surface to 16;451' with 4-1/2" cement stinger. 

12/28/2013: Circulated bottoms up. Spot 35-bbl; 14.5 ppg viscous pill at 16;491'. Made up cement stand and rigged up cementing lines. Pump 150 bbls 14.4 ppg cement spacer. Mixed and pumped 370 bbls (2;079 cu ft) 17.0 ppg cement kick-off plug from 16;356' to 14;857'. POOH from 16;356' to 13;817'; circulated bottoms up. WOC. TIH with cement stinger from 13;817' to 14;708'. Washed down from 14;708' to 15;340'. Circulated bottoms up.
"},{"   ":80,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003102,"WAR_START_DT":"2013-12-29","TEXT_REMARK":"12/29/2013: Circulated wellbore clean at 15;424'. Inserted Nerf ball into the drill string and circulated bottoms up. TOH from 13;828' to surface with 4.5" diverter x 4.5" DP cementing assembly. Slipped and cut drill line; Picked up 14.5" x 16.5" Rotary steerable BHA and ran in hole to 428'.

12/30/2013: TIH from 428' to 14;530' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly on 6 5/8" drill pipe.  Made up MDDM and washed down from 14;530' and tagged TOC at 14;909' with 20 Klbs down. Drilled cement from 14;909' to 15;168'. Circulated Bottoms up. Performed casing test - 5400 psi/ 30 min with 12.4 ppg SBM.

NOTE:
Chevron Operations Engineer Suzanne M. Murphy received approval for the Permit to Bypass has been approved as of 2013-12-30 15:08:25 by Mr. Beau Boudreaux of the BSEE.

12/31/2013: TIH from 14;713' to 15;057' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly. Washed down from 15;057' to 15;168'. Drilled firm cement from 15;168' to 15;328'. Circulated at 15;328' and displaced the wellbore and choke; kill and boost lines from 12.4 ppg SBM to 11.8 ppg SBM. Drilled cement from 15;328' to 15;430'. Initiated KO at 15;430' and drilled 14.5" hole to 15;505'; down-linking as required for directional control. Circulated bottoms up - 95% formation once bottoms up at surface. Performed FIT to 13.1 ppg EMW. Tripped out of hole to 14;778'.

01/01/2014: Pressure and function tested BOP's on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Drilled 14.5" x 16.5" hole from 15;505' to 15;990'; down-linking as required for directional control. 

01/02/2014: Drilled from 15;990' to 16;681' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly. Drilled from 16;681' to 16;921' while increasing MW from 11.8 ppg to 12.0 ppg. Drilled from 16;921' to 17;464'; increasing MW at 17;200' to 12.2 ppg. Down-linked as required for directional control. 

01/03/2014: Drilled from 17;464' to 18;190' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly; increasing MW to 12.3 ppg at 17;610'. Drilled from 18;190' to 18;565'. Down-linked and took surveys as per program.

01/06/2014: Drilled from 20;214' to 20;458' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly. Pumped 100 bbl; 13.4 ppg high viscosity sweep and circulated the wellbore clean. Spotted 30 bbl; 17 ppg pill on bottom. Trip out of hole from 20;452' to 7;984' with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly on 6-5/8" DP. Functioned diverter at 7;984'; Pulled out of hole from 7;984' to 7;805' and functioned BOPs on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Pulled out of hole from 7;805' to 5;970'. Functioned BSRs at 5;970' bit depth. Continued to pull out of hole from 5;970' to 1;173'.

01/07/2013: Pull out of hole with 14.5" x 16.5" RS drilling assembly from 1;173' to surface and rack back BHA. Pick up 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA; function tested reamer at surface. Trip into the hole with 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA on 6-5/8" DP from surface to 8;000'.

01/08/2014: Trip into the hole with 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA on 6-5/8" DP from 8;000' to 15;378'. Performed reamer pull test against 16" casing shoe. Trip into the hole from 15;378' to 17;191'; and encountered tight hole. Washed and reamed from 17;191' to 19;496'; verifying hole is opened to 16.5".

01/09/2014: Washed and reamed from 19;496' to 19;960'; with the 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA.

01/10/2014: Washed and reamed from 19;960' to 20;315' with the 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA.

NOTE: On 01/10/2014 at 13:45 hrs; Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received approval via email from Mr. Beau Boudreaux (BSEE Lafayette) to set the 13-7/8" liner shallow at ±20;348' MD  20;341' TVD.

01/11/2014: Washed and reamed from 20;315' to 20;397' with the 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA. Circulated and conditioned wellbore prior to pull out of the hole. Trip out of the hole from 20;397' to 20;318'; where drillstring became stuck. Attempt to free the drillstring; drillstring came free. Trip out of the hole from 20;271' to 17;362'.
"},{"   ":83,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003103,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-01-12","TEXT_REMARK":"01/12/2014: Continue tripping out of the hole with the 14.5" x 16.5" Hole Opening BHA from 17;362' to 7;736'. Performed BOP function test on 6-5/8" DP; function tested the diverter. Trip out of the hole from 8;008' to surface. BHA left in hole: 14.5" PDC Bit; Bit Sub; 14.5" x 16.5" Reamer and 9-1/2" Drill Collar (~57'); (20;231' estimated top of fish). Serviced rig. Function tested BSRs/CSRs. Performed PMs. Pick up and trip into the hole with 4-1/2" cement stinger from surface to 6;594'.

Note: Suzanne Murphy (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. Mike Hebert (BSEE Lafayette) at 19:37 hrs on 01/12/2014 to proceed with spotting cement plug .

01/13/2014: Trip into the hole with the 4-1/2" cement stinger on 6-5/8" DP from 6;594' to 16;303'. Circulated and conditioned; spotted hi-vis pill. Trip out of the hole from 16;303' to 16;168'. Rig up poor boy cement stand; and chicksans. Tested lines; Pumped 370 bbls/ 2;057 sxs of 17 ppg Class H cement. Displaced and spotted cement plug at 16;168' to ~14;616'. Trip out of the hole from 16;168' to 13;952'; and circulated buttoms up. Picked up BOP test assembly. Performed BOP pressure test on 6-5/8" drill pipe.

01/14/2013: Pressure tested BOPs on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Performed choke manifold tests offline. Function tested BOPs on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Function tested diverter. Rig down BOP testing assembly. Trip into the hole from 13;952' to 14;456' with the 4-1/2" cement stinger. Washed down from 14;456' and tagged top of cement at 14;956'. Flow checked; pull out of the hole from 14;956' to surface with the 4-1/2" cement stinger on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Attempted to pressure test 16" x 22" casing to 5;400 psi. Test was unsuccessful. Pick up 16" RTTS assembly.

Note: Suzanne Murphy received verbal approval to proceed with planned bypass #4 from David LeLeux (BSEE Lafayette) at 15:38 hrs on 01/14/2014.

01/15/2014: Trip into the hole with 16" RTTS to 7;073' bit depth (6;890' packer depth). Set RTTS; tested packer and 22" casing x 16" liner top. Trip out of the hole from 6;885' to 6;073' with the RTTS overshot to test BSRs. Tested BSRs to 250/5;400 psi (good test). Trip into the hole to RTTS; unseated and continued trip into the hole to 14;524' (bit depth)/ 14;336' (packer depth). Set RTTS and attempted to perform 16" casing test 2 times (failed test).

01/16/2014: Continued searching for the leak path in 16" casing using the RTTS packer on 6-5/8" drill pipe. Pressure tested casing from 14;525' (bit depth) to 7;068' (bit depth). Determined that the leak path is between 8;077' and 8;052'. Tripped out of hole from 8;077' to surface and laid down the RTTS assembly. Performed planned rig maintenance. Prepared rig floor for rigging up wireline.

Note: On 1/16/2014 at 17:15 hrs; Suzanne Murphy notified Mr. David LeLeux that a leak was found in the 16.04" 109.6# casing section; below the 16" hanger at ~8;050'. Notified BSEE of the plan forward to run wireline logs to pinpoint leak; evaluate condition of casing; and determine remedial options.

01/17/2014: Performed 30 and 90 day planned maintenance; serviced MDDM and both PRSs. Rigged up Schlumberger wireline and ran in hole from surface to 14;550'. Attempted to log 16" casing with caliper log from 14;500' to 12;870'. 

01/18/2014: Pulled out of hole with SLB 56-arm caliper log toolstring on wireline from 12;870' to surface. Decision made to run Weatherford 60-arm caliper log. Made up Weatherford caliper tool and troubleshot same. RIH with caliper tool string to 8;200'; logged up from 8;200' to 7;900' with Weatherford caliper tool. Ran in hole from 7;900' to 14;500'. Logged up from 14;500' to 10;500' with Weatherford 60-arm caliper tool.
"},{"   ":84,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003103,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-01-19","TEXT_REMARK":"01/19/2014: Logged up from 10;500' to 6;750' with Weatherford 60-arm caliper tool; pulled out of hole with the Weatherford caliper toolstring. Ran in hole with the Gyro-tool from surface to 6;760'. Perform 16" Gyro logs from 6;760' to 14;500'. Pulled out of hole with Gyro from 14;500' to surface; taking check shots as needed. Rigged down SLB wireline equipment. Function tested BSRs/CSRs. Picked up and tripped in hole with the HAL FasDrill Packer on 6-5/8" drill pipe from surface to 6;950'. Set Packer @ 6;950'. Spot 17.0 ppg pill on top of packer. Picked up to 6;760' and displaced Choke/Kill/Boost/drill pipe and Riser from 12.4 ppg to 11.3 ppg. Flow checked; static. Pulled out of hole with FasDrill running tool on 6-5/8" drill pipe from 6;760' to 4;687'.

01/20/2014: Tripped out of hole with Fasdrill running tool on 6-5/8" drill pipe from 4;687' to surface. Picked up and tripped in hole with the Dril-Quip Multi-Purpose Tool on 6-5/8" drill pipe from surface to 6;554'. Washed down from 6;554' to 6;665'. Retrieve NBP from the HPWH. Tripped out of hole with the Dril-Quip NBP on 6-5/8" drill pipe from 6;512' to surface; and racked back. Tripped in hole with the Dril-Quip MPT and retrieve the 16" Casing Seal Assembly. Pulled out of hole with the 16" Seal Assembly from 6;921' to 6;745'. Circulated bottoms up. Pulled out of hole from 6;745' to 6;080'; performed injection test. Pulled out of hole from 6;080' to surface; laid down MPT and 16" SA. Picked up and tripped in hole with the 4-1/2" cement diverter on 6-5/8" drill pipe from surface to 286'.

01/21/2013: Tripped in hole with 4-1/2" cement diverter from 286' to 6;587'. Function BOPs and diverter. Wait on orders from Chevron office to commence cement job. Rigged up to pump cement job; held PJSM on cementing; pumped bullhead cement job - 549 bbls (3;082 cu ft) 13.5 ppg Lehigh Class H cement pumped at 00:00 hrs.

01/22/2014: Pump remaining 8 bbls (45 cu ft) of cement. Total cement pumped 557 bbls (3;127 cu ft) 13.5 ppg Lehigh Class H cement. Bullheaded 40 bbls of seawater spacer with retarder. Pumped 8 bbls of seawater from the cement unit and displaced spacer to the rig floor. Displaced cement with 175 bbls of 9.0 ppg SBM. Cement in place at 01:00 hrs. Monitored well while waiting on cement to set up.

01/23/2014: Monitored riser on trip tank and well on shut-in stand-pipe and BOP HPHT pressure gauges while waiting on cement to set up. Reversed out 9.0 ppg SBM. Circulated 11.3 ppg SBM all the way around. Circulated bottoms up. Performed casing integrity test to 1700 psi for 30 minutes with 11.3 ppg SBM.

Stabbed seal stem into TBR and landed out hanger in HPWH. Begin pumping 6.6 ppg base oil down kill line to spot base oil in riser for reducing hydrostatic in riser to seawater equivalent.

03/04/2014: Continued pumping 6.6 ppg base oil down kill line to spot in riser (reduced the HP at the wellhead by ~1;320 psi). Made several attempts to set 14" seal assembly in HPWH. Unable to achieve a good pressure test on the seal assembly. Displaced riser back to 12.4 ppg SBM. Pick up to release CHSART from 14" hanger. Circulate bottoms up. POOH with CHSART on 6-5/8" landing string to surface. P/U and TIH with the Dril-Quip mill/flush tool assembly from surface to 3;201'.

03/05/2014: Functioned BSR & CSR. Contine TIH with Dril-Quip mill and flush assembly on 6-5/8" DP from 3;201' to 7;054' and landed out on casing hanger. P/U 14" seal assembly on Dril-Quip Seal Assembly Running Tool and continue TIH from 3;152' to 9;762'. P/U from 9;762' to 9;621' to space out 14" seal assembly above BOP. 

03/06/2014: Displaced kill line and riser from 12.4 ppg SBM to 7.2 ppg base oil (contaminated with SBM from previous attempt to set seal assembly) and 6.6 ppg base oil; reducing the HP at the wellhead by ~1;320 psi. Set the 14" seal assembly with 240k.lbs; and test to 10k psi - good test. Sheared the running tool from the seal assembly and begin to u-tube base oil from riser up kill line filling the riser with 12.4 ppg SBM. Close annular and pump 12.4 ppg SBM down the choke line and up the kill line till MW in/out = 12.4 ppg. Open annular and circulated and conditioned riser until MW in/out = 12.4 ppg. Re-tested the 14" seal assembly to 10k psi with 12.4 ppg SBM - good test. Performed flow check - well static; and TOH with the SART on 6-5/8" DP from 9;634' to 9;169'.

03/07/2014: POOH with SART on 6-5/8" DP from 9;169' to 6;514' and function tested the diverter. Continued to POOH with the SART to 3;152' and R/B the SART. P/U and TIH on 6-5/8" DP from 3;152' to 9;690' (bit depth) to land Lead Impression Tool (LIT) in wellhead. Functioned lead blocks in the profile. Begin TOH from 9;690' to 9;549' and function tested the BOP. Continue to TOH with the LIT on 6-5/8" DP from 9;549' to 3;152' and R/B LIT. "},{"   ":114,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003106,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-07-27","TEXT_REMARK":"07/27/2014: Continued TOH with 8-1/2" drilling BHA from 20;360' to 14;612'. "},{"   ":116,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003106,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-08-10","TEXT_REMARK":"08/10/2014: Ran the BOP/LMRP on riser from 5;144' to 6;460'. 08/14/2014: TOH from 174' (MPT depth 140') to surface with the MPT assembly and performed rig maintenance; general housekeeping and PMs on the rig floor.

08/15/2014: TIH from surface with fishing assembly and tagged fish at 154'. Made several fishing attempts to retrieve fish. Decision made to pull riser to retrieve fish. Displaced C&K; boost lines; and the riser from 14.5 ppg SBM to seawater. Circulate until seawater = seawater.

08/16/2014: TIH with fishing assembly from surface to 154' to confirm location of fish after displacement. Closed and blocked the BSR and TOH to surface. Flow check the well - static. Unlatched the LMRP from the BOP stack at 01:55 hrs and moved the rig 325' west of location. TIH with fishing assembly and confirmed that the fish was still lodged in the slip joint. Continued to perform fishing operations to attempt to free fish.

"},{"   ":124,"WELL_NAME":"  001aa","API12":608084003106,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-10-05","TEXT_REMARK":"10/05/2014: TIH from 21;917' to 24;770' with 9-3/8" EZSV/MSD on tapered drill string. "},{"   ":127,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-09-07","TEXT_REMARK":"09/07/2014: Ran 22" casing on landing string to 10;299' then washed down to 10;437'. 09/08/2014: Pumped 1316 bbls (7;388.8 cu ft) of 14.0 ppg Lead Slurry followed by 277 bbls (1276.4 cu ft) of 16.0 ppg Tail Slurry. Dropped dart and displaced drill string with 266 bbls seawater to latch dart. Displace an additional 30 bbls of seawater after latching dart to place tail cement slurry. Verified floats are holding and the ROV closed all 4 conductor valves. Slacked off to neutral weight to check for subsidence. None observed with ROV. POOH with landing string and inner string and R/B.

09/09/2014: Prepare rig floor for riser running operations. Skid BOP to well center and M/U riser pup and slick joint. Splash BOP and test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines. Good test. Run riser to 733'.

09/10/2014: Continue running riser to 2;353'. Test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines at 1;003'; 1;903'. Good tests. Began test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines at 2;353'.

09/11/2014: Complete testing of choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines at 2;353'. Good test. Continue running riser to 5;053' and testing choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines. Good test. Crew greased choke manifold and began testing.

09/12/2014: Pressure test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines at 5;053'. Continue running riser to 6;773' then M/U riser telescopic joint. Latch into HFGN and pressure test choke; kill; boost and rigid conduit lines. Good test. Move rig over location and prepare for latch up. Continue testing choke manifold.

09/13/2014: Crew flushed the rigid conduit lines. ROV observed a leak from the Blue Pod manifold. Crew troubleshot the leak on the Pod and the rig was moved back to the safe zone 500' from wellhead. The decision was made to recover the BOP to surface to repair the leaking SPM on the Blue Pod. Pull BOP to 5;143'.
"},{"   ":128,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-09-14","TEXT_REMARK":"09/14/2014: Finished repairing HPU supply valve and pulled riser/BOP from 5;143' to 3;163'.

Splashed BOP while testing choke/kill lines; boost lines and rigid conduit. Ran BOP on marine riser from 193' to 1;003' and tested choke/kill lines; boost lines and rigid conduit.

09/19/2014: Continue running BOPs on riser from 2;443' to 3;883'. Pressure test choke/kill; boost; and conduit lines. Continue running riser.

09/20/2014: Ran BOPs on riser to 6;763'.  Test choke/kill; boost; and conduit lines.
"},{"   ":129,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-09-21","TEXT_REMARK":"09/21/2014: Finish running riser and BOP. Install riser jewelry. Pressure test choke/kill; boost; and rigid conduits. Position rig over wellhead and record slope indicator readings. Land and latch BOPs in preparation to start integration acceptance testing. Unlatch wellhead connector and remove BOPs. (Integrated Acceptance Testing Requirement) Relatch BOPs to HPWH. Adjust tensioners; perform EDS #3 (Integrated Acceptance Testing Requirement). Troubleshoot riser recoil system.

09/22/2014: Continue with Integrated Acceptance Testing. Perform EDS #3 to retest riser recoil system - good test. Latch LMRP to BOP. Perform EHBS intervention tests for BOP initial latch up. Laid out landing joint and remove riser running tool.

09/23/2014: Installing diverter and test same. Rig down riser handling equipment and rig up pipe handling equipment. ROV pumped shear rams closed. Pressure tested 22" Casing/Blind Shear rams to 1800 psi for 30 min - good test. TIH with BOP test tool to 7;316'.

09/24/2014: Pressure test BOPs per PDC procedure. Test pressures 250/7500 psi against pipe rams; 250/6500 psi against annulars. TOH with BOPTT/painted stand. Verify ram space out and TIH with dual cam tool to 2;970'.

09/25/2014: TIH with dual cam tool. Seat dart and release dual cam tool. Complete BOP pressure testing per PDC procedure - 250/7500 psi against BSRs - good test. Perform function test on Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod. Perform Accumulator Drawdown Test - good test. Function BSRs close via acoustic pod. Pressure test to 1;000 psi - good test. POOH with test assembly and rack back same.

09/26/2014: Rig up to test top drive IBOP and choke/kill manifold. Perform rig maintenance on elevated back-up tong (EBT).

09/27/2014: Continue troubleshooting EBT. M/U 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and TIH. Set wear sleeve in wellhead. Held pre-spud meetings. TIH to 10;280'. Continue pressure testing choke/kill manifold.
"},{"   ":130,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-09-28","TEXT_REMARK":"09/28/2014: Continue pressure testing choke and kill manifold.

Note: Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mark Malbrue (BSEE) to run the backup 18" casing hanger; which has an 18" P-110 pup joint attached; rather than the primary hanger; which had an 18" HPQ-125 pup joint attached.

10/11/2014: Tripped out of hole and replaced PBL sub. Tripped in the hole with cleanout BHA to 7;940'. Began pressure testing BOPs on 6-5/8" 34# drill pipe using Driller's panel; Blue Pod.
"},{"   ":132,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-10-12","TEXT_REMARK":"10/12/2014: Commenced pressure testing of BOP on 6-5/8" drill pipe from Driller's Panel; Blue Pod. Function tested Diverter and BOP. Tripped in the hole with cleanout BHA to 12;569' with pumps off to simulate casing run.

10/13/2014: Tripped in the hole with cleanout BHA to 12;697'. Tagged with 20k down. Washed and reamed down to 13;525' Bit Depth (Reamer Depth 13;509'). Pumped sweep and circulated bottoms up. Displaced well to 10.4 ppg SBM. Worked stand till no drag or torque seen. Pumped and backreamed out of hole to 12;441' due to drag while trying to pull out of hole.

10/14/2014: Continued working pipe through section and washing and reaming through tight spots. Trip out of hole and wash 18" SA.

10/15/2014: Continued to trip out of hole with 18-1/8" X 21" drilling assembly from 8;734' to surface. Pull wear bushing with 55k overpull. R/U and run 17-7/8" x 18" casing from surface to 2;981'.

10/16/2014: Finish running in the hole with 18" casing. Make up casing hanger and tripped in with 18" casing on 6-5/8" landing string to 11;097'. 

10/17/2014: Run and land 17-7/8" x 18" casing. 17-7/8" shoe setting depth at 13;300'. Pumped 204 bbls 16.0 ppg cement (177 bbls/ 994 cu ft Annular Volume); displaced cement to 13;200' inside 17-7/8". Cement in place at 12:40 hrs. Set Drill Quip seals and test same to 1;565 psi.

10/18/2014: Racked back cement head and tripped out of hole. Test 17-7/8" x 18" casing and BSR to 250/1;565 psi - good test. Function test BSRs and CSRs. 
"},{"   ":133,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-10-19","TEXT_REMARK":"10/19/2014: Slipped and cut drill line. Tripped in hole with 16.5" x 19" BHA. Function tested diverter from subsea panel; and then tested BOPs from Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod. 

10/20/2014: Retested BOPs from Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod. Repaired a leaking regulator on the diverter; and then functioned diverter from both Toolpusher's and Driller's panels.

Note: Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from David LeLeux (BSEE) on 10/20/2014 @ 13:17 hrs to proceed with drilling out the shoe of the 18" casing; should the RPD not be approved in time.

10/21/2014: Complete testing surface equipment; and then continued tripping in hole with 16.5" x 19" BHA. Weighted up mud from 10.4 ppg to 11.0 ppg and began drilling cement from 13;200' to 13;278'.

10/22/2014: Continued drilling shoe track; and then cleaned out rathole. Drilled 10' of new formation; circulated clean; and the prepared to perform FIT. Successfully performed FIT to 12.2 ppg; 850 psi; and then weighted up from 11.0 ppg to 11.5 ppg mud.

10/23/2014: Finished weighting up to 11.5 ppg mud; then washed and reamed back to 13;610'. Began seeing drag while washing; so attempted to POOH to simulate connection. Attempted to trip back to bottom; taking weight early. Pumped weighted sweep; and circulated around. Made decision to POOH and set cement kickoff plug. 

10/24/2014: Continued pumping out of the hole to 11;300'; and then pulled out of hole to surface. RIH with 4.5" cement stinger to 912'. Function tested CSR and BSR from Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod.

10/25/2014: Performed trip drill. Continued TIH to bottom; encountering resistance at 13;092'. Washed down into position and pumped a 250 bbl cement kickoff plug. POOH to 11;554' to WOC.
"},{"   ":134,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004700,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-10-26","TEXT_REMARK":"10/26/2014: TOH with cement stinger assembly and rigged up to run 16.5" x19" BHA. Held trip drills with A and B crews. Tripped in hole with 16.5" x 19" BHA. 

Note: Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from David Leleux (BSEE) on 10/26/2014 to proceed with Bypass Operations.

10/27/2014: Function tested BSRs/CSRs from Driller's panel; Yellow Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod. Held trip drill with A crew. Continue tripping in hole below BOP and then function tested BOPs from Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Subsea's panel; Yellow Pod. Performed diverter test from Toolpusher's panel. TIH to TOC at 12;957'. Began drilling cement and kicked off at 13;340'. Continued drilling from 13;340' to 13;380'.

10/28/2014: Tested BOP acoustic system. Continued drilling from 13;380' to 14;215'. 

Note: Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from David Leleux (BSEE) to not to perform an FIT in the bypassed hole section due to hole stability issues. FIT taken previously when initial drill out of 18" shoe used (12.2 ppg EMW).

10/29/2014: Continued drilling 16.5" x 19" hole section from 14;215' to 15;862'.

10/30/2014: Continued drilling 16.5" x 19" hole section from 15;862' to 16;743' with 11.5 ppg MW. Spotted 16 ppg pill in rathole. POOH to 13;180'.

10/31/2014: POOH with drilling assembly to surface; washing supplemental adapter on the way out of the hole. Rigged up to run 16.04" casing; and then ran to 1;018'. 

11/01/2014: Continued picking up and running 16.04" casing from 1;018' to 6;465'. Functioned BSRs/CSRs from Driller's pane; Blue Pod; and Subsea's panel; Yellow Pod.
"},{"   ":135,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-10-26","TEXT_REMARK":"10/26/2014: TOH with cement stinger assembly and rigged up to run 16.5" x19" BHA. Held trip drills with A and B crews. Tripped in hole with 16.5" x 19" BHA.

10/29/2014: Continued drilling 16.5" x 19" hole section from 14;215' to 15;862'.

10/30/2014: Continued drilling 16.5" x 19" hole section from 15;862' to 16;743' with 11.5 ppg MW. Spotted 16 ppg pill in rathole. POOH to 13;180'.

"},{"   ":136,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-11-02","TEXT_REMARK":"11/02/2014: Continued picking up and running 16" casing from 6;465' to 9;245'. Picked up 16" liner hanger and made up to casing string. Ran in hole with 6-5/8" landing string from 9;425' to 11;701'.

11/03/2014: Continued to run in hole with 16" casing on 6-5/8" landing string from 11;701' to 15;029'. Made up cement stand and landed out 16" hanger in SA - 16" shoe depth at 16;585' MD. Performed cementing operations as planned; pumping 206 bbls; 1156 cu ft; of annular cement volume. Displaced cement with 11.5 ppg SBM. Set and tested 16" seal assembly as per procedure. Performed Diverter function test from Driller's panel. Displaced landing string with 8" nerf ball to clean pipe. Began testing BOP on 6-5/8" drill pipe from Subsea control panel; Blue Pod.

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received email confirmation from Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE) on 11/03/2014 at 08:39 AM to delay BOP function testing due on 11/03/2014 until 11/04/2014 due to ongoing cementing operations.

11/04/2014: Continued pressure testing BOP on 6-5/8" drill pipe from Subsea control panel; Blue Pod. Performed BOP function test from Driller's panel; Yellow Pod. Performed Diverter function test from Subsea control panel. Pressure tested Kelly Hose; Stand pipe Valve; Upper; Lower and Manual IBOP. Pulled out of hole with 16" casing running assembly from 7;049' to 2;255'.

11/05/2014: Continued to trip out of hole with 16" casing running tool. Rigged up to run BHA. Picked up and ran 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly. Function tested BSR/CSR from Driller's panel and Subsea panel on both Blue and Yellow Pods. Pressure tested 16" casing and BSR to 3;500 psi. Set wear bushing and continued TIH to 12;053'.

11/06/2014: Continued to TIH with 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly from 12;053' to 16;027'. Wash and ream from 16;027' to 16;340'. Tag TOC 16;340'. Conducted choke drill. Drill cement and upper float equipment. Circulate 11.7 ppg SBM around. Continued drilling lower float equipment and firm cement in shoe track to 16;555'.

11/07/2014: Drilled out 16" casing to shoe at 16;585'. Reamed down and drilled out cement in rat hole to 16;689'. Pulled up into casing shoe and troubleshoot issue with upper and lower IBOP not functioning open. Repaired IBOP and then continued to ream down; drilling cement to 16;720'. Washed and reamed rat hole to 16;743'. Drilled 10' new formation to 16;753'. Pumped sweep and circulated bottoms up. Attempted to perform LOT with a pressure of 1;460 psi. At 1;290 psi; pressure fell off suddenly to 1;000 psi and stabilized at 700 psi. Target LOT was 13.4 ppg EMW.

11/08/2014: ROV inspected Riser and BOP. Continued to circulate B/U. Pump slug and TOH with 16-1/2" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly from 16;553' to surface. TIH with 16" HES FastDrill packer from surface to 1;803'. Decision made to run RTTS; TOH with 16" FastDrill. M/U 16" RTTS and TIH with same to 3;085'. Held Trip Drills with both crews.
"},{"   ":137,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-11-09","TEXT_REMARK":"11/09/2014: Continued to trip with Retrievable Test-Treat-Squeeze (RTTS) packer from 3;085' to 7;480'. Set RTTS and pressure test 16" seal assembly to 3;500 psi with 11.7 ppg SBM. Tripped out with RTTS from 7;480' to surface. Tripped in with 4-1/2" cementing stinger from surface to 16;753'.

11/10/2014: Spotted 40 bbl Hi-Vis pill in open hole. Space out mule shoe @ 16;635'; mix and pump 541 sacks 16.4 ppg Class H cement and displace same with 11.7 ppg SBM. Spot balanced cement plug from 16;635' to 16;135'. Tripped out from 16;635' to 15;393' and began to squeeze 22 bbls of cement away; holding 1;550 psi. Held pressure for 5-1/2 hours. Inserted 8" nerf ball into string and circulated 1.5 times the string volume. POOH from 15;393' to 6;407'.

11/11/2014: Continued tripping with 4-1/2" stinger assembly from 6;407' to surface. Slip and cut drill line. Tripped with 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly from surface to 1;193'.

Note: On 11/11/2014; Mr. Sheldon Langdon (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. Mike Lefleur (BSEE) for a 24 hour extension on the weekly BOP function test to continue with repair of the rig's HydraRacker.

11/12/2014: Continued tripping with 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly from 1;183' to 15;779'. Performed BOP function test from Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod.  Conducted choke drill with drill crew and key business partners. Continued tripping with 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly from 15;779' to 16;020'. Wash from 16;020' to 16;139' (TOC). Drill out cement from 16;139' to 16;432'.

11/13/2014: Continued drilling cement from 16;462' to 16;753'. Drilled 10' of new formation to 16;763'. Performed FIT at 16;585' MD with 11.7 ppg SBM to 1;300 psi; 13.2 EMW. Opened 16-1/2" reamer and drilled 14-1/2" x 16" hole section from 16;763' to 16;820'.

11/14/2014: Continued drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 16;820' to 17;200'. Tripped from 17;051' to 16;452'. Repair upper IBOP actuator on Main TDX 1250. At 17;149'; rotary stalled out with 48;000 ft/lbs of torque while maintaining full circulation rate and full returns. Reduced pump rate to 200 gm and work pipe free with 80k overpull; activating jars up x2; rotation and reciprocation established. Pump 13.8 ppg weighted sweep and circulate same above BOP.

11/15/2014: Continued drilling 14-/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 17;200' to 17;705'. Wash and ream through tight spots at 17;647' to 17;670'. Weight up active system to 12.2 ppg.
"},{"   ":138,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-11-16","TEXT_REMARK":"11/16/2014: Continued drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 17;705' to 17;721'. At 17;713' encountered losses at 5 bbl/min. Well was static with pumps off. Tripped from 17;721 to 17;265' and spotted 100 bbls of 80 lb/bbl LCM pill and allowed LCM pill to soak. Staged mud pumps up to 1;000 gpm to establish loss rate; no losses noted. Tripped in from 17;265' to 17;574' and washed and ream from 17;574' to 17;702'; establishing flow rate vs loss rate. Continued drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 17;721' to 17;885'.

11/17/2014: Continued drilling 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" hole section from 17;885' to section TD at 17;930'. Pumped out of hole from 17;930' to 17;785'. Index lower reamer at 17;785' bit depth and reamed 14-1/2" rat hole with 16-1/2" lower reamer from 17;807' to 17;898' lower reamer depth. Bit depth 17;930'. Pumped 200 bbls Hi-Vis weighted sweep and circulate hole clean at 17;930'. Circulated and spotted 200'/ 53 bbls of weighted pill across salt zone. Pumped out of hole from 17;930' to 16;563' and circulated bottoms up. Began pressure testing BOPs from Driller's panel; Yellow Pod; to 250/5;800 psi.

11/18/2014: Finished pressure testing BOPs. Function tested BOPs from Driller's panel; Yellow Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod. Tripped in with 14-1/2" x 16-1/2" drilling assembly from 16;548' to 17;700'. 

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received email approval from Mr. Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) on 11/18/2014 for a 24 hour extension on the BSR/CSR function test.

11/19/2014: Staged pumps up to 1;100 gpm and made several attempt to wash through tight spots from 17;833' to 17;845' (could not trip through but could ream through). Circulated bottoms up and spotted 56 bbls of 15.0 ppg mud at 17;930'. Pulled to 17;713' and spotted 70 bbls LCM pill. Pumped out of hole to 16;536'; functioned tested diverter and conducted well control drill. Pulled out to 16;035'; noticed hole not taking proper fill-ups. Pumped out hole to 12;061'.

Mr. Steven Scruggs requested and received an additional 24 hour extension for BSR/CSR function test from Mr. Robert Ranney (BSEE) on 11/19/2014. This extension lasts until midnight 11/20/2014. 

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs received verbal approval from Mr. Beau Boudreaux (BSEE) to shallow set the 13-3/4" liner. An RBP will be submitted for this casing design change.

11/20/2014: Continued pumping out from 12;061' to 5;653'. Attempted to function test BSRs/CSRs without success on Blue Pod. Pulled from 5;653' to surface. Clean excess mud and equipment off rig floor; slip and cut drill line. 

Note: Mr. Sheldon Langdon requested and received approval from Mr. Robert Ranney on 11/20/2014 to proceed with running the liner and cementing using Yellow Pod only. Once complete; we will finalize well isolation and pull BOP/LMRP for repairs. 

11/21/2014: Rigged up and began to run 13-3/4" liner. Made up hanger and changed out casing handling equipment with pipe handling equipment.

11/22/2014: Tripped in with 13-3/4" liner to 17;900' on landing string. Made up cement hose; and began to mix and pump 109 bbls of 15.8 ppg Class H cement - 82 bbls (460 cu ft) of annular cement. Chased cement with 12.2 ppg SBM. Bumped plug; bleed pressure off and confirmed floats holding. Set hanger and release from R/T and pumped 1.5 landing string volume. Pumped a slug and pulled landing string
"},{"   ":139,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-11-23","TEXT_REMARK":"11/23/2014: POOH with 13-3/4" liner hanger running tool from 14;114' to surface. Perform casing test against to 3;100 psi for 30 min (successful test). Rig down remaining casing handling equipment. Make up RTTS storm packer assembly and TIH to 4;647'.

Note: On 11/23/2014; Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) requested and received verbal approval from BSEE's Mr. Mark Malbrue to proceed with the negative test and granted approval to displace the riser subsequent to successful positive and negative tests.

11/24/2014: RIH with RTTS at 7;600'. Locate tool joint with annular and set RTTS at 7;600'. Test RTTS storm packer seal to 500 psi (successful test). Test SSC II to 1;000 psi for 5 min (successful test). Spot a 50 bbl 14.2 ppg pill on top of RTTS. POOH to 7;100' and pump 178 bbls of base oil down drill pipe to performed negative test for 30 min (successful test). Bleed back base oil from drill pipe. Displace well and lines from 12.2 ppg SBM to seawater. Close BSRs and perform positive test to 1;000 psi test for 15 min (successful test). POOH from 7;100' to 3;242'.

11/25/2014: POOH with RTTS R/T from 3;242' to surface. Begin to rig up rig floor to unlatch the LMRP and pull riser. Wait on weather.

11/26/2014: Continue waiting on weather until 05:00 hrs. Finish rigging up riser handling equipment. Pick up diverter R/T and take overpull; unlock diverter and lay out same. Make up landing joint; stroke in slip joint and lock. Adjusted weight and unlatch LMRP at 17:20 hrs. Move rig 100m to safe zone and begin pulling riser.

11/27/2014: Pull LMRP from 6;648' to 1;878'.

11/28/2014: Pull LMRP from 1;878' to surface. Move LMRP to set back area and troubleshoot SPM valves. 

11/29/2014: Continue to troubleshoot and repair SPM valves on both pods. Transport LMRP under main rotary and made up double. Splash LMRP and test on double.
"},{"   ":140,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-11-30","TEXT_REMARK":"11/30/2014: Run LMRP from 168' to 2;713' and test Choke; Kill; Boost and Rigid Conduit lines to 250/7500 psi.

12/01/2014: Continue running LMPR to 6;763' and test lines to 250/7500 psi prior to latch up.

12/02/2014: Latch LMRP to BOP. Function test BSR and CSR with both pods per PDC procedure (successful tests). Perform EHBS test (successful test). Install diverter and test (successful test). 

Note: Mr. Sheldon Langdon (Chevron) received approval on 12/02/2014 from Mr. Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) to proceed with operations following the repairs made to the BOP.

12/03/2014: R/D riser running equipment and clean rig floor. TIH with RTTS retrieval tool to 6;338' and shut down. Perform EHBS test per procedure with 1000 psi test (successful test). Continue to RIH to 7;050'. Space out and begin BOP pressure test on 6-5/8" DP from Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod (successful tests). Ram test pressure 250/7500 psi; Annular test pressure 250/6500 psi. Perform function test from Driller's panel; Yellow Pod (successful test). 

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received approval on 12/03/2014 from Mr. Marty Rinaudo (BSEE) to proceed with operations of pulling RTTS and resuming well work.

12/04/2014: POOH 2 stands and function test diverter per procedure (successful test). TIH to 7;050'; line up and displace from 8.6 SW to 12.2 SBM. TIH to 7;582' and unseat RTTS packer. TOH to 2;245'.  

12/05/2014: Continue to POOH with RTTS to surface and rack back. Close BSRs from Drillers panel; Yellow Pod; and perform 13-3/4" casing test to 3100 psi (successful test). Function BSRs and CSRs from Toolpusher's panel; Blue Pod. P/U and RIH with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" BHA. RIH to 7;841' and install the nominal bore protector. POOH to retrieve MPT running tool.

12/06/2014: Continue to POOH and R/B MPT. TIH to tag TOC at 17;681'. Perform choke drills with both crews prior to drilling out cement. Drill cement shoe track while weighting up to 12.7 ppg SBM.  Wash and ream rathole and drilled 10' of new formation to 17;940'. Circulate and condition while preparing for FIT. 
"},{"   ":141,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-12-07","TEXT_REMARK":"12/07/2014: Drilled out float collar; shoe and 10 ft of new formation to 17;940'. Pump 100 bbl hi-vis sweep and circulate bottoms up. Pull into shoe and perform FIT at 17;900' MD with 12.7 ppg SBM to 1;690 psi; 14.5 ppg EMW (good test). Slack off to 17;940' and begin drilling 12-1/4 x 14-1/2 hole section.

12/08/2014: Continue drilling 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section. Exited base of salt at 19;266' MD/ 19;125' TVD. Drill ahead as per salt exit strategy.

12/09/2014: Continued drilling 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section to 19;887' MD. Displaced well to 12.9 ppg SBM; continued circulating and conditioning mud. Increased mud weight to 13.2 ppg due to hole stability.

12/10/2014: Pumped 200 bbl 15.2 ppg weighted sweep. Circulated out sweep; and made mock connection. Drilled to 19;920' MD. Pumped out of the hole to 13-3/4" shoe. Function tested BOP from Driller's panel; Blue Pod; and Toolpusher's panel; Yellow Pod; and function tested Diverter.

12/11/2014: Pump out of hole with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly from 19;162' to 17;880'. Continued TOH from 17;880' to 6;599'. Function test BSR/CSR. TIH from 6;599' to 19;780'. Wash from 19;780' to 19;847'. At 19;847'; hole packed off and injected approximately 55 bbls into the formation; work torque down and jar pipe free.

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE) on 12/11/2014 to proceed with operations to drill to well TD without installing the 11-7/8" liner.

12/12/2014: Jarred pipe free and observed flow with pumps off. Shut well in with 905 psi stabilized SICP. Performed bleed cycles in 100 psi increments to 0 psi SICP; proving trapped pressure due pack off. Monitored well on mini trip tank; well static. Opened well to trip tank; well static. Circulated bottoms up; pumped weighted sweep; and increased mud weight to 13.4 ppg. Washed to bottom; and began drilling 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section to 20;180'.

12/13/2014: Drill 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" hole section to 20;562' MD/ 20;365' TVD. Take Stethoscope measurements. Pump out of hole to 13-3/4" shoe. Circulate 1/2 of bottoms up. Pump slug. POOH with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling assembly.

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs received verbal approval from Mr. Mike Hebert (BSEE) on 12/13/2014 to commence with P&A Operations.
"},{"   ":142,"WELL_NAME":"  002","API12":608084004701,"WAR_START_DT":"2014-12-14","TEXT_REMARK":"12/14/2014: Pulled out of hole with 12-1/4" x 14-1/2" drilling BHA; and rack back same. Performed BSR/CSR function test (Subsea panel/Blue Pod and Driller's panel/ Yellow Pod). Make up 13-3/4" EZSV; and ran in hole with same.

Note: Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. Michael Hebert of BSEE to continue with P&A operations in light of FSV accumulator charge SPM leak on Yellow Pod.

12/15/2014: Ran in hole in with 13-3/4" EZSV; and set at 17;554'. Pressure tested EZSV seals. Squeezed 114 bbls of 16.4 ppg Class H cement below EZSV; placing cement plug from 18;200' to 17;554'. Unstung from EZSV and spotted 45 bbls of 16.4 ppg Class H cement on top of EZSV; placing cement plug from 17;554' to 17;250'. Pulled out of hole with 6 stds of drill pipe; and circulated 1.5x drill string volume. Perform positive test on EZSV/cement plug to 1200 psi for 15 min (good test); and negative test on EZSV/cement plug per procedure monitoring for flow for 30 min (good tests; no flow observed from negative test).

12/16/2014: Make up cement stand with string at 16;255' and spot 108 bbls of 16.4 ppg cement slurry; placing cement plug from 16;255' to 15;655' MD. Pulled out of hole from 16;275' to 14;352'. Put 2 nerf balls in the pipe and circulated 1.5 drill string volumes. Pulled out of hole from 14;352' to surface. Pressure test cement plug from 16;255' to 15;655' to 1;200 psi for 15 min (good test). Make up 16" EZSV and ran in hole to 7;480'.

12/17/2014: Set bridge plug at 7;480'; perform positive to 1200 psi for 15 min and negative test per procedure monitoring for no flow for 30 min (good test). Displace 13.4 ppg SBM with seawater. Mix and pump 137 bbls of 16.4 ppg cement slurry and spot in place with 210 bbls seawater (cement plug from 7;480' to 7;030'). Pulled out of hole from 7;454' to 6;910' insert 2-8" wiper balls and circulated bottoms up. Pulled out of hole from 6;910' to 3;719'.

Note: On 12/17/2014 at 09:49 hrs; Mr. Steven Scruggs (Chevron) received verbal approval from Mr. David LeLeux (BSEE) to waive the BOP pressure test; function test; and Diverter function test due to positive and negative pressure tests that have been performed on 16" bridge plug set at 7;480' and current operations of P&A.

12/18/2014: Continued to POOH from 3;710' to surface. Ran in hole with 8-1/2" jet sub. Wait on cement until suitable compressive strength for tagging. Tag cement at 7;020'; weight test with 30k down; good test. Pulled out of hole with 8-1/2" jet sub to surface. Rig down drill pipe handling equipment. Start rigging up riser handling equipment.

12/19/2014: Rig up spider; pulled diverter; make up landing joint; scope slip joint and lock same. Unlatch BOPs; remove control lines and disengage hands free goose necks. Lay out landing joint and slip joint. Pull riser from 6;763' to 6;133'.

IPT Suretec. Function tested upper & lower blind shear rams from Primary Control Station - Blue Pod. Function tested casing shear rams from Secondary Control Station - Yellow Pod & Primary Control Station - Blue Pod.  PU/MU whipstock BHA and TIH to 8734'.  

Wed - 03/21/18 - TIH with whipstock BHA to 24;071'.  Oriented whipstock 30° right of highside. Continued TIH from 24;071' tagged EZSVB @ 24;221' DPM with 10k down. Pumped 25 bbls super sweep every 5' of window cut.  Took SCR @ 24;187' with 14.8 ppg SBM.  Drilled new formation to 24;226' MD.  Pumped 25 bbls super sweeps as needed.

Thurs - 03/22/18 - Pumped 25 bbl super sweep at 24;226'.  Circulated out same.  Functioned BOPs.
Pumped 15 bbl super sweep down choke and kill lines. Circulated hole clean. Pumped up 2x static mud weight with MWD (15.08 ppg; 15.08 ppg). Closed LAP; performed FIT on 14" shoe @ 23;691' TVD with 14.8 ppg SBM. MWD pumped up 15.64 ppg EMW.  Flow checked well on trip tank; static. Slugged pipe.
POOH with mill asssembly BHA to RKB.  TIH with drillout assembly to 1;113'. Shallow tested MWD.  TIH with drillout assembly to 11;000'.

Fri. - 03/23/18 - TIH with drillout assembly to 24;133'. Washed from 24;133' through window of 14" liner to bottom @ 24;226'MD/23;725'TVD.  Drilling 12.25" hole to 24;506'.  Pumped 30 bbl. super sweep; circulated out. Rotated and reciprocated pipe.  Backreamed from 24;506' to 24;187'.  Flow checked well - well static. Slugged pipe and POOH to 6720'.  Pumped super sweep down choke and kill back to surface from 6718' to flush out BOP.  Pumped down drill string back to surface from 6720'.  POOH to 4;000'.  

Sat. - 03/24/18 - POOH; racked BHA in derrick. TIH with 12.25" drilling BHA to140'. Shallow tested MWD; loaded radioactive sources.  Continued TIH with 12.25" drilling BHA to 19;913'. TIH with 12.25" drilling BHA to 24;424'.  Washed from 24;424 to 24;506'.  Tagged bottom with no fill observed.  Drilled to 24;600'.  

"},{"   ":144,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-03-25","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 03/25/18 - Drilled from 24;600'MD to 26;194'MD (24;927' TVD).

Subsea began Benchmark testing @ 16:00 hrs as per IPT test plan utilizing Halliburton Cement Unit w/ 15.0 ppg SBM; 300 psi / 5 mins; 6;600 psi / 5 mins.  Pressure tested from Secondary test station - Yellow Pod.  Pressure tested BOP pipe rams; annulars; TDX IBOP's; kelly hose and associated BOP and choke manifold valves w/ Halliburton cementer to 250 psi/low 6;600 psi/high 5 min each test; utilizing IPT Sure-Tec w/ 15.0 ppg SBM on 5 7/8" DP from Secondary Control Panel/Yellow Pod. Function tested from Secondary Control Panel/ Yellow Pod in conjunction with BOP test. Monitored well on trip tank; static. Subsea offline pressure tested 5 7/8" IBOP; 2 FOSV's to 250 psi/low; 6;600 psi/high; 5 min each test with subsea test pump.  Function tested BOP's from Primary Control Panel/Blue Pod. Function tested diverter from secondary control panel.  POOH to 5;700'.  Subsea pressure tested choke manifold valves offline with subsea test unit to 250 psi/low; 6600 psi/high; 5 min each test.

Fri. - 03/30/18 - POOH to 1;195'.  Subsea pressure tested choke manifold valves offline with subsea test unit to 300 psi/low; 6600 psi/high; 5 min each test.  POOH with 12.25 drilling BHA to RKB.  Subsea tested 3x 6.625" FOSV's and 6.625" IBOP to 300/6;600 psi for 5/5 min.  Functioned Upper & Lower Blind Shear Rams & Casing Shear Rams F/ Primary Control Station - Blue Pod; Secondary Control Station
Yellow Pod.  P/U E-line Logging toolstring.  RIH w/ Res/sonic/imagers/bore hole profile logging assy on wireline to 29;280'; Logged to 23;900' (ELM).  POOH with Res/sonic/imagers/bore hole profile logging assy on wireline to RKB.  RIH w/ Density/Neutron/Lethal Scanner/CMR/HXPT logging assy to 6000' (ELM).  

Sat. - 03/31/18 - Continued RIH w/ Density/Neutron/Lethal Scanner/CMR/HXPT logging assy to 29;280' (ELM). Logged to 26;450'.  Obtained pressure readings ending @ 28;774'.  POOH w/ Density/Neutron/Lethal Scanner/CMR/HXPT logging assy to 12;000'.  
"},{"   ":145,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-04-01","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 04/01/18 - Continued to POOH and laid out logging assy.  RIH w/ MDT Logging Assy to 27;800'.  Obtained samples.

Pumped 10 bbls of 15.5 ppg TSIII down pipe. Mixed and pumped 73 bbls (408 cu. ft.) 16.4ppg Lead Premium cement. Mixed and pumped 238 bbls. (1335 cu. ft.) 16.4ppg tail Premium cement. Bumped plug with 977 bbls. at 2;520 psi. Checked floats; bled back 6 bbls. Cement in place at 24:00.  Lost returns 220 bbls into displacement. Regained partial returns when lower dart engaged wiper plug @ 603 bbls pumped. Total SBM lost during cement job = 654 bbls. Reciprocated pipe 30' to 40' during job.  Released running tool; set liner packer with 110K down. Closed upper annular; tested packer to 2000 psi - good test.  Circulated drill pipe volume.  Flow checked well; well static. Pumped slug. RD cement head.  POOH with hanger running tool to 16;864'. Mud Losses Last 24 hr. = 752 bbls.

assembly to 10;000 psi for 5 min; on chart. Released running tool from hanger; POOH to 6;680'.  RD and LO cement lines; and cement head. Pumped slug. POOH to 6;137'.
Tested casing to 1;500 psi / 30 min with 15.0 ppg SBM.  Good test.  POOH with hanger running tool to surface. PU 10-3/4" Archer packer and RIH to 7;815'.  Set Archer packer at 7;800'. Closed LAP; tested top of packer to 1;000 psi for 5 min. Opened LAP; test archer packer down string from the bottom to 1;000 psi for 15 min. Released from packer plug. PU above packer; closed LAP and tested packer plug to 1;000 psi for 15 min. All tests performed with 15.0 ppg SBM and on chart.  Located tool joint on LAP; spaced out for negative test.  Pumped 195.5 bbls of 6.6 ppg base oil down string to a differential pressure of 3;050 psi. Closed test rams; bled off differential in 500 psi increments. 3.5 bbl bled back. Performed Negative test for 30 min on chart. No pressure increase observed. Pressured up to 3;050 psi and opened LAP.  

Thurs - 04/12/18 - Displaced well from 15.0 ppg SBM to sea water.  POOH to surface. Began stack hop procedure.  Unlatched at 11:30 a.m. Installed TA cap.  Skid to 003 well.

Fri - 4/13/18 - Waiting to return to 002 for initial completion.

Sat - 4/14/18 - Waiting to return to 002 for initial completion.

Mon - 6/25/18 - Waiting to return to 002 for initial completion

Tues - 6/26/18 - Transferred BOP A from set back to well center. Function tested riser equipment.  Lowered BOP "A" to splash zone.  Tested choke and kill lines with to 250/13;500psi 5/5 min. Tested Boost and rigid conduit lines to 250/5;000 psi 5/5min. Note: Installed Lock down bushing and Tubing head on KC 829 #2 well while prepping BOP's. Tested THD connector with ROV to 14;500 psi for 10 min.

Wed - 06/27/18 - Ran BOP's and riser to 3;295'.  Pressure tested choke and kill lines to 250/13;500 psi 5/5 min. Tested Boost and rigid conduit lines to 250/5;000 psi 5/5min.  Ran BOP's and riser from 3;295' to 6580'.  

Thurs - 06/28/18 - Moved rig over well center.  Latched BOP's @ 05:20 hrs.  EHBS and pressure tested to 1000 psi.  RIH with FMC SLT assembly F/ RKB T/ 7;230'. Landed SLT in well head.  Tested all variable pipe rams and associated valves T/ 250/11;000 psi as per IPT SureTec procedure. Tested all annulars and associated valves T/ 250/7;000 psi as per IPT SureTec. Halliburton performed all tests with 8.6 ppg seawater on 5 7/8" Nu-tec test jt F/ Primary Control Station; Yellow pod; function tested in conjunction with BOP test.  Halliburton continued testing BOP blind shear rams and
associated valves T/ 300/11;000 psi as per IPT SureTec test plan; using 8.6 ppg seawater on 5 7/8" Nu-tec test jt F/ Primary station yellow pod; function tested in conjunction with BOP test. Monitored well on trip tank; well static. Closed upper Blind rams via EHBS. Closed Lower Blind shear rams via ROV hot stab. UBSR; LBSR; UPR; and LPR tested against locks. Functioned and flowed through diverter from both stations. 

Fri - 06/29/18 - Functioned BOP F/ Secondary Panel - Blue Pod on 5 7/8" pipe. Performed Acc drawdown.  POOH and laid down BSR tool F/ 7;230' T/RKB.
Subsea pressure tested (1) 6 5/8" IBOP and (1) TIW with subsea test pump to 250/11000 psi 5min each test.  RIH with Archer Packer over shot assembly F/RKB T/7;790'. Subsea pressure tested remaining 6 5/8" and 5-7/8" TIW's and IBOP's 
with subsea test pump to 250/11000 psi 5 min each test.  Displaced well and lines F/ 8.6ppg seawater T/ 15.0ppg sbm.  Flushed surface equipment with 15.0ppg sbm. Flow checked well - static.  Set down 25k to latch on packer; obtained 25k overpull to verify good latch on fish. Continued rotation while picking up string to unseat packer.
POOH F/ 7;790' T/RKB.  P/U and RIH w/ 8.5" clean out assy  from RKB  to 23;800'.  

Sat - 06/30-18 - Drilled cement F/ 23;800' T/ 23;965'.  RIH F/ 23;965' T/ 25;896'. Tagged with 20k. Washed and reamed @ 415 gpm.
"},{"   ":158,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-01","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 7/1/18 - RIH to 29;195'. Tagged CIBP with 25k down.  Pumped sweeps. Circulated hole clean. Tues - 7/3/18 - POOH; laid out CBL assembly to RKB.  RIH with 8.42" gauge ring and junk basket on wireline to 29;195'; tagged CIBP.  POOH; laid out gauge ring assembly.  RIH with 8.395" Cast Iron Bridge Plug (CIBP) on wireline to 12;719'.  

Wed - 7/4/18 - Continued RIH with same to 14;463' (ELM).  Could not work CIBP beyond 14;463'.  POOH; laid out CIBP assembly and RD wireline.  RIH with 8.5" x 9" displacement assembly to 12;200'.  Pumped 144 bbls of 6.6ppg Base Oil down string. Closed lower annular and test rams.  Negative tested wellbore to 12.84 ppg EMW at 26;229' TVD. Zero pressure gain over 30 minutes. Tested casing to 10;000 psi with 14.8ppg for 30 min as per IPT/SureTec plan. Continued to RIH with clean well assembly to 22;627'.  Note:  On July 4/2018 14:21 hrs Kenny Champagne with LLOG exploration received Verbal approval (attached) from Mike Burdette BSEE Lafayette LA District to set the CIBP after the displacement from mud to brine.

Thurs - 7/5/18 - Continued to RIH with same to 29;186' (DPM).  Tagged CIBP with 10K.  C&C mud.

Fri - 7/6/18 - Flushed lines; cleaned mud pits and shakers in preparation for well displacement.  Function tested BOP's from Primary Control Panel/BluePod; Secondary Control Panel/Yellow Pod on 6-5/8" DP. Function tested diverter from Primary Control Panel.  Displaced choke; kill; and boost lines with 14.8 ppg ZnBr2. Pumped Rig-Chem spacers down pipe followed by 14.8 ppg ZnBr2.  Rotated and reciprocated pipe.  POOH with brush/scraper/displacement assembly to 22;761'.

Sat - 7/7/18 - Cleaned magnets.  RIH to 29;063' (DPM). Cleaned mud pits and shale shakers for completion fluids.  Jetted BOP. Functioned BOP. Jetted BOP with 3 additional passes. Circulated bottoms up.  
"},{"   ":159,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-08","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 07/8/18 - Circulated bottoms up.  PU 2' off bottom and reversed out two casing volumes. POOH to surface laying down & inspecting clean well assemblies. 106.5 lbs of metal recovered from string magnets; 2.75 lbs debris recovered from junk basket. RU wireline.  MU and RIH with 8.42" gauge ring / junk basket on wireline to 15;800'.


Mon - 07/9/18 - Continued RIH with 8.42" gauge ring / junk basket to 28;900' (ELM).  POOH.  MU 8.395" bridge plug assembly.  RIH with 8.395" CIBP assembly to 28;875' (ELM).  Correlated CIBP on depth. Set CIBP at 28;800' WLM.  POOH with CIBP setting tool to 15;100'. 

Tues - 07/10/18 - POOH and LD CIBP setting tool assembly.  RIH with 8.398" sump packer on E-Line to 28;163' (ELM). Correlated sump packer on depth. Set same @ 28;658' (ELM). POOH and LO sump packer setting tools; RD wireline.  PU TCP gun assembly and RIH to 6;038'.

Wed - 07/11/18 - RIH with TCP gun assembly to 23;963'; tagged @ 23;963'.  Attempted to work past 9-7/8" tie back @ 23;963' DPM with no success.  Flow checked well static; POOH with TCP assembly to 7;100'.

Thurs - 07/12/18 - Flow checked; static; POOH with TCP assembly and LD same.  RIH with BOP test assembly on 5-7/8" DP to 7;415'.  Pressure tested BOP from secondary control panel-blue pod.  Tested all variable pipe rams; upper auto IBOP; manual IBOP and associated valves to 250/11;000 psi as per IPT Sure-Tec procedure. Tested all annulars; kelly hose; and associated valves to 250/7;000 psi as per IPT SureTec. Performed all tests with 14.8ppg ZnBr on 5-7/8" pipe against test rams; function tested in conjunction with BOP test.  Troubleshoot leak on Test #4; plug valves leaking on main side stand pipe manifold. Performed BOP test #4 with cement unit as per IPT test plan; UAP; associated failsafe valves; and choke manifold valves to 250/7000psi on 5.875" DP against test rams; using 14.8 ppg ZnBr.  Attempted to perform BOP test # 5 high pressure test failed due to leaking choke manifold valve; greased same.  Performed BOP test #5 from secondary control panel; blue pod. UAP; associated fail safe valves and choke manifold valves to 250/7000 psi on 5.875" DP against test rams; using 14.8 ppg ZnBr.  Attempted to perform BOP test # 6 troubleshoot leak isolating suspected choke manifold valves; re-applying pressure.  Observed lo torque valve in test line to the top drive leaking. Isolated valve; perform offline test.  Attempted to perform BOP test #6; observed the test line isolation valve on main stand pipe manifold leaking. Swapped out same.  Continued testing BOP's from secondary control panel-blue pod.  Tested all annulars; kelly hose; and associated T/250/7;000 psi.  Tested all variable pipe rams; upper auto IBOP; manual IBOP and associated valves to 250/11;000 psi as per IPT Sure-Tec procedure. Performed all tests with 14.8ppg ZnBr on 5 7/8" pipe against test rams; function test in conjunction with BOP test.

Fri - 07/13/18 - Continued testing BOP's from secondary control panel-blue pod. Test all annulars; kelly hose; and associated T/250/7;000 psi.  Tested all variable pipe rams; upper suto IBOP; manual IBOP and associated valves to 250/11;000 psi as per IPT Sure-Tec procedure. Performed all tests with 14.8ppg ZnBr on 5-7/8" pipe against test rams; function tested in conjunction with BOP test.  Function tested BOP from primary control panel - yellow pod. Functioned diverter from secondary control panel. POOH to RKB.  Function tested BSR's from primary control panel - yellow pod; secondary control panel - blue pod.  RIH with string mill assembly to 24;175'.  Rotated and reciprocated pipe from 24;035' to 24;159' working string mills from 23;849' to 24;077' (25 passes).  TIH with string mill assembly from 24;159' to 28;571'.  Washed from 28;571' to 28;668'.  Stung into sump packer @ 28;668' DPM.  PU & reverse circulated.

Sat - 07/14/18 - Reverse circulated.  Flow checked; well static.  POOH to surface.  Tested casing from primary control panel - yellow pod to 10;000 psi against LBSR's with 14.8 ZnBr for 30 minutes.  PU 6-5/8" TCP gun assembly and RIH to 15;167'.

"},{"   ":160,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-07-15","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 07/15/18 - RIH with TCP gun assembly to 28;668'. PU TCP head.  Put guns on depth.  Set packer.  Closed UAP. Cycled ball valve open and circulating valve closed. Began fire sequence.  Guns fired @ 16:56hrs; with 18 SPF TCP guns. Monitored well against closed choke for 30 min.  Perforations at 28;400-28;650'MD 26;029'-26;154' TVD (WLM).  Cycled ball valve closed and circulating valve open. Reverse circulated above packer.  Took returns to rig poorboy degasser.
