Closed master valve; performed negative test on master valve for 5 min; recorded on chart.  Good test. Pressured up to 11;000 psi opened master valve; bled on chart. Good test. Pressured up to 11;000 psi opened master valve; bled to 0 psi.  TEST 3: Pressure up to 11;000 psi against lubricator valve; production wing valve and crown valve.  Closed kill wing valve; bled pressure to 500 psi. Performed negative test of kill wing valve for 5 min; record on chart. Good Test. Pressured up to 11;000 psi opening kill valve; bled to 0 psi.  Broke out lubricator. MU 2.125" bailer tool string; MU lubricator and tested to 11;000 psi; utilizing quick test sub.  Lost commmunications with SLB wireline tool string.  Lay out same to troubleshoot. 
"},{"   ":166,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-08-26","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 08/26/18 - Continued to troubleshoot e-line communication issue with tool string.  PU e-line tools. MU lubricator.  Tested lubricator to 11;000 psi. Opened LV; opened SCSSV. RIH with e-line bailer to 28;400'.  POOH with e-line bailer to RKB.  Encountered tight spots.  Changed out wireline tools.  Established communication and performed checks on tool string.  PU/MU tool string; MU and tested lubricator to 11;000 psi.  RIH with bailer tool string on e-line to 26;415' ELM.  Washed from 26;415' to 28;319' ELM.  POOH with bailer tool string on Eline from 28;319' logging up to 25;500'.  Continue to POOH from 25;500' to 9;500' ELM.

Mon - 08/27/18 - POOH with bailer tool string; LO same.  PU Schlumberger Collapsible shifting tool assembly and tested lubricator to 11;000 psi. Opened LV and RIH with shifting tool to 26;400' (ELM).  Tools lost communication. Trouble shoot same.  POOH with shifting tool to RKB.  Trouble shoot tools; found issue with weight bar.  RIH with shifting tool to 28;297' ELM.  Made several attempts to open MSV sleeve in UW 4B - Tool not working.  POOH with shifting tool.  Closed LV. LD shifting tool assembly and RD e-line equipment.  RU slickline equipment.

Tues - 08/28/18 - Continued to RU slickline equipment and lubricator. MU 2.5" shifting tool. Tested lubricator to 11;000 psi.  RIH with shifting to 27;702'.  Encountered obstruction not allowing shifting tool to reach sleeve #5.  POOH.  RIH with bailer F/RKB to 27;432' (ELM).  Stuck bailer at 27;432' worked string free. POOH with slickline. RD same. RU e-line equipment. PU shifting tool assembly.  RIH with collapsible shifting tool on e-line from RKB to 14;000'.

Wed - 08/29/18 - RIH with collapsible shifting tool on e-line to 28;252' ELM.  Unable to get down to 28;297' ELM.  POOH with shifting tool to 26;000' ELM. Pressured up to 2;500 psi surface pressure; bled off same through Cetco choke; surged tubing 3 times.  RIH with shifting tool to 28;297' ELM.  Pressured up on tubing shifting upper MSV-O in UW-4B @ 28;297' ELM.  Observed 800 psi loss indicating sleeve open.  PU and located upper MSV-O in UW-4A @ 27;702' ELM; shifted open sleeve. PU locate upper MSV-O in UW-3 @ 27;358' ELM.  Attempted to shift sleeve open; observed reduced operating pressure on shifting tool. Decision made to POOH and change e-Line tools.  POOH with e-Line from 27;358' ELM to RKB.  PU new shifting tool assembly and RIH with shifting tool on e-line to 26;512' ELM.  Located MSV-O sleeve @UW-1; shifting sleeve open on UW-1 @ 26;514' ELM.  Located MSV-O sleeve @ UW-2; shifted sleeve open on UW-2 @ 26;929' ELM.  Located MSV-O sleeve @ UW-3; attempted to shift sleeve on UW-3 @ 27;357' ELM.

Thurs - 08/30/18 - Shifted sleeve open on UW-3 @ 27;357' ELM.  POOH with shifting tool on e-line.  Closed LV; RD lubricator and e-line tools.  Opened LV and turned well over to CETCO @ 10:18 hrs & flowed Upper Wilcox sand.  

Fri - 08/31/18 - Continue flowback:  Shut in Well.  Spotted 85 bbls 9.2 ppg MEG in workstring followed by seawater.: Swept BOP's below MPR's while displacing the choke
line from 13.0 CaBr to 8.6 ppg SW - No gas observed on sweep. Displaced Boost Line with 8.6 ppg SW. Displaced riser above MPR's from 13.0 CaBr to 8.6 ppg SW. Monitored pressure build.  RD slickline BOP; installed night cap on flow head. 

Sat - 09/01/18 - Continued to monitor pressure build while rigging down.  Opened PMV; bullheaded 75 bbls of MEG down tubing.  Closed kill wing valve. With 
SCSSV closed; bled pressure down on landing string to 500 psi.  Performed negative test on SCSSV. Recorded on chart for 30 minutes. Good test. Swept BOP with seawater under MPR's. Closed PMV; bled off 400 psi @ choke; performed negative test on PMV; recorded on chart for 15 minutes. Good test. Bled to zero and closed PSV.
Closed UAP; opened MPR's. Unlatched SSTT.  Swept BOP's and landing string with 
seawater. IWOC's tested ASV and PSV to 13;500 psi @ mud line for 15 minutes each from below. Opened UAP; Monitored well - well static.  POOH with SSTT and landing string to RKB.  Unlatched BOP's @ 05:20 hrs.  Moved rig to safe zone.  
"},{"   ":167,"WELL_NAME":"SS002","API12":608084006001,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-02","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 09/2/18 - Continued pulling riser and BOP's.   Landed BOP A on Beams @ 00:00 hrs.  Final Report."},{"   ":168,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-05-27","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 05/27/18 -POOH to surface. RIH with Baker 12.25" drilling assembly to 
24;707'.   Tagged FasDrill packer @ 24;707'. Drilled packer and hard cement to 24;817'. 

Mon - 05/28/18 - Continued drilling packer and hard cement to 25;101'. POOH to 25;025'. Pumped up two static mud weights with Baker MWD @ 14.1; 14.19 ppg. Pumped in 12 bbls of 14.0 ppg at 1 bpm; began pumping in at 796 psi. Shut down 2 min. press. bled back to 630. Pumped in another 2 bbls at .5bpm. 732psi. Shut down 2 min; 640 psi. Pumped in 2 bbls @ .5bpm; 740psi; total of 16 bbls. Bled back 13 bbls. Pumped up equivalent of 14.8 ppg.  Circulated bottoms up. Pumped slug. POOH with 12.25" drilling assembly to surface. RB BHA in derrick.

Tues - 05/29/18 - RIH with cement stinger to 25;101'.  Pumped 82 bbls of 15.2 ppg TS III lead spacer followed by 150 bbls (842.2 cu.ft.) of 16.4 ppg class H cement.
Pumped 18 bbls of 15.2 ppg TS III spacer; followed by 20 bbls of 14.0 ppg SBM. Displaced cement with 590 bbls of 14.0 ppg SBM.  POOH with cement stinger to 23;200'.  Closed LAP; squeezed 90 bbls of cement. Max squeeze pressure 1430 psi.
After 1 hour; squeezed 5 bbls;max squeeze pressure 1159 psi. Waited additional 1 hr; squeezed 2 bbls; max squeeze pressure 1380 psi. Total pumped 104 bbls. Waited on cement holding 600 psi.

Wed - 05/30/18 -  Continued to wait on cement holding 600 psi. Bled off squeeze pressure. Opened LAP and flow checked well. Pumped slug. POOH to surface.
Functioned LBSR; CSR; and UBSR from primary control panel/yellow pod and secondary control panel/blue pod.  RIH with 12.25" x 14.5" drilling BHA to 21;706'. Function tested BOP's on 5-7/8" drill pipe from Primary Control Panel/Yellow Pod and Secondary Control Panel/Blue Pod. Functioned Diverter from Primary Control Panel.
TIH with 12.25" x 14.5" BHA to 24;100'.  

Thurs - 05/31/18 - Washed soft cement from 24;100' to 25;095'. Bypassed from 25;095' to 25;127'.  Bypassed from 25;127 to 25;140'. Drilled 10' formation F/25;140' T/25;150'.  Pumped up 2x static mwt. with MWD: 14.29 & 14.27 ppg. Closed LAP; performed FIT #1 on 14" shoe at 23;352' TVD w/ 14.0ppg; 1365 psi. MWD pumped up 15.38 ppge.  Drilled 12.25" hole from 25;150' to 25;190'.  Pumped up 2x static mwt. 14.24 & 14.26 ppg. Closed annular; performed FIT #2; 1201psi. Opened annular and pumped up 15.25 ppge.  Drilled 12.25" hole from 25;190' to 25;210'.  Pumped up 2x static mwt: 14.25 & 14.23 ppg. Closed annular and performed FIT #3 w/ 1421psi.  Pumped up 15.41 ppge with MWD.  Drilled 12.25" hole F/25;210' T/25;515'.  Raised mud wt to 14.5 ppg while drilling.  Note: Mr. David LeLeux with BSEE granted verbal approval to obtain the FIT for KC 829 003  5-31-18.  

Fri - 06/01/18 - Drilled 12.25" hole 15' to 25;566'.  Flow checked. POOH wet from to 24;941'.  Pumped slug. POOH to surface.  TIH with 12.25" Drilling BHA to 109'. Surface tested MWD.  Changed out TesTrak and LithoTrak. Surface tested MWD. TIH with 12.25" BHA to 13;000'.


Sat - 06/02/18 - TIH with 12.25" BHA to 25;482'. Washed down from 25;482' to 25;566'. Drilled 12.25" hole to 27;136'.  
"},{"   ":169,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-03","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 06/03/18 - Drilled 12.25" hole to 27;888'. Obtained stretch log. Took pressures. Drilled 12.25" hole from to TD of 28;800' (26;697' TVD). Pumped 100 bbls Hi-vis weighted sweep. Circulated hole clean.  Raised mud wt from 14.6 ppg to 14.7 ppg while circulating. Flushed choke & kill line with 14.7 ppg. 

Mon - 06/04/18 - Circulated hole clean.  POOH wet to 28;097'. Took 60k overpull at 28;097'. Attempted to wipe area with no success.  Backreamed out of hole to 24;943'.  
Pumped 100 bbls Hi/Vis weighted sweep; circulated hole clean.  Rotated and reciprocated pipe. Subsea performed offline bench mark tests to 250 / 6;700 psi on IPT/SureTec system.  POOH wet to 21;618'. MU double dutch assembly. Located on LAP with 5-7/8" drill pipe. Began BOP pressure test. Tested BOP Annulars; Pipe rams; and failsafes against test rams with 14.7 ppg SBM on 5-7/8" DP to 300 / 6;700 psi for 5 min each test from Secondary control station/ Yellow Pod on IPT/Suretec system.  Function tested in conjunction with pressure test. Function tested BOP from Primary control station - Blue Pod. Functioned diverter from Secondary control station.  TIH to 25;877'. Washed and reamed from 25;877' to 28;800'.  


Tues - 06/05/18 - Continued pressure testing BOP's 300 / 6700 psi. Function tested in conjunction with pressure test. Function tested BOP from Primary control station - Blue Pod. Functioned diverter from Secondary control station.  TIH to 25;877'. Washed and reamed from 25;877' to 28;800'.  Pumped 100 bbl hi-vis sweep and circulated out bit. Backreamed out hole from 28;800' to 24;943'.  Pumped slug and POOH to surface. 
MU wireline tools and RIH with wireline run #1. 

Wed - 06/06/18 - RIH with wireline run #1 28;770 WLM. Logged from 28;770' to 25'024' WLM. POOH with wireline run #1 to RKB. LD wireline tools.  M/ and RIH with wireline run #2 to 23;917' WLM.  Damaged wire armor; installed T-Bar on wireline to secure wire at rotary table. Removed damaged armor strand from wireline. POOH to 7;775' (WLM).

Thurs - 06/07/18 - POOH to RKB.  RIH with wireline run #2 to 28;760' WLM.
Correlated depth; began logging up F/ 28;760' T/ 27;500'.  POOH with wireline run #2 to RKB. Removed radioactive sources and LD toolstring. Pick up wireline run #3 to 16;000'. 

Fri - 06/08/18 - RIH with wireline run #3 MDT from 16;000' to 28;684' WLM.  Took samples/pressures. Flushed Choke; Kill and boost lines with 14.7 ppg.

Sat - 06/09/18 - Continued taking pressures and samples w/ wireline run #3 MDT.
POOH with wireline run # 3 MDT to RKB.  TIH with 12.25" BHA from RKB to 27;400'. Washed to 28;800'.  Rotated and reciprocated drill pipe while circulating a High Vis sweep. 
"},{"   ":170,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-10","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 06/10/18 - Backreamed out of hole slowly while circulating hole clean from 28;800' to 28;339'. Mud wt. in and out 14.7 ppg.  Performed flow check; well static. POOH from 28;339' to 15;024'.  Function tested BOP (annulars and pipe rams; failsafe valves) on 5 7/8" drill pipe from Primary Control Station/ Yellow pod; from Secondary Control Station/ Blue pod. Function tested diverter from Primary Control Station. Continued POOH from 15;024' to RKB.  Functioned Upper Blind Shear Rams; Lower Blind Shear Rams and Casing Shear Rams from Primary Control Station Yellow Pod; and Secondary Control Station Blue Pod.  Picked up 9.875" shoe track from RKB to 171'. Ran 9.875" casing from 171' to 2;833'.

Mon - 06/11/18 - Ran 9.875" casing from 2;833' to 4;018'.  P/U Baker 9 7/8" liner hanger.  RIH to 4;084'. Ran 9 7/8 casing on 6 5/8" landing string from 4;084' to 28;611'.  Mixed and pumped 685 cu-ft 16.4 ppg Premium Lead Cement & 593 cu-ft 16.4 ppg Premium Tail Cement. Started displacement at 8 BPM.

Tues - 06/12/18 - Continued displacing cement. Bumped plug with 1000 psi over displacement pressure (2000 psi). Full returns and no losses during cement job.
Set Packer. Set 100k down on Packer.  Closed LAP; tested packer down backside to 
1800 psi; good test.  Opened LAP.  Pulled packoff from liner top @ 24;724'. Closed LAP.  TOL @ 24;726' & 9.875" Shoe depth @ 28;800'.  Opened LAP; performed flow check; well static. Pumped slug. POOH with landing string from 24;724' to RKB. TIH with EZSV from RKB to 6;636' MD.

Wed - 06/13/18 - TIH with EZSV from 6;636' to 28;672' MD.  Washed from 28;672' to 28;662'. Set CIBP inside 9 7/8" liner @ 28;672'. Weight tested with 20k down. Closed UAP. Tested CIBP; 9 7/8" casing and liner top to 1;500 PSI/30 minutes with 14.7 ppg. 
SBM. Flow checked well on trip tank for 5 minutes; well static. POOH from 28;643' to 6;850'.  

Thurs - 06/14/18 - POOH with CIBP setting tool from 6;855' to RKB. TIH with polish mill assy from RKB to 24;708'. Polished 9 7/8" liner top @ 3 bpm with 12k down for 5 minutes.  Tagged 9 7/8" TOL w/ 10K down; function closed LAP and LPR. Opened back up; pumped 65 bbl slug while picking up out of PBR. POOH with polish mill assembly from 24;748' to 8;613'. Functioned BOP from Primary Control Station Yellow Pod & Secondary Control Station Blue Pod. Functioned Diverter from Secondary Control Station.  POOH with polish mill assembly from 8;613' to 8;400'. 

Fri - 06/15/18 - POOH with polish mill assembly from 8;400' to RKB.  P/U FMC SLT assembly to 200'. RIH on 6 5/8" landing string from 200' to 6;723'.  Washed wellhead/wear bushing @ 6;723'. RIH from 6;723' to 6;876'; landed SLT in wear bushing @ 6;723'. Pulled wear bushing with 48k over pull. POOH to 6;723' (bull nose depth). Washed wellhead. Circulated bottoms up.  Flushed choke/kill lines w/ 14.7 ppg.  POOH with wear bushing from 6;723' to RKB.  

Sat - 06/16/18 -  Ran seal assembly and orifice collar to 128'. Picked up and ran 10-1/8" casing from 218' to 18;020'.  Made up FMC hanger. Rigged down the remaining casing equipment; installed remaining landing string handling equipment and OES flow back tool and service loop. RIH with 10.125X10.750 casing on landing string from 18;020' to 18;476'.
"},{"   ":171,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-06-17","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 06/17/18 - RIH with 10.125 x 10.750 casing on landing string from 18;476' to 24;594'.  MU cement head. POOH w/ 10 1/8" x 10 3/4" Tieback on landing string to 18020'. 10 3/4" Tieback hanger @ surface. Observed all 10 shear pins had sheared. Tool did not shift and no damage to hanger noted. Hanger reset; installed 5 shear pins same.  TIH with 10.125 X10.750 casing on landing string from 18;020' to 24;730'.  M/U cement head. RIH; stung into liner top.  Mixed and pumped 3595 cu-ft 16.4# Premium Cement.

Mon - 06/18/18 - Displaced cement with 1;345 bbls of 14.7 ppg SBM. Slacked off; landed hanger in wellhead @ 6;727'. Rotated to release hanger.  Broke circulation down kill line with 14.7 ppg. Closed Upper Pipe Rams; tested hanger to 10;000 PSI for 5 minutes. Good test.  POOH with 6 5/8" landing string and hanger running tool from 6;727' to RKB. Halliburton tested 10 1/8" x 10 3/4" casing with 14.7 ppg against UBSR to 1;500 PSI for 30 minutes; utilized IPT. Good test. PU and RIH with Archer packer from RKB to 7718' on 6 5/8" drill pipe.  MU TDX Slack off put archer packer on depth @ 7813'. Set packer plug. Closed lower annular and pressure tested the top of the plug with cementer 1;000 psi for 5 mins.  Opened annular and pressure tested down the drillpipe; tested bottom of archer plug 1;000 psi for 15 mins. Recorded on chart. Closed ball valve in archer plug and released from plug.  Tested top of Archer plug 1;000 psi for 15 mins. Recorded on chart. Opened annular. RU lines and pressure tested to 3;000 psi.  Performed negative test; pumped 186.5 bbls of base oil down drill pipe achieved differential pressure of 2;681 psi. Closed test ram on BOP and bled off in 500 psi increments to 100 psi. Recorded negative test on chart for 30 mins.  Displaced choke; kill; boost and well from SBM to Seawater. 

Tues - 06/19/18 - POOH with Archer packer running tool from 7;802' to RKB.
PU diverter running tool. Locked in and performed 20k overpull test on diverter. Pulled & laid down diverter.  (Significant Event) Suspended riser operations due to high current.  Waited on weater.

Wed - 06/20/18 - Continued with suspension of riser operations due to high current.  Waited on weather.

Thurs - 06/21/18 - Continued with suspension of riser operations due to high current.  Waited on weather.

Fri - 06/22/18 - Continued with suspension of riser operations due to high current.  Waited on weather.

Sat - 06/23/18 - Continued with suspension of riser operations due to high current.  Waited on weather.

"},{"   ":182,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-09-02","TEXT_REMARK":"Mon - 09/03/18 - Transferred Mux cables from BOP A to B.  Function tested BOPs from Primary Control Station/Blue Pod; Secondary Control Station/Yellow Pod.  Performed soak test on BOP and pods.  Draw down tested from Primary Control Station/Blue Pod. Drift BOP.  Skid BOP to well center.  Prepped moon pool for running BOP & riser.  Ran riser and BOP "B" to 2;100'.

Tues - 09/04/18 - Ran riser and BOP "B" to 6;585'.  Tested choke and kill lines to 250/10;700 for 5/5 minutes.  Tested boost and conduit lines to 250/5;000 psi for 5/5 minutes.  Moved vessel over well center.  Landed and latched BOP's.  RD riser running tool. RU elevators and PU diverter and slacked off into position locked in same.  Started bench mark testing as per IPT test plan from primary control panel-yellow pod using 8.6 seawater. 300 psi 5 min; 10;700 psi 5 min.  Function tested in conjunction with pressure test. MU BSRTT BHA.  Function tested diverter from primary control panel and secondary control panel. TIH with BSRTT on 6-5/8" drill pipe to 7;230' and landed out.  Began offline testing of choke and kill manifold as per IPT test plan using 8.6 seawater. 300 psi 5 min; 10;700 psi 5 min.

Wed - 09/05/18 - Tested UAP and LAP on 5-7/8" pipe to 250/7;000 psi. Performed Tree Gallery test via ROV to 13;500 psi and charted for 5min.  Tested surface equipment to 10;700 psi for 5 min on chart. Aligned surface tree and manifolds for opening SCSSV. Pressured up 3;800 psi and opened SCSSV.   Opened Upper IWS; pressured up on landing string to 3500 psi ( 18;960 psi DH) and closed upper IWS.
Equalize pressure across Lower IWS sleeve; opened same. Pressured up on tubing to shear X-RFV; observed 25;476 psi on Lower IWS & 19;450 psi on Upper IWS when AFV shifted.  Handed over well to Cetco @ 02:30 hrs. Began flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. Initial UW4 Sand Reading @ 0300 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 18;873 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 220°F; Annulus PSI 6;370; Choke Pressure 3;488 PSI on 14/64 Choke; Gas Rate 0 MMscfd; Oil Rate 0 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day.
 
Sat - 10/20/18 - Continued flowing well as per LLOG/Cetco flowback procedure. 
Reading @ 0500 hrs: Down Hole Lower Pressure 17;221 psi; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;704; Choke Pressure 7;295.48 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .467 MMscfd; Oil Rate 6;971 bbl/day; Water Rate 116.7 bbl/day.

"},{"   ":189,"WELL_NAME":"SS003","API12":608084006101,"WAR_START_DT":"2018-10-21","TEXT_REMARK":"Sun - 10/21/18 - Continued well flow operations.  Shut in lower zone on Cetco choke @ 06:30 hrs.  Final Reading for UW4 sand @ 0600 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 17;202 PSI; Down Hole Temperature 231°F; Annulus PSI 7;727; Choke Pressure 7;312.92 psi on 18/64 Choke; Gas Rate .459 MMscfd; Oil Rate 7;014.4 bbl/day; Water Rate 58.2 bbl/day.  Equalized pressure in tubing; shifted upper IWS sleeve. Closed KWV; bled pressure to 0 psi. Shifted upper sleeve.  Turned well over to Cetco; flowed upper zone as per LLOG procedure. Initial Reading for upper sands @ 1000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 18;666 psi; Down Hole Temperature 223°F; Annulus psi 7;126; Choke Pressure 8;232.67 psi on 12/64 Choke; Gas Rate .19 MMscfd; Oil Rate 3;074.50 bbl/day; Water Rate 0 bbl/day.

Mon - 10/22/18 - Continued well flow operations by flowingd upper zone as per LLOG procedure.  Shut well in @ 00:20 hrs @ Cetco Choke.  Closed upper IWS sleeve. Final Reading for upper sands @ 0000 hrs: Down Hole Pressure 19;091 psi; Down Hole Temperature 226°F; Annulus psi 7;537; Choke Pressure 9;030.26 psi on 22/64 Choke; Gas Rate .803 MMscfd; Oil Rate 9;322.1 bbl/day; Water Rate 504.9 bbl/day. Equalized pressure between Common DHPT and Lower DHPT; Closed PMV and SCSSV. Spotted 10 bbls MEG + 25 bbls of 10.6 CaCl2 plus 100 bbls of Soap in kill line.  

Tues - 10/23/18 - Spotted 75 bbls MEG in landing string and bullheaded across tree and SSCSV.  Shifted lower IWS closed.  Closed KWV; bled off. Bled 1;000 psi off landing string to 8;000 psi. Performed negative test on SCSSV for 30 minutes on chart (Good Test). Closed PMV; bled pressure on landing string to 0 psi. Closed Cetco choke; opened KWV. Applied 100 psi down landing string against PMV. Closed KWV; bled off 
pressure. Performed negative test on PMV for 15 minutes; recorded on chart (Good Test).  IWOCS applied 12;700 psi as recorded @ PTU through CIT1. Tested PSV; PMV; PWV for 15 minutes. Recorded tests via IWOCS @ PTU. Cetco chart PSV (Good Test).  Unlatched SSTT; verified unlatch. Sweep stack under UAP with seawater. Spotted 50 bbls soap pill down kill line taking returns up landing string through Cetco choke. Continued sweeping landing string with 50 bbls soap pill.   Boosted riser with seawater.  POOH with SSTT to RKB; LD same. 

Wed - 10/24/18 - Unlatch BOP "B".  Moved vessel SW to safe zone. ROV installed TA cap on EVDT.  Pulled riser to 1070'.  

Thurs - 10/25/18 - Pull riser to 145' . RD moon pool. Put BOP on Beams @ 10:20 hrs.
RD riser running tool.  Jetted BOP 3x passes through BOP. Cleared rig floor of riser running equipment. Vessel under way from KC 829 safe zone to location MC 257 safe zone @ 13:00 hours.  FINAL REPORT.
